Hamm Peak ( 69 ° 43′S 74 ° 8′E ) is a small rock peak just back from the coast of Antarctica , standing close south of Strover Peak and 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) west - northwest of Mount Caroline Mikkelsen .
Mount Hassage ( 75 ° 51′S 72 ° 29′W ) is a prominent isolated mountain , 1,120 metres ( 3,670 ft ) high , located 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) southwest of Mount Horne in Palmer Land , Antarctica .

The Gruber Mountains ( German : Otto - von - Gruber - Gebirge ) are a small group of mountains consisting of a main massif and several rocky outliers , forming the northeast portion of the Wohlthat Mountains in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Manning Island is an island in the vicinity of Antarctica .
The Morrison Hills ( 84 ° 12′S 168 ° 40′E ) are a series of rugged east -- west trending hills between Garrard Glacier and Hewson Glacier in the Queen Alexandra Range of Antarctica .

Amundsen Icefall ( 85 ° 28′S 166 ° 42′W ) is a steep and turbulent icefall where the Axel Heiberg Glacier descends from the polar plateau between Mount Fridtjof Nansen and Mount Don Pedro Christophersen , in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .

Wilson Hills ( 69 ° 40′S 158 ° 30′E ) is a group of scattered hills , nunataks and ridges that extend NW - SE for about 110 kilometres ( 68 mi ) between Matusevich Glacier and Pryor Glacier in Antarctica .

Onogur Islands ( Bulgarian : Оногурски острови , `` Onogurski ostrovi '' \o - no-'gur - ski ' os - tro - vi\ ) is the group of nine islands and some islets and rocks adjacent to the northwest coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Algae Lake ( 66 ° 18′S 100 ° 48′E ) is a narrow , winding lake , 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) long and between 0.2 and 1 nautical mile ( 0.4 and 1.9 km ) wide , extending in an east -- west direction in the ice - free Bunger Hills of Antarctica .
Ferrell Buttress ( 79 ° 57′S 159 ° 2′E ) is a distinctive rock buttress , about 900 metres ( 3,000 ft ) high , near the east end of Cranfield Icefalls , on the south side and near the terminus of Darwin Glacier in Antarctica .
Peacock Sound is an ice - filled sound , 216 kilometres ( 134 mi ) long and 64 km ( 40 mi ) wide , separating Thurston Island from the Eights Coast of Ellsworth Land in Antarctica .
Lagrelius Point ( 63 ° 55′S 58 ° 17′W ) is a low , ice - free point on the northwest side of James Ross Island , Antarctica , 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) south of Carlson Island .
The Ingrid Christensen Coast is that portion of the coast of Antarctica lying between Jennings Promontory , in 72 ° 33′E , and the western end of the West Ice Shelf in 81 ° 24′E. It is located in the western half of Princess Elizabeth Land , just east of the Amery Ice Shelf .
Helen Glacier Tongue ( 66 ° 33′S 94 ° 0′E ) is a glacier tongue which extends seaward from Helen Glacier on the coast of Antarctica .
Madrid Dome ( Bulgarian : купол Мадрид , `` Kupol Madrid '' \'ku - pol ma-'drid\ ) is the ice dome rising to 1650 m at the southwest extremity of Aristotle Mountains on Oscar II Coast , Graham Land in Antarctica .
Grotto Island is a narrow island 0.5 nautical miles ( 1 km ) long with a serrated coastline , lying 0.1 nautical miles ( 0.2 km ) north of Galindez Island in the Argentine Islands , Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Crutch Peaks is a dark , rocky ridge extending 900 m in north - south direction and rising to 275 m in the north extremity of Dryanovo Heights , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Hélène Island is a small rocky island 370 metres ( 0.2 nmi ) northwest of Ifo Island marking the west end of the Géologie Archipelago in Antarctica .
Gateway Nunatak ( 77 ° 1′S 160 ° 15′E ) is a prominent nunatak near the head of Mackay Glacier , standing 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) west of Mount Gran , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Burkett Nunatak ( 72 ° 42′S 162 ° 14′E ) is a nunatak , 2,180 metres ( 7,150 ft ) high , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) east of Minaret Nunatak , in the Monument Nunataks , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Hargreaves Glacier ( 69 ° 46′S 74 ° 20′E ) is a glacier 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) west of Mount Caroline Mikkelsen on the Ingrid Christensen Coast of Antarctica .
The Mackellar Islands , also MacKellar Islets , are a group of about 30 small islands and rocks lying 3 kilometres ( 1.5 nmi ) north of Cape Denison in the center of Commonwealth Bay , Antarctica .
The Dunedin Range ( 71 ° 24′S 167 ° 54′E ) is a northwest - trending mountain range , 37 km ( 23 mi ) long and 3 to 6 km ( 2 to 4 mi ) wide , located 8 km east of Lyttelton Range in the Admiralty Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Cape Mikhaylov ( 66 ° 54′S 118 ° 32′E ) is an ice - covered point about 42 nautical miles ( 78 km ) east of Totten Glacier , Wilkes Land , Antarctica .
Horseshoe Harbour ( 67 ° 36′S 62 ° 52′E ) is a harbour in Holme Bay , Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica , formed by the horseshoe - shaped rock projections of West Arm and East Arm .
Ferrer Point is a point projecting 700 m into the south part of Discovery Bay , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica with an adjacent ice - free area of 24 hectares ( 59 acres ) .
Ravelin Ridge is a ridge which extends north - south and rises to 1400 m ( Jerez Peak ) in northern Clarence Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Kinntanna Peak ( 71 ° 53′S 8 ° 21′E ) is a sharp peak , 2,725 metres ( 8,940 ft ) high , about 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) north of Holtanna Peak in the eastern part of Fenriskjeften Mountain in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Mount Ethelwulf ( 70 ° 2′S 69 ° 34′W ) is a mainly ice - covered mountain , 2,590 metres ( 8,500 ft ) high , standing between Mount Egbert and Mount Ethelred at the head of Tumble Glacier , in the Douglas Range of northeast Alexander Island , Antarctica .
The Fringe Rocks ( 66 ° 4′S 65 ° 55′W ) are a group of rocks forming the western limit of the Saffery Islands , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Honkala Island is a rocky island , 1.4 kilometres ( 0.75 nmi ) long , at the southeast side of Burnett Island , in the Swain Islands of Antarctica .
Tufts Pass ( 69 ° 25′S 70 ° 35′W ) is a pass extending in an east - west direction between the Rouen Mountains and the Elgar Uplands in the north part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Haffner Pass ( 69 ° 47′S 71 ° 22′W ) is a pass running northeast -- southwest and rising to about 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) between Gilbert Glacier and Mozart Ice Piedmont in northern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
The Elephant Rocks in Antarctica are a group of three prominent rocks connected by shoals , located between Torgersen Island and the north - west entrance to Arthur Harbour , off the south - west coast of Anvers Island .
The Hydrographer Islands are a prominent group of small islands in the bay just south of Sakellari Peninsula , Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Mount Lacey ( 70 ° 11′S 64 ° 43′E ) is a high , pyramidal , brown rock mountain with two sharp peaks , standing 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) west of Mount Béchervaise in the Athos Range , Prince Charles Mountains , Antarctica .
Quaver Nunatak ( 71 ° 0′S 70 ° 17′W ) is a small nunatak rising to about 250 m , lying in the northernmost exposure of the Walton Mountains , situated in the central portion of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Manoury Island is an island lying 3 kilometres ( 1.5 nmi ) south of Gand Island at the north end of Schollaert Channel , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Harter Nunatak ( 81 ° 14′S 84 ° 54′W ) is a small , relatively isolated nunatak lying 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) northeast of Mount Tidd at the northeast side of the Pirrit Hills in Antarctica .
Mount Waesche is a large and prominent mountain of volcanic origin , standing immediately SW of Mount Sidley and marking the southern end of the Executive Committee Range in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
High Nunatak ( 80 ° 3′S 82 ° 35′W ) is an isolated nunatak 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) east of the Liberty Hills in the Heritage Range of the Ellsworth Mountains , Antarctica .
Honnør Glacier ( 69 ° 23′S 39 ° 50′E ) is a glacier flowing to the east side of Lützow - Holm Bay , Antarctica , to the north of the Byvågåsane Peaks .
Hobbs Peak ( 77 ° 53′S 163 ° 55′E ) is a prominent peak , 1,510 metres ( 4,950 ft ) high , on the divide between Hobbs Glacier and Blue Glacier in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Liston Nunatak ( 70 ° 54′S 63 ° 45′W ) is a large nunatak immediately northwest of Heintz Peak in the Welch Mountains of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Pomorie Point ( Nos Pomorie \'nos po-'mo - ri - e\ ) is a point on the coast of McFarlane Strait forming the north side of the entrance to Lister Cove , Varna Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Liberty Rocks is a group of four prominent adjacent rocks lying at the north entrance to Nelson Strait in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and extending 430 by 120 m ( 470 by 131 yd ) .
Togo ( i/ˈtoʊɡoʊ/ ) , officially the Togolese Republic ( French : République Togolaise ) , is a country in West Africa bordered by Ghana to the west , Benin to the east and Burkina Faso to the north .
Hanson Peak ( 71 ° 21′S 170 ° 18′E ) is a small peak , 1,255 metres ( 4,120 ft ) high , 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) south of Cape Adare in the northern part of Adare Peninsula , Antarctica .
The Ohio Range ( 84 ° 45′S 114 ° 00′W ) is a mountain range in the Transantarctic Mountains of Antarctica .
Cape Lloyd ( 61 ° 7′S 54 ° 1′W ) is a cape which forms the north end of Clarence Island in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica , on the north side of the entrance to Kutela Cove .
Balan Ridge ( Bulgarian : хребет Балан , `` Hrebet Balan '' \'hre - bet ba-'lan\ ) is the ridge rising to 800 m ( 2,600 ft ) in the Sofia University Mountains on Alexander Island in Antarctica .
Mount Rossman ( 79 ° 47′S 82 ° 48′W ) is a prominent wedge - shaped , ice - free mountain , 1,450 m , located at the north end of the Enterprise Hills between Union and Henderson Glaciers , in the Heritage Range in Antarctica .
Flynn Glacier ( 81 ° 31′S 159 ° 21′E ) is a glacier about 10 nautical miles ( 20 km ) long , draining eastward from Mount Nares in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica , and entering Starshot Glacier south of Kelly Plateau .
The McKinzie Islands are a group of small islands in the northeastern extremity of Cranton Bay , Antarctica .
Świba ( ˈɕfiba ) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kępno , within Kępno County , Greater Poland Voivodeship , in west - central Poland .
The Magdalena River Valley ( Spanish : El Valle del Río Magdalena ) is a valley in Colombia located within the Colombian Andes mountain ranges .
A Time for Drunken Horses ( Central Kurdish : کاتێک بۆ مەستیی ئەسپەکان , Persian : زمانی برای مستی اسب‌ها‎‎ , Zamani barayé masti asbha , Kurdish : Demek jibo hespên serxweş‎ ) is a 2000 Iranian ( Kurdish / Persian ) film directed by Bahman Ghobadi and produced in Iran .
Silence in Dreamland ( Spanish : Silencio en la tierra de los sueños ) is a 2013 Ecuador drama film directed by Tito Molina .
Saint Luke Drawing the Virgin is an oil and tempera on oak panel painting attributed to the Early Netherlandish artist Rogier van der Weyden .
The Fairy Feller 's Master - Stroke is a painting by English artist Richard Dadd .
Go Set a Watchman is a novel by Harper Lee published on July 14 , 2015 , by HarperCollins in the United States and William Heinemann in the United Kingdom .
Violon et raisins ( Violins and Grapes ) is a 1912 painting by Pablo Picasso .
Valdemar Atterdag holding Visby to ransom , 1361 is a historical painting ( oil on canvas , signed in 1882 ) by the Swedish historical painter Carl Gustaf Hellqvist ( 1851 -- 1890 ) .
The Finding of Erichthonius is a fragment of a larger painting by Peter Paul Rubens , produced around 1632 or 1633 .
The Situation Room is a photograph taken by White House photographer Pete Souza in its namesake , the White House Situation Room , at 4:06 pm on May 1 , 2011 .
Law & Order is an American police procedural and legal drama television series , created by Dick Wolf and part of the Law & Order franchise .
Evening Mood ( Humeur Nocturne ) is a painting by William - Adolphe Bouguereau in 1882 , now in the collection of the Havana 's Museum of Fine Arts , in Cuba .
Mary Magdalen in Ecstasy ( 1606 ) is a painting by the Italian artist Michelangelo Merisi da Caravaggio ( 1571 - 1610 ) .
Kelewan is one of the fictional worlds described by Raymond E. Feist and Janny Wurts .
Not Going Out is a British television sitcom that has aired on BBC One since 2006 , currently starring Lee Mack , Sally Bretton and Katy Wix .
Lying Cow is the name of two oil paintings created by Vincent van Gogh around 1882 when he was living at The Hague .
The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy ( also known as Billy & Mandy ) is an American animated television series created by Maxwell Atoms for Cartoon Network , and the fourteenth of the network 's Cartoon Cartoons .
The San Marco Altarpiece ( also known as Madonna and Saints ) is a painting by the Italian early Renaissance painter Fra Angelico , housed in the San Marco Museum of Florence , Italy .
Goethe in the Roman Campagna is a painting from 1787 by Johann Heinrich Wilhelm Tischbein , a German Neoclassical painter , depicting Johann Wolfgang von Goethe whilst the writer was travelling in Italy .
Phantom 2040 is a French - American animated science fiction television series loosely based on the comic strip hero The Phantom , created by Lee Falk .
The BBC Nine O'Clock News was the flagship BBC News programme .
Wainy Days is an internet video series starring David Wain that is hosted on the website , My Damn Channel .
Porthos , Baron du Vallon de Bracieux de Pierrefonds is a fictional character in the novels The Three Musketeers , Twenty Years After and The Vicomte de Bragelonne by Alexandre Dumas , père .
In 1956 , a writer from the Perry Mason radio show , Irving Vendig , created a retooled idea for daytime television -- and The Edge of Night was born .
The Portrait of Pietro Aretino is a portrait of the Renaissance poet Pietro Aretino by Titian , painted around 1545 , possibly for Cosimo I de ' Medici .
The O'Reilly Factor , originally titled The O'Reilly Report from 1996 to 1998 and often called The Factor , is an American cable television news and talk show on the Fox News Channel hosted by political commentator Bill O'Reilly , who often discusses current controversial political issues with guests .
Shearing the Rams is an 1890 painting by the Australian artist Tom Roberts .
Absolutely Fabulous , also known as Ab Fab , is a BBC television sitcom created by , written by and starring Jennifer Saunders .

A Young Man in a Fur Cap and a Cuirass ( probably a Self Portrait ) is a 1654 portrait painting by Carel Fabritius .
Bear Surprise ( often dubbed just `` Surprise ! '' ) is a watercolor painting by American painter / musician John Lurie , the style of which has been described as primitivist and naïve .

Space Duel is an arcade game released in 1982 by Atari Inc. It is a direct descendant of the original Asteroids , with asteroids replaced by colorful geometric shapes like cubes , diamonds , and spinning pinwheels .

Vindhya Pradesh was merged into Madhya Pradesh in 1956 , following the States Reorganisation Act .
The Second Polish Republic , also known as the Second Commonwealth of Poland or interwar Poland , refers to the country of Poland between the First and Second World Wars ( 1918 - -1939 ) .
Colonial Brazil ( Portuguese : Brasil Colonial ) comprises the period from 1500 , with the arrival of the Portuguese , until 1815 , when Brazil was elevated to a kingdom alongside Portugal as the United Kingdom of Portugal , Brazil and the Algarves .
From its founding in 1701 to 1918 , the Order of the Black Eagle was awarded 407 times , with 57 of these installations during the reign of Friedrich I ( 1701 - -1713 ) .

Bank of Boston had a venerable history dating back to 1784 , but the merged BankBoston was short - lived , being acquired by Fleet Bank in 1999 .
The Lohara dynasty were Hindu rulers of Kashmir between 1003 and approximately 1320 .

In mathematics , a Cauchy sequence ( French pronunciation : ​(koʃi ) ; English pronunciation : /ˈkoʊʃiː/ KOH - shee ) , named after Augustin - Louis Cauchy , is a sequence whose elements become arbitrarily close to each other as the sequence progresses .

The Mincer earnings function is a single - equation model that explains earnings as a function of schooling and experience , named after Jacob Mincer .
The Feast of the Ascension of Our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ , also known as Ascension Thursday , Holy Thursday , or Ascension Day , commemorates the bodily Ascension of Jesus into heaven .
EFnet or Eris - Free network is a major IRC network , with more than 35,000 users .
The Hilbert numbers were named after David Hilbert .
Ricardian economics are the economic theories of David Ricardo , an English political economist born in 1772 who made a fortune as a stockbroker and loan broker .
Daggett Brook was named for Benjamin F. Daggett , a lumberjack who felled trees there .

The Kurchatov Medal , or the Gold Medal in honour of Igor Kurchatov is an award given for outstanding achievements in nuclear physics and in the field of nuclear energy .
In mathematics , a Noetherian topological space , named for Emmy Noether , is a topological space in which closed subsets satisfy the descending chain condition .
The Memorial to the Murdered Jews of Europe ( German : Denkmal für die ermordeten Juden Europas ) , also known as the Holocaust Memorial ( German : Holocaust - Mahnmal ) , is a memorial in Berlin to the Jewish victims of the Holocaust , designed by architect Peter Eisenman and engineer Buro Happold .
Shimon HaTzadik is a Jewish neighborhood in East Jerusalem , established around the Tomb of Simeon the Just , after whom it was named .
Viviani 's theorem , named after Vincenzo Viviani , states that the sum of the distances from any interior point to the sides of an equilateral triangle equals the length of the triangle 's altitude .
In mathematics , Helmut Hasse 's local - global principle , also known as the Hasse principle , is the idea that one can find an integer solution to an equation by using the Chinese remainder theorem to piece together solutions modulo powers of each different prime number .
The Gosper curve , also known as Peano - Gosper Curve , named after Bill Gosper , also known as the flowsnake ( a spoonerism of snowflake ) , is a space - filling curve .

The Grimme - Preis ( `` Grimme Award '' ; up to 2010 : Adolf - Grimme - Preis ) is a television award and one of the most prestigious awards for German television .
In mathematics , the Hurwitz problem , named after Adolf Hurwitz , is the problem of finding multiplicative relations between quadratic forms which generalise those known to exist between sums of squares in certain numbers of variables .
Kochite is found in the alkaline igneous complex of East Greenland and is named after Danish geologist Lauge Koch ( 1892 - 1964 ) , a geologist who overturned the previous conception of Greenland 's landscapes .
Macphersonite is named after Harry Gordon Macpherson , a keeper of minerals at the Royal Scottish Museum .
The J J Ebers Award was established in 1971 with the intention to foster progress in electron devices and to commemorate the life activities of Jewell James Ebers , whose distinguished contributions , particularly in the transistor art , shaped the understanding and technology of electron devices .
The Langhian was a continuing warming period defined by Lorenzo Pareto in 1865 , it was originally established in the Langhe area north of Ceva in northern Italy , hence the name .
In mathematical logic , the Mostowski collapse lemma is a statement in set theory named for Andrzej Mostowski .
In mathematics , Osgood 's lemma , introduced by William Fogg Osgood ( 1899 ) , is a proposition in complex analysis .
The Erdős number ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈɛrdøːʃ ) ) describes the `` collaborative distance '' between mathematician Paul Erdős and another person , as measured by authorship of mathematical papers .

The Wien bridge is a type of bridge circuit that was developed by Max Wien in 1891 .

Faraday 's laws of electrolysis are quantitative relationships based on the electrochemical researches published by Michael Faraday in 1834 .

In mathematical analysis Hölder 's inequality , named after Otto Hölder , is a fundamental inequality between integrals and an indispensable tool for the study of Lp spaces .

Tomichia is a genus of very small freshwater snails which have a gill and an operculum , gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .

Cryptobatrachus is a genus of frogs under family Hemiphractidae .
The Australian mottled moray ( in Australia ) , and mottled moray ( in New Zealand ) , Gymnothorax prionodon , is a moray eel of the family Muraenidae , found at depths down to 80 m. Their length is between 80 and 150 cm .
Phunginus apicalis is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Phunginus .
Adelphailurus is an extinct genus of saber - toothed cats of the family Felidae and tribe Metailurini which inhabited western North America during the Miocene , living from 10.3 - -5.33 Ma and existing for approximately 4.97 million years .
Brazza 's martin ( Phedina brazzae ) is a passerine bird in the swallow family , Hirundinidae .
Tertremoides is an extinct genus of trematosaurian temnospondyl within the family Trematosauridae from Madagascar .
Tenagodes is a genus of sea snails with irregularly coiled shells , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Siliquariidae , the slit worm snails .
Censky 's ameiva or Little Scrub Island ground lizard ( Ameiva corax ) is a lizard species in the genus Ameiva .
Jay 's river snail also known as the rugose rocksnail , scientific name Lithasia jayana , is a species of small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Pleuroceridae , the hornsnails .
The Peruvian eagle ray ( Myliobatis peruvianus ) is a species of fish in the Myliobatidae family .
The North American river otter ( Lontra canadensis ) , also known as the northern river otter or the common otter , is a semiaquatic mammal endemic to the North American continent found in and along its waterways and coasts .
The Uddenitinae a subfamily of the Medlicottiidae , a family of ammonoid cephalopods included in the Prolecanitida .
It was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Dalbergia clade of the Dalbergieae .
Centaurium ( Centaury ) is a genus of 20 species in the gentian family ( Gentianaceae ) , tribe Chironieae , subtribe Chironiinae .
Latzelia is an extinct genus of scutigeromorph centipedes , and the type and only genus of the family Latzeliidae .
Roscoea is a genus of perennial plants of the family Zingiberaceae ( the ginger family ) .
The Brazilian ruby ( Clytolaema rubricauda ) is a species of hummingbird found in forest edge , second growth , gardens and parks in eastern Brazil .
The Micronesian myzomela ( Myzomela rubratra ) is a species of bird in the honeyeater family Meliphagidae .
Beetles are members of the superorder Endopterygota , and accordingly most of them undergo complete metamorphosis .
Stenella is a genus of aquatic mammals in Delphinidae , the family informally known as the oceanic dolphins .
In the 1981 version of the influential Cronquist system , order Violales was placed in subclass Dilleniidae with a circumscription consisting of the families listed below .
The Hispaniolan slider ( Trachemys decorata ) or Haitian slider is a species of turtle in the Emydidae family .
Pliauchenia is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America during the Pliocene .
Rhytidognathus is a genus of beetle in the family Carabidae with two described species .
Astroloba is a genus of flowering plants in the subfamily Asphodeloideae , native to the Cape Province of South Africa .
Pastinachus is a genus of stingrays in the family Dasyatidae .
The Chinese pygmy dormouse ( Typhlomys cinereus ) is a species of rodent of the family Platacanthomyidae found in China and Vietnam .
Ellobiidae is the only family in the superfamily Ellobioidea , according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Bishop 's slender opossum ( Marmosops bishopi ) is a small , arboreal marsupial opossum native to Brazil , Peru , and Bolivia .
Plaisiodon is an extinct genus of Zygomaturinae from the late Miocene Alcoota Fossil Beds in the Northern Territory , Australia .
Danilia is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs of the family Chilodontidae .
Anderson 's squirrel ( Callosciurus quinquestriatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Cynomya ( Ancient Greek : κυνόμυια kunomuia `` dog - fly '' ) is a genus in the family Calliphoridae of flies .
Together with Spinacia , the genus Blitum was grouped into tribe Anserineae ( Syn . Spinacieae ) .
Enneapterygius nanus , known commonly as the Pygmy triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
The Magenta petrel or Chatham Island taiko ( Pterodroma magentae ) is a small seabird in the gadfly petrel genus , Pterodroma .
The Sulawesi dwarf kingfisher ( Ceyx fallax ) is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae that is endemic to Sulawesi island , Indonesia .
The Grand Comoro bulbul ( Hypsipetes parvirostris ) is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
Noorda is a genus of moths of the Crambidae family , and the only genus in the Noordinae subfamily .
The November moth ( Epirrita dilutata ) is a moth of the family Geometridae .
The Clostridia are a highly polyphyletic class of Firmicutes , including Clostridium and other similar genera .
Oryzoideae ( syn . Ehrhartoideae ) is a subfamily of the true grass family Poaceae .
Delacour 's marmoset rat ( Hapalomys delacouri ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Far Eastern smooth flounder , Liopsetta pinnifasciata , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
Taurotragus is a genus of large African antelopes , placed under the subfamily Bovinae and family Bovidae .
The Luzon forest rat or Luzon hairy - tailed rat ( Batomys granti ) is one of five species of rodent in the genus Batomys .
Aglaodiaptomus is a genus of copepods in the family Diaptomidae .
In Genera Orchidacearum volume 2 , Pachites and Satyrium constitute the subtribe Satyriinae of the tribe Diseae .
Murchisonelloidea is an unassigned superfamily of mostly very small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks and micromollusks within the clade Heterobranchia .
Sparganophilus , the only genus in the family Sparganophilidae , is a group of long , slender , limicolous ( mud - dwelling ) earthworms native to North America .
Pontomyia Edwards , 1926 is an insect genus belonging to the subfamily Chironominae in the Chironomidae family .
Genus Parabelminus Lent , 1943 belongs to the subfamily Triatominae .
HIV is a member of the genus Lentivirus , part of the family Retroviridae .
The Indian pitta ( Pitta brachyura ) is a passerine bird native to the Indian subcontinent .
Opahs ( also commonly known as moonfish , sunfish ( not to be confused with Molidae ) , kingfish , redfin ocean pan , and Jerusalem haddock ) are large , colorful , deep - bodied pelagic lampriform fishes comprising the small family Lampridae ( also spelled Lamprididae ) .
Zieria is a genus of plants in the Rutaceae family , all of which are native to Australia except for one species which is found in New Caledonia .
Bathyraja is a large genus of skates in the family Rajidae .
Helcion is a genus of sea snails , true limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Patellidae .
Pseudohomalenotus bicornutus is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Measles virus ( MeV ) is a single - stranded , negative - sense , enveloped ( non - segmented ) RNA virus of the genus Morbillivirus within the family Paramyxoviridae .
Pachyneuria is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae found from Mexico to South America .
Ailuroedus is a genus of birds in the Ptilonorhynchidae family ( bowerbirds ) .
Eurymyrmex is an extinct genus of ant in the Formicidae subfamily Dolichoderinae .
Oxytenis is a genus of moth in the family Saturniidae and subfamily Oxyteninae .
Eurillas is a genus of greenbuls , songbirds in the bulbul family ( Pycnonotidae ) .
Serratia is a genus of Gram - negative , facultatively anaerobic , rod - shaped bacteria of the Enterobacteriaceae family .
Dioscoreophyllum is a genus of three species of flowering plants in the family Menispermaceae , native to Africa .
Psoinae is a small subfamily of beetles in the family Bostrichidae .
Carpinus japonica ( Japanese hornbeam ) is a hornbeam endemic to Japan but cultivated elsewhere as an ornamental .
The Sulawesi streaked flycatcher ( Muscicapa sodhii ) is a small passerine bird in the Old World flycatcher family .
Micropanope is a genus of crabs in the family Xanthidae , containing one exclusively fossil species and the following species :
The Eurasian dotterel ( Charadrius morinellus ) , or in Europe just dotterel , is a small wader in the plover family of birds .
The Salvin 's anetia ( Anetia cubana ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Calantica is a genus of barnacles in the family Calanticidae , containing the following species :
Erythrotrichiaceae is a red algae family in the order Erythropeltidales .
Godman 's tree frog ( Tlalocohyla godmani ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae endemic to Mexico .
Baecacanthus is a genus of beetles in the family Cerambycidae , which contains Baecacanthus telamon and Baecacanthus trifasciatus .
Klunzinger 's wrasse , Thalassoma rueppellii , is a species of wrasse endemic to the Red Sea .
Acer nigrum ( Black maple ) is a species of maple closely related to A. saccharum ( sugar maple ) , and treated as a subspecies of it by some authors , as Acer saccharum subsp .
The Paederinae are a subfamily of the Staphylinidae , rove beetles .
Uncinula necator ( syn . Erysiphe necator ) is a fungus that causes powdery mildew of grape .
Ennominae is the largest subfamily of the geometer moth family ( Geometridae ) with some 9,700 described species in 1,100 genera .
Enoplometopus antillensis ( commonly dwarf reef lobster , Atlantic reef lobster or flaming reef lobster ) is a species of reef lobster endemic to the Atlantic Ocean .
Monophyllites is an extinct cephalopod genus belonging to the family Ussuritidae that lived during the Triassic period , from Anisian to Ladinian age .
Hippa is a genus of decapod crustaceans in the family Hippidae , containing the following species :
Leleupanillus uluguruanus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Leleupanillus .
This genus alone makes up the monogeneric Trichocentrum alliance , a quite distinct lineage of the subtribe Oncidiinae .
Migmocera flavicauda is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Migmocera .
Eoporis is a genus of beetles in the family Cerambycidae , containing the following species : subgenus Eoporimimus Eoporis bifasciana Schwarzer , 1925 Eoporis differens Pic , 1926 Eoporis mitonoi ( Seki , 1946 ) Eoporis pedongensis Breuning , 1969 subgenus Eoporis Eoporis elegans Pascoe , 1864
The Salinas monjita ( Xolmis salinarum ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Shinto shrew ( Sorex shinto ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Philippine dawn bat , ( Eonycteris robusta ) , is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae found in the Philippines .
Philby 's partridge or Philby 's rock partridge ( Alectoris philbyi ) , is a relative of the chukar , red - legged partridge and barbary partridges and is native to southwestern Arabia and northern Yemen .
The Patagonian weasel ( Lyncodon patagonicus ) is a small mustelid that is the only member of the genus Lyncodon .
The Japanese pugnose grenadier ( Nezumia condylura ) is a species of rattail fish .
Huodendron is a genus of four species of flowering plants in the family Styracaceae , native to eastern Asia , from southern China south to Thailand and Vietnam .
The Jaeger 's anetia ( Anetia jaegeri ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The Junin slender opossum ( Marmosops juninensis ) is a species of South American opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Bovine ephemeral fever ( BEF ) also known as Three Day Sickness is an arthropod vector - borne disease of cattle and is caused by the Ephemerovirus virus of the Rhabdoviridae family of virus .
Brunneria is a genus of praying mantises in Family Mantidae .
The Cundinamarca antpitta ( Grallaria kaestneri ) is a species of bird in the Grallariidae family .
Cochlicopidae is a taxonomic family of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Swinhoe 's snipe , Gallinago megala , also known as forest snipe or Chinese snipe , is a medium - sized ( length 27 - -29 cm , wingspan 38 - -44 cm , weight 120 gm ) , long - billed , migratory wader .
The Tanzanian woolly bat ( Kerivoula africana ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Protogenia escheri is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Protogenia .
The Chin Hills wren - babbler ( Spelaeornis oatesi ) is a bird species in the family Timaliidae .
Poirieria is a genus of large predatory sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Muricidae , the rock snails .
The Indian rhinoceros ( Rhinoceros unicornis ) , also called the greater one - horned rhinoceros and great Indian rhinoceros , is a rhinoceros native to the Indian subcontinent .
Temecla is a genus of Neotropical hairstreak butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
Orchideae is a tribe of orchid in the subfamily Orchidoideae .
The species Taï Forest ebolavirus is a virological taxon included in the genus Ebolavirus , family Filoviridae , order Mononegavirales .
Trepostomata ( the trepostomates ) is an extinct bryozoan order in the class Stenolaemata .
Lates macrophthalmus , the Albert lates , is a species of lates perch endemic to Lake Albert in Africa .
Tylopoda ( meaning `` swollen foot '' ) is a suborder of terrestrial herbivorous even - toed ungulates belonging to the order Artiodactyla .
Pink ivory ( Berchemia zeyheri ) , also called purple ivory , red ivory , umnini or umgoloty , is an African hardwood used to make a variety of products ( for example : billiard cues and knife handles ) .
The Bismarck masked flying fox ( Pteropus capistratus ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae found in Papua New Guinea and named after the Bismarck Archipelago .
The Apinae are the subfamily that includes the majority of bees in the family Apidae .
The Antipodes parakeet or Antipodes Island parakeet ( Cyanoramphus unicolor ) is endemic to the Antipodes Islands of New Zealand , one of two parrot species found on the islands , and one of only five ground - dwelling parrots in the world .
Phyllospadix , surfgrass , is a genus of seagrass , a flowering plant in the family Zosteraceae , described as a genus in 1840 .
Psittacanthus , also parrott - flower , is a plant genus in the family Loranthaceae .
The name Bothriechis is derived from the Greek words bothros and echis that mean `` pit '' and `` viper '' respectively .
Vermilacinia , a genus of lichenized fungi in the family Ramalinaceae , is a yellow - green fruticose type of lichen with about 30 species that grow on rocks , trees , and soil within the fog zone along the Pacific Coast of North America and South America .
Dactylella is a genus comprising 72 species of mitosporic fungi in the family Orbiliaceae .
Chontalia cyanicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Chontalia .
Plaumannium denticolle is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Plaumannium .
Merrilliopanax is a genus of flowering plant of family Araliaceae , comprising 3 species of the sub - genus Airampora .
Myrsinaceae , or the myrsine family , was formerly recognized as a rather large family from the order Ericales , consisting of 35 genera and about 1000 species .
The Madagascan hoopoe ( Upupa epops marginata ) is a subspecies of hoopoe in the Upupidae family .
Ctenophryne aequatorialis ( common name : Cuenca Nelson frog , reflecting its earlier placement in Nelsonophryne ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
The subfamily Xylocopinae ( family Apidae ) occurs worldwide , and includes the large carpenter bees ( tribe Xylocopini ) , the small carpenter bees ( tribe Ceratinini ) , the allodapine bees ( tribe Allodapini ) , and the relictual genus Manuelia ( tribe Manueliini ) .
The Eldorado broad - nosed bat ( Platyrrhinus aurarius ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .

Incilius is genus of toads in the true toad family , Bufonidae .
Melithaea is a genus of octocorals in the family Melithaeidae .
Both Tylosaurus and Hainosaurus are grouped together into the subfamily Tylosaurinae and are referred to informally as `` tylosaurines '' or `` tylosaurs . ''
Corypheae is a tribe of palm trees in the subfamily Coryphoideae .
Encyrtinae is a subfamily of parasitic wasps in the family Encyrtidae .
Currently , the venom of a different species of pit viper , Agkistrodon rhodostoma , is used to isolate a thrombin - like enzyme called ancrod .
Rivetina is a genus of praying mantises in the family Mantidae , of the order Mantodea .
Allomycterus pilatus also known as the Deepwater burrfish is a porcupinefish of the family Diodontidae , found in the eastern Indian Ocean , and southern Australia and New Zealand .
The Sulawesi white - handed shrew or Temboan shrew ( Crocidura rhoditis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The members of the Uroteuthis genus are the only squids of the Loliginidae family that possess photophores ( light - emitting organs ) and all species in the genus have a pair of photophore organs on the ventral surface of their ink sac either side of their intestine .
Dollman 's tree mouse ( Prionomys batesi ) is a poorly understood climbing mouse from Central Africa .
The Humaita antbird ( Schistocichla humaythae ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
The Tanimbar starling ( Aplonis crassa ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .

Pseudoparalegoceratidae is one of six families of the Somoholitaceae superfamilia .
The New Mexico hotspring snail , scientific name Pyrgulopsis thermalis , is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Goliath birdeater ( Theraphosa blondi ) is a spider belonging to the tarantula family Theraphosidae .
Deiphon is a distinctive genus of Silurian phacopid trilobites of the family Cheiruridae found in Western and Central Europe , and in Central and Eastern United States .
The New Zealand urchin clingfish ( Dellichthys morelandi ) is a clingfish , the only species in the genus Diplocrepis .
Argopecten is a genus of saltwater clams , or scallops , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Pectinidae .
Acrocanthosaurus is classified in the superfamily Allosauroidea within the infraorder Tetanurae .
The Bismarck whistler ( Pachycephala citreogaster ) is a species of bird in the Pachycephalidae family , which is endemic to the Bismarck and Louisiade Archipelagos in Papua New Guinea .
Rhynchaeites is an extinct genus of Threskiornithidae related to modern ibises and has a single named species Rhynchaeites meselensis .
In their 1997 book Classification of Mammals , Malcolm C. McKenna and Susan K. Bell ranked Simplicidentata as a mirorder within the grandorder Anagalida ( also including lagomorphs , macroscelideans , and some additional extinct groups ) .
Nyctibatrachus anamallaiensis ( Anamallai night frog ) is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family that is endemic to the southern Western Ghats , India .
The Chiribiquete emerald ( Chlorostilbon olivaresi ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Bonaparte 's nightjar ( Caprimulgus concretus ) , also known as the Sunda nightjar , is a species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .

Eubranchus is a genus of aeolid nudibranch in the family Eubranchidae .

The Luzon fanged frog ( Limnonectes macrocephalus ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
The inclusion of the Sinoceratidae in some classifications in the Lituitida instead of the Orthocerida is based in part on the idea that the Lituitidae are included in the Orthocerida rather than as originally perceived in the Tarphycerida .

Nelusetta ayraud also known as the Chinaman - leatherjacket is a filefish of the family Monacanthidae , found around Australia to depths of about 360 metres ( 1,180 ft ) .
The Mexican golden trout ( Oncorhynchus chrysogaster ) is a species of fish in the Salmonidae family .
Criopsis curtus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Criopsis .
Gracupica is a genus of Asian birds in the family Sturnidae .
Kionoceratidae is a family in the Orthocerida , proposed by Hyatt in 1900 for genera characterized by prominent ornamentation in the form of longitudinal ribs , ridges , or lirae , or combinations thereof , sometimes with similar transverse ornament or faint transverse annulations .
An extensive DNA study showed three discrete clades , or genetic groups , consisting of the black morels ( Morchella elata and others ) , the yellow morels ( Morchella esculenta and others ) , and the white morels ( Morchella rufobrunnea and Morchella anatolica ) .
Teratosphaeria is a genus of fungi in the family Teratosphaeriaceae ; according to the 2007 Outline of Ascomycota , it was placed in the Phaeosphaeriaceae , but the placement within this family was uncertain .
Polymesoda is a genus of clams in the family Corbiculidae , or alternately , the Cyrenidae .
Enneapterygius mirabilis , known commonly as the Miracle triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
The Caspian plover ( Charadrius asiaticus ) is a wader in the plover family of birds .
Pseudocyon was assigned to Amphicyoninae by Hunt in 1988 and to Amphicyonidae by Lartet ( 1851 ) , Carroll ( 1988 ) and Pickford et al .
Acanthacris aithioptera Acanthacris deckeni Acanthacris elgonensis Acanthacris ruficornis Genus Acanthacris belongs to subfamily Cyrtacanthacridinae ( W.F. Kirby , 1902 ) , which belongs to the same order ( Orthoptera ) as crickets ( Gryllidae ) , locusts ( Acrididae ) , katydids ( Tettigoniidae ) , and other grasshoppers .
Bactroceras is a genus of the family Baltoceratidae , orthoceroid cephalopods that lived during the early Middle Ordovician , from about 472 - -464 mya , existing for approximately 8 million years .
The Mackenzie River wolf ( Canis lupus mackenzii ) is a subspecies of the gray wolf , Canis lupus , and is found in the Canadian Northwest Territories .
Arkelloceras is an early Middle Jurassic ( Bajocian stage ) Stephanoceratacean ( Ammonitina ) genus from arctic Canada , Alaska , and Siberia belonging to the family Otoitidae ( Imlay 1984 , Westermann 1965 ) Arkelloceras seems to be a direct descendant of Abbasites and is thought to have given rise to Ermoceras and possibly to Thamboceras .
Galeodea is a genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cassidae .
Acanthocleithron chapini is the only species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) in the genus Acanthocleithron of the family Mochokidae .
Frigidispora is a fungal genus in the Ascomycota division .
The Emei music frog ( Babina daunchina ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Natalina is a genus of medium - sized predatory air - breathing land snails , carnivorous terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Rhytididae .
Pleurococcus is a genus of green algae , in the family Chaetophoraceae , purported to be the most abundant organism on the planet at ten trillion trillion .
Gelsemium is an Asian and North American genus of flowering plants belonging to family Gelsemiaceae .
Borophagus ( `` gluttonous eater '' ) is an extinct genus of the subfamily Borophaginae , a group of canids endemic to North America from the Late Miocene epoch through the late Pliocene epoch 12 - -2 Mya .
Conidae ( also previously referred to as Coninae ) , with the current common name of `` cone snails '' , is a taxonomic family ( previously subfamily ) of predatory sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Conoidea .
The Valle tree frog , Hypsiboas rubracylus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia and possibly Ecuador .
The Sacramento beetle ( Anthicus sacramento ) is a species of ant - like flower beetle that is endemic to California in the United States .
The Pacific ocean perch ( Sebastes alutus ) , also known as the Pacific rockfish , Rose fish , Red bream or Red perch has a wide distribution in the North Pacific from southern California around the Pacific rim to northern Honshū , Japan , including the Bering Sea .
The Felder 's tiger ( Parantica phyle ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Hinde 's babbler ( Turdoides hindei ) , also known as Hinde 's pied - babbler , is a species of bird in the Leiothrichidae family .
Horvath 's rock lizard ( Iberolacerta horvathi ) is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .
The genus Sericulus of the family Ptilonorhynchidae consists of three spectacularly colored bowerbirds .
Eriopidion is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described as a genus in 1976 .
Canarium is a genus of about 100 species of tropical and subtropical trees , in the family Burseraceae .
Misonne 's soft - furred mouse or Misonne 's praomys ( Praomys misonnei ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Corsican hare ( Lepus corsicanus ) , also known as the Apennine hare or Italian hare , is a species of hare found in southern and central Italy and Corsica .
Traditionally , the Myodocopa and Podocopa have been classified as subclasses within the class Ostracoda , although there is some question about how closely related the two groups actually are .
Goniodelphis hudsoni is an extinct genus of Iniidae ( river dolphin ) known from the waters of Florida during the Miocene ~14.9 - -11.5 through 9.1 - -8.7 Ma ( AEO ) .
The Guerreran stream frog , Ptychohyla erythromma , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Mexico .
Speocolpodes franiai is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Speocolpodes .
Benthamiella is a genus of plants in the Solanaceae family , native to Patagonia in southern South America .
The Puerto Rican nightjar or Puerto Rican whip - poor - will ( Antrostomus noctitherus ) is a very rare bird found in the coastal dry scrub forests in localized areas of southwestern Puerto Rico .
Afrolicania is a genus of plant in family Chrysobalanaceae described as a genus in 1921 .
Leptosema is a genus of flowering plants from the legume family Fabaceae .
Olindias is a genus of jellyfish in the family Olindiidae .
The Hispaniolan hutia ( Plagiodontia aedium ) is one of several hutia ( also called zagouti , and jutía in Spanish ) species to have inhabited at some time the island of Hispaniola ( island shared by Haiti and the Dominican Republic ) .
The Tumbes round stingray , Urobatis tumbesensis , is a little - known species of round ray , family Urolophidae , known only from two immature male specimens collected from estuarine waters at depths of 1 - -2 m , and a third specimen collected in 2006 near mangroves .
Astroloma is an endemic Australian genus of around 20 species of flowering plants in the family Ericaceae .
Trimeroceras is a straight oncocerid ( Nautilodea , Cephalopoda ) from the Middle and Upper Silurian of Europe , and type for the Trimeroceratidae .
Dimeroceratidae is one of three families in the Dimeroceratoidea , a goniatid superfamily included in the Ammonoidea ; extinct shelled cephalopods with adorally convex septa and usually narrow ventro - marginal siphuncles .
The Japanese wood pigeon ( Columba janthina ) is a species of bird in the Columba genus in the family Columbidae .
Chaiturus is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1787 .
Tristram 's starling or Tristram 's grackle ( Onychognathus tristramii ) is a species of starling native to Israel , Jordan , northeastern Egypt ( Sinai Peninsula ) , western Saudi Arabia , Yemen , and Oman , nesting mainly on rocky cliff faces .
Promanus is a genus of beetle of the family Trogossitidae , endemic to New Zealand .
Banksia nivea , commonly known as Honeypot Dryandra , is a shrub endemic to Western Australia .
Lates mariae , the Bigeye lates , is a species of lates perch native to Lake Tanganyika and from the Lualaba drainage in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Isonandra is a genus of plants in the family Sapotaceae found in tropical Asia , described as a genus in 1840 .
Lirceus is a genus of isopod crustaceans in the family Asellidae that live in southern Canada and the eastern United States as far west as the Great Plains .
Coccidia ( Coccidiasina ) are a subclass of microscopic , spore - forming , single - celled obligate intracellular parasites belonging to the apicomplexan class Conoidasida .
Afroedura is a genus of African geckos .
The Tumbes hummingbird ( Leucippus baeri ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
The term Njangsa refers to an oily seeds tree , Ricinodendron heudelotii , found in tropical West Africa .
The Cactoideae are the largest subfamily of the cactus family , Cactaceae .
Lepidopsocidae are an insect family of bark lice ( Psocoptera ) belonging to the suborder Trogiomorpha .
The genus Sauropus , of the Phyllanthaceae family , comprises about 40 species of herbs , shrubs or subshrubs , sometimes with woody bases .
Colasposoma is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae .
The Lilioideae are a subfamily of monocotyledon perennial , herbaceous mainly bulbous flowering plants in the Liliaceae ( Lily ) family .
Chrysosplenium ( golden saxifrage or golden - saxifrage ) is a genus of 57 species of flowering plants in the family Saxifragaceae .
Mischocephalus lithostrota is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Mischocephalus .
Anambulyx is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Anambulyx elwesi , which is known from northern Pakistan , northern India , Nepal , south - western China , northern Thailand and northern Vietnam .
The Ozark bass ( Ambloplites constellatus ) is a species of freshwater fish in the sunfish family ( Centrarchidae ) of order Perciformes .
The Indochinese black langur ( Trachypithecus ebenus ) is a poorly known lutung native to Laos and adjacent Vietnam .
The Chaco earthcreeper ( Tarphonomus certhioides ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Yates ( 2006 ) found Zupaysaurus to form a group with Dilophosaurus and Dracovenator , placing it in a monophyletic Dilophosauridae .
Brant 's climbing mouse ( Dendromus mesomelas ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Lutz 's poison frog ( Ameerega flavopicta ; formerly Epipedobates flavopicta ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family found in Bolivia and Brazil .
The Atlantic wreckfish , Polyprion americanus , is a marine , bathydemersal , and oceanodromous fish in the family Polyprionidae .
Torula ( Latin name : Candida utilis ; formerly Torulopsis utilis , Torula utilis ) is a species of yeast .
Paramachairodus ( alternately Paramachaerodus ) is an extinct genus of saber - tooth cat of the subfamily Machairodontinae , which was endemic to Europe and Asia during the late Miocene from 15 to 9 Ma .
Photuris is a genus of fireflies ( beetles of the family Lampyridae ) .
European Bat lyssavirus 2 ( EBLV-2 ) is one of three species of Rabies - like virus of the genus Lyssavirus found in Daubenton 's bats ( Myotis daubentonii ) in Britain .
Uapaca is a genus of plant , in the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1858 .
Guineafowl ( /ˈɡɪnifaʊl/ ; sometimes called `` original fowl '' or guineahen ) are birds of the family Numididae in the order Galliformes .
The Hispaniolan emerald ( Chlorostilbon swainsonii ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Budin 's chinchilla rat ( Abrocoma budini ) is a species of chinchilla rat in the family Abrocomidae .
The Arabian fat - tailed scorpion ( Androctonus crassicauda ) is a species of dangerous scorpion usually found in North Africa and the Middle East .
Antisabia , common name hoof shells or hoof snails , is a genus of small sea snails , limpet - like marine gastropod molluscs in the family Hipponicidae .
Lyncornis is a genus of eared nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
The Matinan blue flycatcher ( Cyornis sanfordi ) , also known as the Matinan flycatcher , is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Caenopithecinae is a subfamily within the extinct primate family Adapidae , found in Europe and northern Africa from the Eocene to the Oligocene .
Spelaeodiaptomus rouchi is a species of copepod in the family Diaptomidae .
Chitoria is a genus of butterflies in the family Nymphalidae found in Southeast Asia .
Volvarina is a genus of small to very small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Marginellidae , the margin shells .
Blackfin tuna ( Thunnus atlanticus ) is the smallest tuna species in the Thunnus genus , generally growing to a maximum of 100 cm ( 39 in ) in length and weighing 21 kg ( 46 lbs ) .
The Elachistidae ( grass - miner moths ) are a family of small moths in the superfamily Gelechioidea .
Rafinesque 's big - eared bat ( Corynorhinus rafinesquii ) , sometimes known as the southeastern big - eared bat , is a species of vesper bat native to the southeastern United States .
The Madagascan yellowbrow ( Crossleyia xanthophrys ) , also known as the yellow - browed oxylabes , is a species of Malagasy warbler , formerly placed in the Sylviidae family .
Bromelia is the type genus of the botanical family Bromeliaceae , subfamily Bromelioideae .
Omnidemptus is a monotypic genus of fungi in the family Magnaporthaceae containing the sole species Omnidemptus affinis .
Acruspex spinipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Acruspex .
Langeria is an extinct genus of flowering plant in the family Hamamelidaceae , commonly known as the witch - hazel family , containing the solitary species Langeria magnifica .
Copperband butterflyfish ( Chelmon rostratus ) , commonly known as beaked coral fish , are found in reefs in both the Pacific and Indian Oceans .
The Cauca tree frog , Hyloscirtus caucanus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Geoffroy 's bat ( Myotis emarginatus ) is a species of vesper bat .
Plerandra is a genus of flowering plants in the family Araliaceae that has long been considered a synonym of Schefflera , which has been a polyphyletic group .
The Andaman spiny shrew or Andaman shrew ( Crocidura hispida ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Mesogyne is a genus of plant in family Moraceae ( Mulberry ) .
Cadoceras is an extinct ammonite genus belonging to the Cardioceratidae that lived during the Jurassic period from the late Bajocian to the early Callovian .
The Sunda flying lemur ( Galeopterus variegatus ) , also known as the Malayan flying lemur , Sunda Colugo or Malayan colugo , is a species of colugo .
Carassius auratus grandoculis ( Japanese : nigoro - buna ) , a freshwater ray - finned fish , is a wild subspecies of goldfish endemic to Japan ; its habitat is limited to Lake Biwa , its tributaries and distributaries , and irrigation canals .
The family Droseraceae is part of the order Caryophyllales in the clade core eudicots .
The Pagai spiny rat ( Maxomys pagensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Eurasian least shrew ( Sorex minutissimus ) , also called the lesser pygmy shrew , is the second - smallest mammal after the Etruscan shrew .
Askeptosauridae is a family of thalattosaurs within the superfamily Askeptosauroidea .
Leucicorus is a small genus of cusk - eels found in deep oceanic waters .
The Orinoco goose ( Neochen jubata ) is a member of the duck , goose and swan family Anatidae .
The Syrman goby ( Ponticola syrman ) is a species of goby native to marine , brackish and probably fresh waters of the Black Sea , the Sea of Azov and the Caspian Sea basins .
The Geelvink Bay flying fox or Geelvink Bay fruit bat ( Pteropus pohlei ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
Neaphaenops tellkampfii is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Neaphaenops .
Mareyopsis is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1919 .
Synemosyninae is a subfamily of spiders belonging to the family Salticidae , the order Araneae and the class Arachnida .
Hoplosternum is a small genus of freshwater catfish in the Callichthyinae subfamily of the armored catfish family .
Coccomyxaceae is a family of algae , in the order Chlorococcales .
The Stereaceae are a family of corticioid fungi in the Russulales order .
Spirinchus is a genus of smelts ( Osmeridae ) .
The Cratomorphini are a disputed tribe of fireflies of the large subfamily Lampyrinae .
Gonyostomum is a genus of freshwater algae in the class Raphidophyte .
Ambuchananiaceae is a family of moss in the order Sphagnales with only two genera , Ambuchanania and Eosphagnum
Calotis is a genus of herbs or small shrubs in the daisy family Asteraceae .
Diplasiotherium is an extinct genus of herbivore litoptern belongs to the family Proterotheriidae , that lived between the late Miocene and the early Pliocene ( in the SALMAs Huayquerian and Montehermosan ) .
Tryblidiopsis ( Triblidiopsis is an orthographical variant ) is a genus of fungi within the Rhytismataceae family .
Gonocephalum is a genus of darkling beetle in the family Tenebrionidae .
Chrysopinae is a subfamily of green lacewings in the insect family Chrysopidae in the order Neuroptera .
Xenophrys wuliangshanensis ( Wuliangshan horned toad ) is a species of frog found in Asia .
Ceratostigma ( /ˌsɛrətoʊˈstɪɡmə , sᵻˌræ-/ ; ) , or leadwort , plumbago , is a genus of eight species of flowering plants in the family Plumbaginaceae , native to warm temperate to tropical regions of Africa and Asia .
Copland 's rock frog or the saxicoline tree frog ( Litoria coplandi ) a frog in the family Hylidae .
Threespot barb ( Barbus trimaculatus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
Dusky - faced tanager ( Mitrospingus cassinii ) Olive - backed tanager ( Mitrospingus oleagineus ) The name Mitrospingus is a combination of the Greek words mitra meaning `` cap '' or `` head - dress '' and spingos , meaning `` finch '' .
Machairophora fulvipuncta is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Machairophora .
Chilocorus is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Coccinellidae , subfamily Chilocorinae .
The Madagascan big - headed turtle ( Erymnochelys madagascariensis ) is a turtle native to the waters of permanent slow moving rivers and lakes in western Madagascar .
The Micropygidae form a family of sea urchins within the Diadematoida order or echinoderms .
Pseudosquillopsis is a genus of mantis shrimp in the family Parasquillidae .
Braunsiomyia is a genus of horseflies of the family Tabanidae .
Moserius is a genus of crustacean in family Trichoniscidae , with two described species :
Stempfferia congoana , the Black - veined Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The Ivory Coast rat ( Dephomys eburneae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Poecilium lividum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Poecilium .
The Emesinae , or thread - legged bugs , are a subfamily of the Reduviidae ( i.e. , assassin bugs ) .
Hyperolius ( commonly known as the African reed frogs or reed frogs ) is a large genus of frogs in the Hyperoliidae family from Sub - Saharan Africa .
Thecacera is a genus of sea slugs , specifically nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the family Polyceridae .
The Red pike conger ( Cynoponticus coniceps , also known as the Conehead eel in Mexico ) is an eel in the family Muraenesocidae ( pike congers ) .
The Mississippi gopher frog or dusky gopher frog ( Rana sevosa ) is a rare species of true frog .
The Patagonian tinamou ( Tinamotis ingoufi ) also known as Ingouf 's tinamou is a member of the most ancient group of bird families , the tinamous .
Drupina is a genus of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Compsodes is a genus of hooded , sand cockroaches , of the subfamily Polyphaginae , in the family Polyphagidae .
The Kurdistan spotted newt ( Neurergus microspilotus ) is a species of salamander in the Salamandridae family found in areas of Iran , possibly Iraq , and possibly Turkey .
Arctic cisco ( Coregonus autumnalis ) is an anadromous species of freshwater whitefish that inhabits the Arctic parts of Siberia , Alaska and Canada .
Eatoniopsis is a genus of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Cingulopsidae .
Fischer 's starling ( Spreo fischeri ) is a bird which is an uncommon resident breeder from southern Ethiopia and Somalia to eastern Kenya and Tanzania .
The Leucascidae are a family of sponges in the order Clathrinida .
Jayakar 's seahorse ( Hippocampus jayakari ) is a species of fish in the Syngnathidae family .
Black - chested mountain tanager , Cnemathraupis eximia Golden - backed mountain tanager , Cnemathraupis aureodorsalis
Dibamus is a genus of legless lizards in the family Dibamidae .
The Roanoke logperch ( Percina rex ) is a small freshwater fish found in the Roanoke and Chowan drainages in Virginia , United States .
Anthochortus is a group of plants in the Restionaceae described as a genus in 1837 .
The Deirochelyinae are a subfamily of Emydidae consisting of species native to North , and South America , some of which are frequently kept as pets .
Temnostega antarctica is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Temnostega .
Mullerornis is the smaller of the two genera of extinct elephant birds ( Aepyornithidae ) of Madagascar ( the other is Aepyornis ) .
The Microstigmatidae are a small spider family with fifteen described species in seven genera .
The Reiser 's tyrannulet ( Phyllomyias reiseri ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Benitez 's tree frog , Hypsiboas benitezi , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Brazil , Venezuela , and possibly Guyana .
Pseudomonotes is a monotypic genus of plants in family Dipterocarpaceae .
Atya is a genus of freshwater shrimp of the family Atyidae , ranging through the Antilles and along the Atlantic and Pacific slopes of Central and South America and in western Africa .
Potoxylon is a monotypic genus of evergreen trees belonging to the Laurel family , Lauraceae .
Breviea is a genus of plant in family Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1935 .
The Stenopodainae are a subfamily of Reduviidae ( assassin bugs ) .
The Moheli bulbul ( Hypsipetes moheliensis ) is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
The Baffin Island wolf ( Canis lupus manningi ) , also known as the Baffin Island tundra wolf , is a subspecies of the gray wolf , Canis lupus , which resides exclusively on Baffin Island and several nearby islands .
Enneapterygius williamsi , known commonly as the William 's triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Chrysopogon nigritanus , more widely known by the taxonomic synonym Vetiveria nigritana , or the common name black vetivergrass , is a perennial grass species of the Poaceae family and therefore is also a monocotyledon .
Letestua is a genus of plant in family Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1917 .
The Qinling panda ( Ailuropoda melanoleuca qinlingensis ) is a subspecies of the giant panda , discovered in the 1960s but not recognized as a subspecies until 2005 .
Lithobiidae is a family of centipedes in the order Lithobiomorpha , containing the following genera :
Telekia is a genus of flowering plant , of the family Asteraceae .
Xenobolus is a genus of millipedes in the family Pachybolidae , containing two species found in India and Sri Lanka .
Savi 's pipistrelle ( Hypsugo savii sometimes classified as Pipistrellus savii ) is a species of vesper bat found across North West Africa , the Mediterranean region and the Middle East .
Todd 's sirystes ( Sirystes subcanescens ) , is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Heinroth 's shearwater ( Puffinus heinrothi ) is a poorly known seabird in the family Procellariidae .
Arumecla is a Neotropical genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
The Central Antillean slider ( Trachemys stejnegeri ) , is a species of turtle in the Emydidae family .
Cinara , the conifer aphids or giant conifer aphids , is a genus of aphids in the family Aphididae .
The Bahia spinetail ( Synallaxis whitneyi ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Hydrichthys is a genus of colonial marine hydrozoans that used to be placed in the family Hydrichthyidae but is now included in Pandeidae .
Solanum chilense ( syn . Lycopersicon chilense ) is a plant species from the `` tomato '' subgenus Lycopersicon within the nightshade genus Solanum .
Daribok 's striped caecilian , Ichthyophis daribokensis , is a species of amphibian in Assam in northern India .
Graphania is a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , containing over 100 species .
Deroo 's mouse or Deroo 's praomys ( Praomys derooi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The La Plata skate ( Atlantoraja platana ) is a species of fish in Rajidae family .
Nanolestes is an extinct genus of mammals in the order Amphitheriida .
Macleaya or plume poppies is a genus of two or three species of flowering plants in the poppy family Papaveraceae , native to China and Japan .
The North Island giant moa ( Dinornis novaezealandiae ) is one of two extinct moa in the genus Dinornis .
Dary 's burrowing snake ( Adelphicos daryi ) is a species of snake in the family Colubridae .
Kelletia kelletii , common name Kellet 's whelk , is a species of large sea snail , a whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Pierella is a butterfly genus from the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae found from Mexico through Central America to South America .
Mirza 's western moss rat ( Mirzamys louiseae ) is a species of rodent endemic to Papua New Guinea .
The Australian pied cormorant ( /ˌpaɪd ˈkɔrmərənt/ PYD KOR - mər - ənt ) , Phalacrocorax varius , also known as the pied cormorant or pied shag , is a medium - sized member of the cormorant family .
Anarithma is a small genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Mitromorphidae , in the superfamily Conoidea the cone snails and their allies .
Guamia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the soursop family , Annonaceae .
The Sri Lanka swallow ( Cecropis hyperythra ) is a large swallow .
One characteristic that distinguishes Smilacaceae from most of the other members of the Liliaceae - like Liliales is that it has true vessels in its conducting tissue .
Coptis ( Goldthread or Canker Root ) is a genus of between 10 - -15 species of flowering plants in the family Ranunculaceae , native to Asia and North America .
The Bayou darter ( Etheostoma rubrum ) is a rare species of darter endemic to western Mississippi in the United States , where it is found only in the Bayou Pierre River and its tributaries .
Hackelia ( Stickseeds ) is a genus of plants in the borage family , Boraginaceae .
Cratoxylum ( or Cratoxylon Blume , an orthographic variant ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Hypericaceae , native to tropical Asia .
Codonocarpus is a small genus of shrubs or small trees in the family Gyrostemonaceae .
Macreurops longicollis is a species of beetle in the family Monotomidae , the only species in the genus Macreurops .
Giant petrels form a genus , Macronectes , from the family Procellariidae , which consists of two species .
Obania is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
Orthopoxvirus is a genus of viruses in the family Poxviridae and subfamily Chordopoxvirinae .
The Philippine deer ( Rusa marianna ) , also known as the Philippine sambar or the Philippine brown deer , is a species of deer that is native to the forests and grasslands , on most larger islands of the Philippines , .
Isopyrum is a genus of flowering plants of the family Ranunculaceae native to Eurasia .
Harrington 's gerbil or Harrington 's tateril , Taterillus harringtoni , is a species of gerbil found in Central African Republic , Ethiopia , Kenya , Somalia , South Sudan , Tanzania , and Uganda .
Astronotus is a genus of South American fish from the family Cichlidae .
Sychr 's catfish ( Corydoras sychri ) is a tropical freshwater fish belonging to the Corydoradinae sub - family of the Callichthyidae family .
The Negros forest frog ( Platymantis negrosensis ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
The Luzon fruit bat ( Otopteropus cartilagonodus ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Babault 's mouse shrew ( Myosorex babaulti ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae found in Burundi , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , and Uganda .
Aceratheriinae is an extinct subfamily of rhinoceros endemic to Asia , Africa , Europe , and North America during the Oligocene through Pliocene living from 33.9 - -3.4 mya , existing for approximately 30.5 million years .
The Shipova ( × Sorbopyrus auricularis ) is a hybrid of the European Pear ( Pyrus communis ) and the Common Whitebeam ( Sorbus aria ) .
Tuarangia is an extinct genus of early bivalve , the only genus in the extinct family Tuarangiidae and order Tuarangiida .
Grandidier 's mongoose ( Galidictis grandidieri ) , also known as the giant - striped mongoose or Grandidier 's vontsira , is a small carnivoran that lives only in a very small area of southwestern Madagascar , in areas of spiny forest vegetation .
Spathiostemon is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1826 .
Tetradoxa is a monotypic genus in the family Adoxaceae containing the single species Tetradoxa omeiensis .
Franquet 's epauletted fruit bat ( Epomops franqueti ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae , and is one of three different species of epauletted bats .
The Otjikoto tilapia ( Tilapia guinasana ) is a species of cichlid endemic to Namibia where it was originally only found in Lake Guinas .
Bothrostethus is a genus of Coreidae family , subfamily Pseudophloeinae .
The Zambezi flapshell turtle ( Cycloderma frenatum ) is a species of softshell turtle ( family Trionychidae ) .
The Ceram fruit bat or Seram flying fox ( Pteropus ocularis ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Tateidae is a family of very small and minute aquatic snails with an operculum , gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Truncatelloidea .
In taxonomy , Dimorphococcus is a genus of fresh water green algae , specifically of the Scenedesmaceae .
Heptasaurus is an extinct genus of Triassic capitosaurian temnospondyl amphibian within the family Mastodonsauridae .
The Queen Carola 's parotia ( Parotia carolae ) also known as Queen Carola 's six - wired bird - of - paradise is a species of bird - of - paradise .
Parochetus is traditionally classified in the tribe Trifolieae of the family Leguminosae ( Fabaceae ) , although its inclusion in that tribe has also been considered doubtful .
Banded dwarf cichlid ( Apistogramma bitaeniata ) is a species of benthopelagic freshwater fish from South America .
Desmomyia is a genus of snipe fly of the family Rhagionidae .
The Variegated catshark , Asymbolus submaculatus , is a cat shark of the family Scyliorhinidae , found off New South Wales and Western Australia at depths between 30 and 200 m. Its length is up to 41 cm . The reproduction of this catshark is oviparous .
Fox 's shaggy rat ( Dasymys foxi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Zyziphora is a genus of flies in the tribe Metopinini .
Anchovy sprat , Clupeonella engrauliformis , is a species of fish in the Clupeidae family .
Deania is a genus of long - snouted , deepwater dogfish sharks in the family Centrophoridae .
Swainson 's hawk ( Buteo swainsoni ) , is a large Buteo hawk of the Falconiformes , sometimes separated in the Accipitriformes like its relatives .
Zegalerus is a genus of small to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Calyptraeidae , commonly known as slipper snails , cup - and - saucer shells , and Chinese hat shells .
The Chiguanco thrush ( Turdus chiguanco ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
Duashnoceras is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus included in the Stephanoceratidae that lived during the Bathonian stage of the Middle Jurassic .
The Allegheny Mountain dusky salamander ( Desmognathus ochrophaeus ) is a species in the Plethodontidae ( lungless salamander ) family .
Abedus is a genus of giant water bugs ( family Belostomatidae ) .
Mimetes is a genus of plants in the large family Proteaceae .
Mantis religiosa , with the common name praying mantis , and outside Europe the European mantis , is an insect in the family Mantidae .
Pseudothyrea oppenheimi is a fossil species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Pseudothyrea .
Shouchangoceratinae is one of three ammonoid subfamilies of the family Pseudohaloritidae , which in turn is one of two families in the Goniatitid superfamily Pseudohaloritaceae .
The Sudan gerbil , Gerbillus nancillus is distributed mainly in central Sudan .
Hannia is a monotypic genus of fish in the family Terapontidae containing the single species Hannia greenwayi .
The Halmahera swiftlet ( Aerodramus infuscatus ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
Ectinosomatidae is a family of the Harpacticoida , a huge group of crustaceans belonging to the subclass Copepoda .
Scotomenia cetrata is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Praestrigites is a genus from the Strigoceratidae which is included in the ammonitid superfamily , Haplocerataceae .
Kazakhstan blind mole - rat ( Spalax uralensis , alternatively Ural blind mole - rat ) is an extant species of blind mole - rat indigenous to Kazakhstan , along the Ural River basin and the flood plains of the Uil , Temir , and Emba rivers .
Cauliflower mosaic virus ( CaMV ) is a member of the genus Caulimovirus , one of the six genera in the Caulimoviridae family , which are pararetroviruses that infect plants .
Lithophyllum is a genus of thalloid red algae belonging to the family Corallinaceae .
The Orthopterida is a superorder of the Polyneoptera that represents the extant orders Orthoptera ( grasshoppers , crickets , and katydids ) , and Phasmatodea ( stick insects and leaf insects ) .
Thrausmosaurus is a genus of synapsid pelycosaurs from the extinct family Varanopidae .
The Borneo loach ( Pangio shelfordii ) is an Southeast Asian species of cobitid fish .
Tasmanoplectron is a monotypic genus of cricket in family Rhaphidophoridae described by A. M. Richards .
The Chihuahuan pocket mouse ( Chaetodipus eremicus ) is a species of heteromyid rodent found in the southwestern United States and Mexico .
Potnyctycia ; a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family .
The Pacific baza ( Aviceda subcristata ) also known as the crested hawk , is a slender , medium - sized hawk with a distinctive crest .
