Leucosolenia is a genus of calcareous sponges belonging to the family Leucosoleniidae .
The Arbutoideae are a subfamily in the flowering plant family Ericaceae .
Schistidium is a plant genus in the moss family Grimmiaceae .
The Philippine mouse - deer ( Tragulus nigricans ) , also known as the Balabac chevrotain or pilandok ( in Filipino ) , is a small , nocturnal ruminant , which is endemic to Balabac and nearby smaller islands ( Bugsuc and Ramos ) southwest of Palawan in the Philippines .
The Flores shrew ( Suncus mertensi ) is a white - toothed shrew found only on Flores Island , Indonesia .
The Maendeleo horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus maendeleo ) is a recently discovered species of bats in the family Rhinolophidae .
The Temotu flying fox ( Pteropus nitendiensis ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
Glomeridesmida is the only living order of the superorder Limacomorpha .
Mesophyllum is a genus of red alga belonging to the family Hapalidiaceae .
Amblyornis is a genus of bowerbirds belonging to the family Ptilonorhynchidae .
Pacific spotted scorpionfish ( Scorpaena mystes ) .
The Maupiti monarch ( Pomarea pomarea ) was a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Blechnum ( hard fern ) is a genus of between 150 - -220 species of ferns with a cosmopolitan distribution , in the family Blechnaceae in the eupolypods II clade of the order Polypodiales .
Otitinae is the name of a subfamily of flies in the family Ulidiidae .
Brachymyrmex is a genus in the ants subfamily Formicinae .
Eupolybothrus is a genus of centipedes in the family Lithobiidae .
The Agaricostilbales are an order of fungi in the class Agaricostilbomycetes of the division Basidiomycota .
Calopiidae is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Rissooidea .
Ceuthophilus is a genus of insects in the cave cricket family Rhaphidophoridae .
Igarkiella is the sole genus within the Igarkiellidae , an extinct family of Paleozoic fossil molluscs of uncertain position .
Lepterpeton is an extinct genus of nectridean lepospondyl within the family Urocordylidae .
Worthen 's sparrow ( Spizella wortheni ) is a species of American sparrow that is endemic to northeastern Mexico .
The Mayr 's honeyeater ( Ptiloprora mayri ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
The Lesser Antillean flycatcher ( Myiarchus oberi ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Indian courser ( Cursorius coromandelicus ) is a species of courser found in mainland South Asia , mainly in the plains bounded by the Ganges and Indus river system .
Ceriospora is a genus of fungi in the family Amphisphaeriaceae ; according to the 2007 Outline of Ascomycota , the placement of this family is uncertain .
The Trebouxiophyceae are a class of green algae , in the division Chlorophyta .
The Urich 's tyrannulet ( Phyllomyias urichi ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Clarence galaxias ( Galaxias johnstoni ) is a species of fish in the Galaxiidae family endemic to Tasmania .
Torre 's cave rat ( Boromys torrei ) was a species of rodent in the family Echimyidae .
Raymunida is a genus of squat lobsters in the family Munididae , containing the following 11 species :
Kloneus is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Kloneus babayaga , which is known from Nicaragua but probably ranges from Mexico to Costa Rica .
The Sakhalin sturgeon ( Acipenser mikadoi ) is a species of fish in the Acipenseridae family .
The Javan lutung ( Trachypithecus auratus ) , also known as the ebony lutung and Javan langur , is an Old World monkey from the Colobinae subfamily .
Dromiops nanniscus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Dromiops .
Nebriosoma fallax is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Nebriosoma .
The Sardinian pika ( Prolagus sardus ) was a pika native to the islands of Sardinia , Corsica and neighbouring Mediterranean islands until its extinction in the late 1700s or early 1800s .
Jordan 's casque - headed tree frog , Trachycephalus jordani , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Ecuador , and Peru .
The Sabine 's spinetail ( Rhaphidura sabini ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
The Arabian cobra ( Naja arabica ) is a species of cobra in the genus Naja found in the Arabian Peninsula .
Mariaella is a genus of air - breathing land slugs , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Ariophantidae .
Helanthium is a genus of plants in the Alismataceae , native to the Western Hemisphere .
Sayella is a genus of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
The Tana River cisticola ( Cisticola restrictus ) is a species of bird in the Cisticolidae family .
The Moluccan starling ( Aplonis mysolensis ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
Kihaule 's mouse shrew ( Myosorex kihaulei ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae endemic to Tanzania .

Chalciporus is a genus of fungi in the family Boletaceae ( suborder Boletineae ) .

Syleter papua is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Syleter .
The Tahiti swiftlet or Polynesian swiftlet ( Aerodramus leucophaeus ) is a species of swift in the family Apodidae .
The Santa Barbara shelled slug or slug snail , scientific name Binneya notabilis , is a species of air - breathing land slug , a shell - less terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Binneyidae .
Chymsydia is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , native to the Caucasus .
The Chrysopeleiinae are a subfamily of the Cosmopterigidae , although some authors treat it as a full family , the Chrysopeleiidae .
Devia is a genus of Iridaceae first described in 1990 .
Abrus is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae and the only genus found in the tribe Abreae .
Entovalva nhatrangensis is a species of small marine bivalve mollusc in the family Lasaeidae .
The Nubian bustard ( Neotis nuba ) is a species of bird in the bustard family .
The Curacao myotis ( Myotis nesopolus ) is a species of vesper bat ( family Vespertilionidae ) .
The `` Corvida '' were one of two `` parvorders '' contained within the suborder Passeri , as proposed in the Sibley - Ahlquist taxonomy , the other being Passerida .
Platyhelluo weiri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Platyhelluo .
It was renamed Ponerosteus exogyrarum ( species name amended ) by George Olshevsky in 2000 ; however , the taxon is considered a nomen dubium by most , as the type material is extremely poor , being apparently an internal cast of a tibia from an animal that may or may not be a dinosaur .
Zug 's monitor ( Varanus zugorum ) , also known as the silver monitor , is a species of monitor lizard found on the island of Halmahera in the Moluccas .
Tecticrater is a genus of very small deepwater limpets , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Lepetellidae .

The Wyoming toad or Baxter 's toad ( Anaxyrus baxteri , formerly Bufo baxteri ) is an extremely rare amphibian that exists only in captivity and within Mortenson Lake National Wildlife Refuge in Wyoming in the United States .
Hericium is a genus of edible mushrooms in the Hericiaceae family .
Paramiella is a genus of land snails with gills and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Neocyclotidae .
Oweniidae is a family of marine polychaete worms in the suborder Sabellida .
Bougainville 's skink ( Lerista bougainvillii ) is a species of skink in the Scincidae family .
Otothyrinae is a subfamily of South American catfishes order Siluriformes of the family Loricariidae .
The Minahassa pipistrelle ( Pipistrellus minahassae ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Huanchaca mouse ( Juscelinomys huanchacae ) is a rodent species in the family Cricetidae .
Valvata is a genus of very small freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Valvatidae , the valve snails .
Bromus is part of the cool - season grass lineage ( subfamily Pooideae ) , which includes about 3300 species .
Belgrandiella is a genus of minute freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Horvathinia is a small genus in the family Belostomatidae , and the only genus in its subfamily .
Paradnatoceras is included in the Orthocerida according to Sepkoski ( 2002 ) .
The Slender whiting , Sillago attenuata , is a poorly known species of inshore marine fish of the smelt whiting family , Sillaginidae that has a distribution limited to the Persian Gulf only .
The Zacatecan deer mouse , or southern rock deermouse ( Peromyscus difficilis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Dictyaster is a small genus of starfish in the family Echinasteridae in the order Spinulosida .
Altingiaceae , a small family of flowering plants in the order Saxifragales , are wind - pollinated trees that produce hard , woody fruits containing numerous seeds .
The Ozark minnow ( Notropis nubilus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Cercocarpus , commonly known as mountain mahogany , is a small genus of five or six species of nitrogen - fixing flowering plants in the rose family , Rosaceae .
Kryoryctes is a genus of prehistoric monotreme mammal from the Early Cretaceous ( Albian ) Eumeralla Formation of Victoria , Australia , from the Otway Group of Dinosaur Cove .
The Luzon montane forest mouse ( Apomys datae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae , from the genus Apomys .
Adelaide 's warbler ( Setophaga adelaidae ) is a bird endemic to the archipelago of Puerto Rico belonging to the Setophaga genus of the Parulidae family .
Coenothecalia ( also known as Helioporacea ) is an order of the subclass Octocorallia that forms massive lobed crystalline calcareous skeletons in colonial corals .
The Cabanis 's bunting ( Emberiza cabanisi ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .
The Carbonera pupfish , also Perrito de carbonera , ( Cyprinodon fontinalis ) is a species of fish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
Amphipterygium is a small genus in the subfamily Anacardioideae of the cashew and sumac family Anacardiaceae .
The Solomon 's naked - backed fruit bat ( Dobsonia inermis ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Randall 's frogfish or Antennarius randalli , is a marine fish belonging to the family Antennariidae .
The Chinese high fin banded shark ( Myxocyprinus asiaticus ) is a popular freshwater aquarium fish that belongs to the Catostomidae family .
Shinkaia crosnieri is a species of squat lobster in a monotypic genus in the family Munidopsidae .

The San Bruno elfin butterfly ( Callophrys mossii bayensis or Incisalia mossii bayensis ) is a U.S. Federally listed endangered subspecies that inhabits rocky outcrops and cliffs in coastal scrub on the San Francisco Peninsula , endemic to this habitat in California .
Cephalomappa is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1874 .
Carinaria is a genus of medium - sized floating sea snails , pelagic gastropod molluscs in the family Carinariidae .
Mesonauta is part of the family Cichlidae and is included in subfamily Cichlasomatinae .
Pseudophlocteis vidua is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Pseudophlocteis .
The Chiloé wigeon ( Anas sibilatrix ) , also known as the southern wigeon , is one of three extant species of wigeon in the genus Anas of the dabbling duck subfamily .
Amana edulis ( formerly Tulipa edulis ) is a flowering bulb that is native to China , Japan , and Korea .
The Inagua slider ( Trachemys stejnegeri malonei ) is a subspecies of the Central Antillean slider .
Molopinus pilipes is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Molopinus .
Perissodonta is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Struthiolariidae , the ostrich - foot snails .
The extinct penguin genus Pseudaptenodytes contains the type species P. macraei ; smaller bones have been assigned to P. minor , although it is not certain whether they are really from a different species or simply of younger individuals ; both taxa are known by an insufficient selection of bones .
The Dasycerinae are a subfamily of the Staphylinidae ( Coleoptera ) rove beetles .
Longimornis robustirostrata is an extinct genus and species of bird in the old world oriole family .
Teleoceras is an extinct genus of grazing rhinoceros .
Caviinae is a subfamily uniting all living members of the family Caviidae with the exception of the maras , capybaras , and Kerodon .
Pterogmus rufipes is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Pterogmus .
Pentaschistis is a genus of grass in the Poaceae family .
The Comoros thrush ( Turdus bewsheri ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
The Ear - spot squirrel ( Callosciurus adamsi ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Trichoglottis , abbreviated Trgl in horticultural trade , is a genus of plant in family Orchidaceae .
The Namaqua dwarf chameleon or the Western dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion occidentale ) occurs in beach vegetation , along the west coast of South Africa and Namibia .
The Moluccan dwarf kingfisher ( Ceyx lepidus ) , is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae that is endemic to the Maluku Islands .
The Ceropalinae are a subfamily of the Pompilidae , the spider wasps , containing two genera , whose members are kleptoparasitic on other solitary wasps which hunt spiders , mainly fellow members of the Pompilidae .
The Choanoceratidae is a small , mono - generic , family of extinct nautiloid cephalopods in the order Orthocerida that lived in what would be Europe during the middle Silurian from 428.2 - -426.2 mya , existing for approximately 2 million years .
Brodiaeoideae are a monocot subfamily of flowering plants in the family Asparagaceae , order Asparagales .
Liniaxis is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the subfamily Coralliophilinae , the coral snails , within the family Muricidae , the murex snails and rock snails .
The Tacarcuna bat ( Lasiurus castaneus ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Talaud rail ( Gymnocrex talaudensis ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
The Micropezidae are a moderate - sized family of acalyptrate muscoid flies in the insect order Diptera , comprising about 500 species in about 50 genera and five subfamilies worldwide , ( except New Zealand and Macquarie Island ) .
Notiokasis chaudoiri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Notiokasis .
Antarctic krill ( Euphausia superba ) is a species of krill found in the Antarctic waters of the Southern Ocean .
Rabidosaurus is an extinct genus of large herbivorous dicynodont of the family Kannemeyeriidae from Russia .
Protortalotrypeta is a monotypic genus of tephritid or fruit flies in the family Tephritidae .

Josef Streb ( born 16 April 1912 , date of death unknown ) was a German footballer who participated at the 1934 FIFA World Cup .

Yekaterina Lisina ( born October 15 , 1987 ) , is a Russian basketball player who competed for the Russian National Team at the 2008 Summer Olympics , winning the bronze medal .

M. Oskar Quarg ( born September 15 , 1887 , date of death unknown ) was a German athlete , who competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics in London .
Eva Hagenbäumer ( born January 5 , 1967 in Wiesbaden , Hessen ) is a former field hockey player from Germany , who was a member of the national squad that won the silver medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .

František Maxa ( born 13 February 1923 ) is a Czech former sport shooter who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics and in the 1956 Summer Olympics .
Nandor Sabo Paloc ( February 19 , 1960 ) is a former wrestler who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics for Yugoslavia and in the 1992 Summer Olympics as an Independent Olympic participant .
André Mourlon ( 9 October 1903 -- 31 July 1970 ) was a French sprinter who competed at the 1924 and 1928 Summer Olympics in the 100 m , 200 m and 4×100 metre relay .

Carroll Morgan ( born October 3 , 1947 in Antigonish , Nova Scotia ) is a former heavyweight boxer from Canada , who represented his native country at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich , West Germany .

Kim Probst ( born 6 March 1981 ) is an American synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .

Harald Heinke ( born 15 May 1955 in Eilenburg ) is a German former judoka who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Michaela Michalopoulou ( born 20 April 1980 ) is a Greek handball player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics .

Hans Harting ( 2 February 1926 -- 8 July 2004 ) was a Dutch middle - distance runner who competed in the 1500 m event at the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Julius Körner ( born April 2 , 1870 -- died ? ) was a German rower who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics .
M.J. Hans Taihuttu ( born 1909 , date of death unknown ) was an Indonesian football forward who played for the Dutch East Indies in the 1938 FIFA World Cup .
Shingo Kawabata ( born 15 May 1978 ) is a Japanese former sprinter who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Karen Nystrom ( born June 17 , 1969 ) was a member of the 1998 Canadian National women 's team that participated in ice hockey at the 1998 Winter Olympics .
Márta Megyeri ( née Pacsai , born August 29 , 1952 in Dorog ) is a former Hungarian handball player who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics , where she won the bronze medal with the Hungarian team .
Gunnel Johansson ( 12 August 1922 -- 7 May 2013 ) was a Swedish artistic gymnast who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Giovanni Kasebacher ( born December 13 , 1910 -- date of death unknown ) was an Italian cross - country skier who competed in the 1936 Winter Olympics .
Gary di Silvestri ( born February 3 , 1967 in Staten Island , United States ) is a cross - country skier who competed for Dominica at the 2014 Winter Olympics in the 15 kilometre classical race .
Brixx was a Danish pop group which represented Denmark in the Eurovision Song Contest 1982 , with the song `` Video , Video '' .
Rob Denton ( November 20 , 1907 -- August 12 , 1997 ) was an American soccer goalkeeper who was a member of the United States soccer team at the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Eilert Bøhm ( born July 17 , 1900 - February 1 , 1982 ) was a Norwegian gymnast who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Dolly Shefali ( Bengali : ডলি শেফালী ) is a Bangladeshi national women Kabaddi player who was part of the team that won the bronze medal at the 2010 Asian Games .
Dino Kessler ( born December 23 , 1966 ) is a former Swiss professional ice hockey defenceman who last played for EHC Basel in Switzerland 's National League B. Kessler has participated as a member of the Swiss national team in numerous international tournaments , including the 1992 Winter Olympics .
Kaeo Pongprayoon ( Thai : แก้ว พงษ์ประยูร ; rtgs : Kaeo Phongprayun ; pronounced ( kɛ̂ːw pʰōŋ.prà.jūːn ) ; born 28 March 1980 in Kamphaeng Phet ) is a Thai amateur boxer who won a silver medal at the 2012 Summer Olympics , and a sergeant in the Royal Thai Army .
Achim Hill ( April 1 , 1935 -- August 4 , 2015 ) was a German rower who competed for the Unified Team of Germany in the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics and for East Germany in the 1968 Summer Olympics .
Helma Lehmann ( born June 23 , 1953 ) is a German rower who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics representing East Germany .
Ken Doubleday ( born 14 February 1926 - 8 June 2014 ) is an Australian former hurdler and triple jumper who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics and in the 1956 Summer Olympics .
Johan Hübner von Holst ( 22 August 1881 -- 13 June 1945 ) was a Swedish sport shooter who competed at the 1906 , 1908 and 1912 Summer Olympics .
Despoina Solomou ( born 18 August 1990 ) is a Greek synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2008 and 2012 Summer Olympics .
Otar Tushishvili ( born 14 June 1978 in Gori ) is a Georgian wrestler , who has won a bronze medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Thoralf Sandaker ( born 4 May 1923 ) is a Norwegian former rower who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Patrick Kühl ( born March 26 , 1968 in Güstrow , Mecklenburg - Vorpommern ) is a former medley swimmer from East Germany , who won the silver medal in the 200 m individual medley for the GDR at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .
Andrea Šušnjara ( born 26 February 1987 ) is a Croatian singer who was the Croatian entrant for the Eurovision Song Contest 2009 .
Eugen Rupf was a Swiss footballer who played for Switzerland in the 1938 FIFA World Cup .
Vadim Kaptur ( born 12 July 1987 ) is a Belarusian diver who competed at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Anna Bacchiega ( born 18 July 1957 ) is an Italian yacht racer who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Julia Müller ( born 10 December 1985 ) is a German field hockey national team player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics and the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Igor Grivennikov ( born 11 July 1952 ) is a Russian former swimmer who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics and won a silver in the 4×100 m freestyle relay .
Ahmed Elmaghraby ( born April 26 , 1968 in Suez , Egypt ) is a former field hockey forward who finished twelfth with the United States men 's national team at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , Georgia .
Sheree Horvath ( born 7 April 1980 ) is a New Zealand field hockey player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
František Šulc ( born June 8 , 1950 ) is a Czech former handball player who competed for Czechoslovakia in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Aleksandr Sychyov ( Russian : Алекса́ндр Сычёв ; born October 10 , 1959 ) is a retired field hockey player from Russia , who won the bronze medal with the Men 's National Field Hockey Team from the Soviet Union at the boycotted 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow .
Maria Liku ( born in Levuka on 27 April 1990 ) is a Fijian weightlifter who represented Fiji at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Helga Németh ( born August 7 , 1973 in Nagykanizsa ) is a Hungarian handball player who has won the bronze medal with the Hungarian team on the 1996 Summer Olympics .
Juan Carlos Masnik ( born 2 March 1943 ) is a former Uruguayan football player and manager , who represented his country at the 1974 FIFA World Cup in Germany .
Guillermo Geary ( born July 18 , 1926 ) represented Argentina at the 1948 Summer Olympics in London , he was entered in the 200 m , he finished third in his heat and failed to advance .

Philippe Hardy ( 5 July 1954 -- 1984 ) was a French alpine skier who competed in the 1976 Winter Olympics .

Ralph Mecredy ( 12 July 1888 -- 1968 ) was an Irish cyclist who competed for Great Britain in two events at the 1912 Summer Olympics in Stockholm , Sweden .
Emil Oberle ( November 16 , 1889 in Karlsruhe -- December 25 , 1955 in Karlsruhe ) was a German amateur football ( soccer ) player who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Karin Rutz - Gießelmann ( born 16 January 1948 ) is a German fencer who competed at the 1972 and 1976 Summer Olympics in foil events ; her teams finished in fifth and fourth place , respectively .
Kwon Hyuk ( Hangul : 권혁 ; hanja : 權赫 ; born November 6 , 1983 in Daegu , South Korea ) is a baseball player from South Korea who won a gold medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics .

Iacob Felecan ( 1 January 1914 -- 1964 ) was a Romanian football who played for Romania in the 1938 FIFA World Cup .
Saroj Maharjan ( Nepali : सरोज महर्जन , born 23 February 1990 ) is an extra lightweight Nepalese judoka who won Gold at the Ninth South Asian Judo Championship and represented Nepal in the 2009 Asian Martial Arts Games ( details ) , 2011 World Judo Championships ( details ) and 2014 Asian Games ( details ) .
Fiona Iredale ( born 1 December 1967 ) is a former Olympic athlete from Dundee , Scotland who represented New Zealand in Women 's Heavyweight Judo at the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Yukari Kawase ( Japanese : 川瀬 ゆかり ; born March 2 , 1967 ) is a Japanese former volleyball player who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics .

Paul Staub was a Swiss rower who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics and was the part of the Swiss Team which won a Gold Medal in 1920 Antwerp in coxed fours .
Fabrice Colas ( born 21 July 1964 ) is a retired French track cyclist who competed at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles , winning a bronze medal in the 1000 metres time trial .
Tyler Bjorn ( born 13 March 1970 ) is a Canadian former yacht racer who competed in the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Spiro Debarski ( Bulgarian : Спиро Дебърски ; born 8 December 1933 in Blagoevgrad ) is a former Bulgarian footballer who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics .

Jerzy Hewelt ( born 23 August 1948 in Trzebież Szczeciński ) is a Polish former hurdler who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Per August Gustafsson ( 4 November 1875 -- 31 October 1938 ) was a Swedish policeman who won a gold medal in the tug of war competition at the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Margaret Hoffman ( June 19 , 1911 -- March 25 , 1991 ) was an American competition swimmer who represented the United States at the 1928 Summer Olympics and 1932 Summer Olympics .
Georges Speicher ( pronounced : ( ʒɔʁʒ spɛ.ʃe ) ; 8 June 1907 -- 24 January 1978 ) was a French cyclist who won the 1933 Tour de France along with three stage wins , and the 1933 World Cycling Championship .

Gerrit Solleveld ( De Lier , 8 June 1961 ) is a former Dutch professional road bicycle racer , who won two stages in the Tour de France .

Hans Sedlmayr ( 18 January 1896 , in Szarvkő , Kingdom of Hungary -- 9 July 1984 , in Salzburg ) was an Austrian art historian .

Blas de Lezo y Olavarrieta ( 3 February 1689 -- 7 September 1741 ) was a Spanish admiral best remembered for the Battle of Cartagena de Indias ( 1741 ) in modern - day Colombia , where the Spaniards resisted a siege by a combined British force under the command of Admiral Vernon .
Sophie Elkan , née Salomon ( 3 January 1853 , Gothenburg --5 April 1921 , Stockholm ) , was a Swedish - Jewish writer and translator .

Thomas Harrison Montgomery ( February 27 , 1830 - April 4 , 1905 ) was an American businessman and writer from Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .

William Fielding Ogburn ( June 29 , 1886 -- April 27 , 1959 ) was an American sociologist who was born in Butler , Georgia and died in Tallahassee , Florida .
Walter M. Lowrey ( July 19 , 1921 -- May 29 , 1980 ) was a historian affiliated with Centenary College , a Methodist - institution in Shreveport , Louisiana , who was also a founding member of the Louisiana Historical Association .
Max Miedinger ( 24 December 1910 in Zurich , Switzerland -- 8 March 1980 , Zürich , Switzerland ) was a Swiss typeface designer .
Auguste André Thomas Cahours ( 2 October 1813 , Paris -- 17 March 1891 , Paris ) was a French chemist .
Fabrizio Dentice ( also Fabricio , Fabritio ) ( Naples ca . 1539 -- Naples ca . 1581 ) was an Italian composer and virtuoso lute and viol player .
Çetin Özek ( 1934 Çorum , Turkey -- 16 July 2008 Istanbul ) was a prominent Turkish university professor of criminal law , jurist , author and journalist .
During a tremendous thunderstorm in New York City , Bob Hope observes that `` Basil Rathbone must be throwing a party '' .
Doctor Diego Núñez de Avendaño ( d. 1607 , presumably in Lima , Peru ) was oidor ( judge ) of the Royal Audiencia of Lima , and for a brief period in 1607 , interim viceroy of Peru .
Giulio Rosati ( Rome 1857 -- Rome 1917 ) was an Italian painter specialized in orientalist and academic scenes .
Cardinal Frederick Jagiellon ( Polish : Fryderyk Jagiellończyk ; 27 April 1468 , in Kraków -- 14 March 1503 ) was a Polish prince , Archbishop of Gniezno , Bishop of Kraków , and Primate of Poland .
Tobeen ( Bordeaux , July 20 , 1880 - Saint - Valery - sur - Somme , March 1938 ) is the pseudonym of the French artist Félix Elie Bonnet .

Murray Handwerker died of complications from dementia on May 14 , 2011 , at his home in Palm Beach Gardens , Florida , at age 89 .
Carlos Bee was born in 1869 in Saltillo , Mexico , where his parents Hamilton Prioleau Bee and Mildred Tarver Bee had moved from San Antonio after the collapse of the Confederacy and the end of the American Civil War .
Alice Rollit Coe ( 1858 - -1940 ) was a Canadian emigrant to the United States , Seattle housewife and author .
Francesco Novati ( Cremona , 1859 - Sanremo , 1915 ) was an Italian historian and philologist .
Pierre Lantier died on 4 April 1998 in Ollioules , in southeastern France .

Mosè Bianchi ( Monza , 1840 - -1904 ) was an Italian painter and printmaker .
Nevit Kodallı ( born 12 December 1924 in Mersin ; died 1 September 2009 in Mersin ) is a Turkish composer of western - influenced classical music including operas and ballets .
Professor Ludwig Marcuse ( February 8 , 1894 in Berlin -- August 2 , 1971 in Bad Wiessee ) , was a philosopher and writer of Jewish origin .
Adam Benjamin Jr. ( August 6 , 1935 -- September 7 , 1982 ) was an American politician and a United States Representative from Indiana 's 1st congressional district , serving from 1977 until his death from a heart attack in Washington , D.C. in 1982 .
Katti Lanner ( 14 September 1829 -- 15 November 1908 ) was a Viennese ballet dancer , choreographer , and ballet mistress who found fame in Germany and England , where she staged many productions at the Empire Theatre in London .
Jules Marie Auguste Leroux was born in the 3rd arrondissement of Paris on 14 April 1871 , during the Commune .
Harvey Manning ( July 16 , 1925 in Ballard , Seattle , Washington - November 12 , 2006 in Bellevue , Washington ) was a noted author of hiking guides and climbing textbooks , and a tireless hiking advocate .
Eva Taylor died from cancer in 1977 in Mineola , New York .
Armand Borel ( 21 May 1923 --11 August 2003 ) was a Swiss mathematician , born in La Chaux - de - Fonds , and was a permanent professor at the Institute for Advanced Study in Princeton , New Jersey , United States from 1957 to 1993 .
Gohar Gasparyan ( Armenian : Գոհար Գասպարյան ; December 14 , 1924 , Cairo , Egypt -- May 16 , 2007 , Yerevan , Armenia ) also known as the `` Armenian nightingale '' , was an Armenian opera singer .
True Eames Boardman ( October 25 , 1909 , Seattle , Washington -- July 28 , 2003 , Pebble Beach , California ) was an actor and scriptwriter .
Francis Edward Lauricella , known as Hank Lauricella ( October 9 , 1930 -- March 25 , 2014 ) , was a real estate developer from suburban New Orleans , Louisiana , a college football legend , and a member of both houses of the Louisiana State Legislature .
Eduardo Jimeno Correas ( 22 February 1869 in Zaragoza -- 30 October 1947 in Madrid ) was a Spanish filmmaker and producer .
Robert Pete Williams ( March 14 , 1914 -- December 31 , 1980 ) was an American Louisiana blues musician .

Johann Carl Loth ( 1632 -- 6 October 1698 ) was a German Baroque painter , born in Munich but active most of his life in Venice .
Charles - Joseph de Harlez de Deulin ( Liège , 21 August 1832 -- Leuven , 14 July 1899 ) was a Belgian Orientalist , domestic prelate , canon of the cathedral of Liège , and member of the Academie Royale of Belgium , who studied and translated the Zoroastrian holy texts .
Christian Ehregott Weinlig ( September 30 , 1743 -- March 14 , 1813 ) was a German composer and cantor of Dresden 's Kreuzkirche .
Liviu Deleanu ( born Lipe Kligman ; February 21 , 1911 , Iași - May 12 , 1967 , Chișinău ) was a Moldovan and Romanian poet and playwright , a doyen of postwar Moldovan literature .

Anton Dostler ( Munich , May 10 , 1891 -- Aversa , December 1 , 1945 ) was a general of the infantry in the regular German Army during World War II . In the first Allied war trial after the war , Dostler was found guilty of war crimes and executed by a firing squad .

Winifred Wagner ( born Winifred Marjorie Williams ; 23 June 1897 -- 5 March 1980 ) was the English - born wife of Siegfried Wagner , the son of Richard Wagner , and ran the Bayreuth Festival after her husband 's death in 1930 until the end of World War II in 1945 .
Ida Saxton McKinley ( June 8 , 1847 -- May 26 , 1907 ) , wife of William McKinley , was First Lady of the United States from 1897 to 1901 .
Stelios Kazantzidis married Marinella on 7 May 1964 and they toured together in Germany and the United States .
Mary Smith Jones ( 1819 - -1907 ) was the last First Lady of the Republic of Texas , as wife of Anson Jones , the last president of the Republic .
Countess Ilona Andrássy de Csíkszentkirály et Krasznahorka ( May 21 , 1858 -- April 2 , 1952 ) was a Hungarian noblewoman , wife of Count Lajos Batthyány de Németújvár ( 1860 - -1951 ) who served as Governor of Fiume .
Cratesipolis ( Greek : Kρατησίπoλις meaning `` conqueror of the city '' ; lived 4th century BC ) , wife of Alexander , the son of Polyperchon , was highly distinguished for her beauty , talents , and energy .
Anny Ondra ( 15 May 1903 -- 28 February 1987 ) was a Czech film actress whose husband was German boxing great Max Schmeling .
Meeru Dhalwala is an author , chef and co - owner , with her husband Vikram Vij , of the Indian restaurants Vij 's and Rangoli in Vancouver , British Columbia .
Janni Spies ( née Brodersen , born 19 September 1962 ) is a Danish businesswoman , multimillionaire , and former owner of the Scandinavian travelling empire Spies Rejser including the charter airline Conair of Scandinavia , companies she inherited from her first husband Simon Spies .
In the early 1980s , Paulene Stone married Peter Morton , co - founder of the Hard Rock Cafe restaurant chain , and moved to Los Angeles .
Fredegund ( or Fredegunda ) ( Latin : Fredegundis ; French : Frédégonde ) ( died 597 ) was the Queen consort of Chilperic I , the Merovingian Frankish king of Soissons .
Shana'Kin Yaxchel Pacal ( `` Green Jay on the Wall '' ) was a Mayan Queen of Copan and the wife of Yik'in Chan K'awiil .
Maud de Prendergast , Lady of Offaly ( 17 March 1242 -- before 1273 ) , was a Norman - Irish noblewoman , the first wife of Maurice FitzGerald , 3rd Lord of Offaly , Justiciar of Ireland , and the mother of his two daughters , Juliana FitzGerald and Amabel .
Benjamin Raich is married to skier Marlies Schild .
Barth Jules Sussman is a novelist , screenwriter , and children 's book author married to illustrator Jen Sussman .

Princess Pei ( 裴王后 , personal name unknown ) ( died 354 ) was the wife of the Chinese state Former Liang 's ruler Zhang Chonghua .

Sally Katzen is married to U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit judge Timothy B. Dyk , and they have one child , Abraham Benjamin Dyk .

Gyalopion is a genus of small nonvenomous colubrid snakes , which are commonly referred to as hooknose snakes , that are native to the southwestern United States and Mexico .
The Coelopidae or kelp flies are a family of Acalyptratae flies ( order Diptera ) , they are sometimes also called seaweed flies , though both terms are used for a number of seashore Diptera .
Lophiocharon is a genus of frogfishes native to the Indian Ocean and western Pacific Ocean .

Sarcobatus , is a North American genus of two species of flowering plants , formerly considered to be a single species .

Tuberculobasis geijskesi is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae first identified in Suriname .
Uroteuthis is a genus of 14 species of common inshore squids of the Indo - West Pacific and is further subdivided into 3 subgenera .
Calathus albanicus is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Albania , Kosovo , Montenegro , Republic of Macedonia , Serbia , and Voivodina .
Hickory ( from Powhatan ) is a type of tree , comprising the genus Carya ( Ancient Greek : κάρυον `` nut '' ) .
Bathanalia howesi is a species of tropical freshwater snail with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Paludomidae .
Macrothyatira is a genus of insects belonging to the subfamily Thyatirinae .

Henricia leviuscula , commonly called the Pacific blood star , it is a species of starfish found along the Pacific coast of North America .
Spineuteleuta celebensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spineuteleuta .
Erigeron reductus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name lesser California rayless fleabane .
Lucinoida is a taxonomic order of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs .
Javichthys kailolae is a species of pufferfish known only from the Bali Strait off Java in Indonesia .
Urotrygon is a genus of American round stingrays .

Girella nigricans , commonly known as the opaleye or rudderfish , is a species of sea chub found in the Eastern Pacific , from California to southern Baja California .

The Cocculinoidea is a superfamily of deepwater limpets ( marine gastropods ) , the only superfamily in the clade Cocculiniformia , one of the main clades of gastropods according to the taxonomy as set up by ( Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Sympterygia is a genus of fish in the family Rajidae .
Perittopus zhengi is a species of Riffle bug from Thailand .
Oxyurichthys microlepis , the maned goby , is a species of goby native to tropical marine and brackish waters along the coasts of the Indian Ocean from Africa to the western Pacific Ocean where it occurs in estuaries and inshore waters to depths of about 75 metres ( 246 ft ) .

The Ethiopian hare ( Lepus fagani ) is a species of mammal in the family Leporidae .
The genus Carthamus , the distaff thistles , includes plants in the thistle family .
Heliconius charithonia , the zebra longwing or zebra heliconian , is a species of butterfly belonging to the subfamily Heliconiinae of the Nymphalidae .
Pelophila borealis is a species of ground beetle in Nebriinae subfamily which was described by Gustaf von Paykull in 1790 .
Biceropsis maculata is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Veragua cross - banded tree frog , Smilisca sordida , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Costa Rica , Honduras , Nicaragua , and Panama .
Mimohoplorana puncticollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimohoplorana .
Poa howellii is a species of grass known by the common name Howell 's bluegrass .
Pelargonium drummondii is a species of Pelargonium found around the southern coasts of Western Australia .
The Transcaucasian sprilin ( Alburnoides fasciatus ) is a fish species in the Cyprinidae family .
Strychnos millepunctata is a species of shrub or small tree in the Loganiaceae family .
Actinokineospora is a genus in the phylum Actinobacteria ( Bacteria ) .
Stylidium asymmetricum , the asymmetric triggerplant , is a flowering plant species of the genus Stylidium and is endemic to south - west Western Australia .
Menarana is an extinct genus of madtsoiid snake which existed in Madagascar during the Late Cretaceous .
Pione vastifica , commonly known as red boring sponge , is a species of sponge found from the Red Sea to Western Pacific .
Crossosoma californicum , known by the common name California rockflower , is one of only a few species in the flowering plant family Crossosomataceae .
Barbatodon is a mammal genus from the Upper Cretaceous period .
Orphium is a plant genus in the Gentian family ( Gentianaceae ) , endemic to South Africa .
Penicillium daleae is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil under conifers in Poland .
Paramphistomatidae is a family of flukes which are parasitic on herbivorous mammals , and sometimes humans .
Boraras brigittae is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Boraras .
The Tamaricales are an obsolete order of dicotyledons .
Viola stipularis , is a species of violet that grows in southern Central America , some Caribbean islands and northern South America ; from Costa Rica and Guadeloupe south to Peru .
Pyrgospira ostrearum , common name the oyster turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pseudomelatomidae .
Pseudagrilodes leonensis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Pseudagrilodes .
Picconia excelsa is a species of Picconia , endemic to Macaronesia , occurring on the Canary Islands ( Spain ) and Madeira ( Portugal ) .
Giant cockroaches , or blaberids ( family Blaberidae ) are the second - largest cockroach family .
Leucosioidea is a superfamily of crabs containing the two families Leucosiidae and Iphiculidae .
Corumbataia veadeiros is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is found in tributaries of the Rio das Almas and the Ribeirão dos Bois , both of which are tributaries of the Rio Paranã , in the headwaters of the Rio Tocantins basin , Goiás , central Brazil .
Persicaria wallichii is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common names Himalayan knotweed and cultivated knotweed .
Huilatherium is an extinct genus of leontiniid , a group of hoofed mammals belonging to the order Notoungulata , that comprising other South American ungulates families that evolved in parallel with some mammals of the Northern hemisphere .
Selenidioides are a genus of parasitic protozoa in the phylum Apicomplexa .
Coccoderma is a genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Late Jurassic period , Kimmeridgian Stage .
Aesculus parviflora ( bottlebrush buckeye ) is a species of buckeye .
Guichenotia ledifolia is a small shrub species in the family Malvaceae .
Rissoa violacea , common name the violet risso , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Rissoidae .
Gideonmantellia is an extinct genus of basal ornithopod dinosaur known from the Early Cretaceous ( Barremian stage ) of Galve , Province of Teruel , Spain .
Heuchera pulchella , the Sandia Mountain alumroot or Sandia Mountain coral - bells , is a plant species endemic to central New Mexico , mostly in the Manzano and Sandia Mountains , but cultivated as an ornamental elsewhere .
Microchilus is a neotropical genus of about 75 species belonging to the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) .
Migmacastor is an extinct member of the beaver family , Castoridae , known from a single species , Migmacastor procumbodens .
Coprosma perpusilla , commonly known as Creeping Coprosma , is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae , or coffee family .
Arcinella arcinella , or the Caribbean spiny jewel box clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Chamidae .
Symphoricarpos sinensis is an uncommon Chinese species of shrubs in the honeysuckle family .
Rubus adenocaulisis a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
The genus Aulacosphinctoides has been found in Somalia , northern India , Japan , Argentina , Mexico , New Zealand , and Madagascar .
The Indus river dolphin ( Platanista gangetica minor ) is a subspecies of freshwater river dolphin found in the Indus river ( and its Beas and Sutlej tributaries ) of India and Pakistan .
Chilatherina is a genus of rainbowfishes that is endemic to freshwater in New Guinea .
Anthothoe albocincta , common name white - striped anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Sagartiidae .
It is monotypic and the only species is Astroides calycularis , which is endemic to the western Mediterranean Sea .
Echinometra lucunter , the rock boring urchin , is a species of sea urchin in the family Echinometridae .
Hamadasuchus is an extinct genus of sebecian crocodylomorph .
The Forbes 's forest rail or Forbes 's forest crake ( Rallina forbesi ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
Camelops is an extinct genus of camel that once roamed western North America , where it disappeared at the end of the Pleistocene about 10,000 years ago .
It contains the single species Agyrtiola niepelti , which is found in Brazil .
Mammillaria elongata ( gold lace cactus , ladyfinger cactus ) is a species of flowering plant in the Cactaceae family , native to central Mexico .
Cyathocrinites is an extinct genus of crinoid that lived from the Early Silurian to the Late Permian in Europe and North America .
Schizosaccharomycetes is a class in the kingdom of fungi .
Psammoperca waigiensis , the Waigeo barramundi , is a species of marine fish in family Latidae of order Perciformes .
Squillidae is a family of mantis shrimp , the only family in the superfamily Squilloidea .
Bergenia stracheyi is a plant species in the genus Bergenia found in the Western Himalayas , from 2700 - 4700 m , Afghanistan and Tajikistan .
Rapetosaurus is a genus of sauropod dinosaur that lived in Madagascar from 70 to 66 million years ago , at the end of the Cretaceous Period .
Campanulales is a valid botanic name for a plant order .
Saproscincus is a genus of skinks native to Australia , sometimes referred to as shade skinks .
Myxaster is a genus of deep - sea velatid sea stars containing three species .
Leptotyphlops rubrolineatus , or the Red - lined blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Monodilepas skinneri is a species of small sea snail , a keyhole limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Phacelia distans is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , known by the common names distant phacelia and distant scorpionweed .
Pseudocentruropsis flavosignata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudocentruropsis .
The Napo sabrewing ( Campylopterus villaviscensio ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Colquhounia elegans ( 秀丽火把花 , xiu li huo ba hua ) is a shrub species in the genus Colquhounia found in Asia ( Yunnan , Cambodia , Laos , Myanmar , Thailand , Vietnam ) .
The Tetratomidae are a small family of beetles with no vernacular common name , though recent authors have coined the name polypore fungus beetles .
Atherina lopeziana is a species of marine fish of the Atherinidae family .
Melanthiaceae is a family of flowering perennial herbs native to the Northern Hemisphere .
It is monotypic , the only species being Crassadoma gigantea , the rock scallop , giant rock scallop or purple - hinge rock scallop .
Paraponera dieteri is an extinct species of Miocene ant in the genus Paraponera .
Urocystis is a genus of smut fungi containing plant pathogens , which infect grass species and other plants .

Olearia suffruticosa , commonly known as Clustered Daisy - bush , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae .
Leptolalax oshanensis ( Oshan metacarpal - tubercled toad or pigmy crawl frog ) is a frog species in the family Megophryidae .
Saxicola ( Latin : saxum , rock + incola , dwelling in ) , the stonechats or chats , is a genus of 15 species of small passerine birds restricted to the Old World .
Trichoanoreina albomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichoanoreina .
Bursa rhodostoma , common name the wine - mouth frog shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bursidae , the frog shells .
Barleeiidae ( often also spelled Barleeidae ) is a family of minute sea snails , micromollusks in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Acherontisuchus is an extinct genus of dyrosaurid neosuchian from Middle to Late Paleocene deposits of Colombia .
The Lycidae are a family in the beetle order Coleoptera , members of which are commonly called net - winged beetles .
Cryptomastix devia , common name the Puget Oregonian snail , ( Escargot du Puget ) is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
Arctostaphylos gabrielensis , known by the common name San Gabriel manzanita , is a species of manzanita .
Hyperstrotia secta , the Black - patched Graylet Moth , is a species of moth of the Erebidae family .
The Reichenow 's seedeater ( Crithagra reichenowi ) , is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Boechera laevigata is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name smooth rockcress .
Macroplata ( meaning `` big plate '' ) is an extinct genus of Early Jurassic basal plesiosaur which grew up to 4.5 metres ( 15 ft ) in length .
Mugilogobius platynotus , commonly known as the flatback mangrove goby , is a species of goby native to eastern Australia .
Hackelia nervosa is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Sierra stickseed .
Speothos is a genus of canid found in Central and South America .
The Hazar bleak ( Alburnus heckeli ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Atractopyge is a genus of trilobite that lived in what would be Asia and Europe from the middle Ordovician to the early Devonian from 472 - -412.3 mya , existing for approximately 59.7 million years .
Manipontonia psamathe is a species of saltwater shrimp that was first described in 1902 .
Horalabiosa is a genus of cyprinid fish found only in India .
Megalograptidae is an extinct family of eurypterids .
Triphysaria is a genus of five plants in the broomrape family which are known generally as owl's - clovers .
Ephedra altissima is a species of Ephedra that is native to the western Sahara ( Morocco , Algeria , Tunisia , Libya , Chad , Mauritania ) , and also to the Canary Islands .
Amphisbaena neglecta , also known as the neglected worm lizard , is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .
Sphagnum falcatulum is a species of peat moss .
Dorstenia peltata is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to the Dominican Republic and Cuba .
Hookeria is a genus of mainly tropical mosses .
Mycobacterium cookii is a species of the phylum actinobacteria ( Gram - positive bacteria with high guanine and cytosine content , one of the dominant phyla of all bacteria ) , belonging to the genus mycobacterium .
Antonietta luteorufa is a species of sea slug or aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Facelinidae .
Tropheus annectens is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika preferring a substrate consisting of large , fixed rock .
Serapias bergonii is a species of orchid found from Italy to western and southern Turkey .
Orthotylus virens is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that can be found in Austria , Baltic states ( except for Lithuania ) , Bulgaria , Czech Republic , France , Germany , Moldova , Poland , Russia , Slovakia , Switzerland , Ukraine , Scandinavia , and Benelux ( except for Belgium ) .
Rhamnus petiolaris is a buckthorn plant species endemic to Sri Lanka .
Berthella martensi is a species of sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurobranchidae .
Calliclinus geniguttatus is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Chile and the Atlantic coast of Argentina .
The harvest mite , Trombicula autumnalis , is a species of mite of the family Trombiculidae .
Cucumerunio websteri is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusc in the family Hyriidae .
Polygonum parryi is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common names Parry 's knotweed and prickly knotweed .
Pseudohelenoconcha spurca is an extinct species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Endodontidae .
The genus contains only one species , i.e. Plectroniella armata , which is found in southern Mozambique and northeastern South Africa .

Ulva chaetomorphoides is a species of tropical and benthic seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found in Gulf of Mexico and European waters .
Underwoodisaurus is a small genus of Australian Gekkonidae , described as thick - tailed or barking geckoes .
Microcachrys tetragona ( Creeping Pine or Creeping Strawberry Pine ) is a species of dioecious conifer belonging to the podocarp family ( Podocarpaceae ) .
Oeceoclades sclerophylla is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to Comoros and southeastern Madagascar .
Blattodea is an order of insects that contains the cockroaches and the termites .
Collinsia concolor is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Chinese houses .
Philodendron cordatum ( common names : philodendron angra dos reis , heart leaf philodendron ) is an epiphytic and epilithic species of Philodendron endemic to southeastern Brazil .
Monachather , common name mulga oats , is a genus of Australian plants in the grass family .
Nemacladus rigidus is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name stoutstem threadplant .
The Brachyceran infraorder Xylophagomorpha is a small group that consists solely of the family Xylophagidae , which presently contains subfamilies that were sometimes considered to be two small related families ( Coenomyiidae and Rachiceridae ) .
Corynephorus is a genus of European , North African , and Middle Eastern plants in the grass family .
Penicillium variabile is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which has been isolated from permafrost deposits . Penicillium variabile produces rugulovasine A and rugulovasine B This species occurs on wheat , flour , maize , rice , barley and it is also very common in indoor environments

Mimosaperdopsis apiculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimosaperdopsis .

Pronorites is a prolecanitid genus from the middle and upper Carboniferous , upper Mississippian and Pennsylvanian .
Pseudodusa is an extinct genus of prawn , containing only the species Pseudodusa frattigianii , known from the Solnhofen limestones of southern Germany .
Carex sylvatica is a species of sedge found in deciduous woodlands across Europe .
Stomatella auricula , common name the false ear shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The aloe - leafed cymbidium ( Cymbidium aloifolium ) is a species of orchid found in Asia , especially China and southeast Asia from Burma to Sumatra .
Puntius nigronotus also called as Malabar black - backed barb is a species of fish in the family Cyprinidae in Puntius genus .
Dipterocarpus verrucosus is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae , endemic to Brunei , Indonesia ( Kalimantan , Sumatra ) , Malaysia ( peninsular Malaysia , Sabah , Sarawak ) .

Chaerophyllum is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with 35 species native to Europe , Asia , North America , and northern Africa .
Pimephales vigilax , also known as the bullhead minnow , is a species of freshwater demersal fish , native to the Southern United States .
The Barbary leopard or North African leopard from the Atlas Mountains of North Africa has initially been described as a leopard subspecies ( Panthera pardus panthera ) in the late 18th century .
Fritillaria graeca is a European plant species in the lily family native to the Balkans(Albania , Macedonia , and Greece ) .

Antlerpeton is an extinct genus of early tetrapod from the Early Carboniferous of Nevada .
Interzumia is an afrotropical genus of potter wasps with a single species , Interzumia rufonigra .
Boonea bisuturalis ( also known as the three - toothed odostome or the two - groove odostome ) is a species of minute sea snail , a pyramidellid gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
It is the only species in the genus Adrorhizon and one of three genera in the subtribe Adrorhizinae .
Aenictus gracilis is a species of reddish brown army ant found in Borneo , Indonesia , Malaysia , Philippines , Bangladesh , India , Myanmar , and Sri Lanka .
Pseudotragiscus venus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudotragiscus .
Corallorhiza mertensiana was previously considered a subspecies of Corallorhiza maculata but was given species rank in 1997 by Freudenstein .
Cystoporata is an extinct order of Paleozoic bryozoans .
Gaultheria ovatifolia is a species of shrub in the heath family which is known by the common names western teaberry and Oregon spicy wintergreen .
Brasilodontidae is an extinct family of cynodonts closely related to mammals .
Urocoras longispinus is a funnel weaver spider species found in Central and Eastern Europe .
Scotinotylus sanctus is a species of sheet weaver found in Canada and the United States .

Cylindera bonina is a species of ground beetle of the subfamily Cicindelinae that is endemic to Micronesia .

The Semaeostomeae ( literally `` flag mouths '' ) are an order of large jellyfish characterized by four long , frilly oral arms flanking their quadrate mouths .
The Koepcke 's screech owl ( Megascops koepckeae ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Leptotyphlops burii , commonly known as the Arabian blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Fossarina picta is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .

Ternstroemia maclellandiana is a species of plant in the family Pentaphylacaceae .
Polinices immaculatus , common name the immaculate moonsnail , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Naticidae , the moon snails .

Fejervarya assimilis or Rana assimilis is a species of frog described from India .

Hoya aldrichii , commonly known as the Christmas Island Waxvine is a species of flowering plant in the Apocynaceae or dogbane family .

Paederus baudii is a species of rove beetles belonging to the family Staphylinidae subfamily Paederinae .
Platypus australis , commonly known as the polyphagous pinhole borer , is a species of ambrosia beetle in the weevil family Curculionidae found in Australia .
Wannanosaurus ( meaning `` Wannan lizard '' , named after the location where it was discovered ) is a genus of basal pachycephalosaurian dinosaur from the Campanian - age Upper Cretaceous Xiaoyan Formation , about 80 million years ago ( mya ) in what is now Anhui , China .
Antennarius is a genus of 11 species of fish in the family Antennariidae .
Cucumaria echinata is a sea cucumber species in the genus Cucumaria .
Platypleura haglundi is a medium - sized African cicada species , that occurs from northern South Africa to Zimbabwe , where it is found in diverse habitats .

Myscelia orsis is a species of nymphalid butterflies native to Brazil .

Cistanthe pygmaea , common name pygmy pussypaws , is a plant species endemic to California .
Megacephala fulgida is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Klug in 1834 , and could be found everywhere in South America except for Chile , Suriname , and Guyana .
Manicariais a palm genus which is found in Trinidad , Central and South America .

Conus ammiralis , common name the admiral cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Babelomurex tosanus is a species of sea snail , which is a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex or rock snails .
Navanax inermis , common name the California aglaja , is a species of predatory sea slug , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aglajidae and the order Cephalaspidea , the headshield slugs and bubble snails .
Acanthotrophon carduus is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae in the genus Acanthotrophon , the murex snails or rock snails .
It is the only species currently recognized in the genus Antiaris .
The family Micrococcaceae includes bacterial genera of Gram positive cocci that inhabit the air and skin , such as Micrococcus luteus .
Thelodus is an extinct genus of thelodont agnathan that lived during the Silurian period .
Anseranatidae , the magpie - geese , is a biological family of waterbirds .
Orobanche californica , known by the common name California broomrape , is a species of broomrape .
Carabus alajensis is a species of either black or brown coloured ground beetle from Carabidae family , that is endemic to Kyrgyzstan .
Oedemera is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Oedemeridae subfamily Oedemerinae .
Cymindis elegans is a ground beetle species in the genus Cymindis .
Zosne cachita is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Zosne that was discovered by Heller in 1922 .
Dypsis brevicaulis is a species of dwarf palm that is found on only three sites in Madagascar , with fewer than fifty plants ever found in the wild .
Solymus pictor is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Solymus .
Sea lemon is a loosely applied common name for a group of medium - sized to large shell - less colorful sea slugs or nudibranchs , specifically dorid nudibranchs in the taxonomic family Dorididae and other closely related families .
Paranotothenia is a genus of cod icefishes native to the Southern Ocean .
Gastrophysa is a genus of beetles in the family Chrysomelidae .
Dipteroides is an extinct genus of lungfish which lived during the Devonian period .
Awaous tajasica , the sand fish or sandfish , is a species of goby native to fresh and brackish waters of Brazil in South America with reports outside of Brazil considered to be questionable .
Bhavania is a small genus of loaches of the family Balitoridae .
Lactarius alnicola , commonly known as the golden milkcap , is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family .
Erigeron humilis is an arctic and alpine species of flowering plants in the daisy family known as Arctic Alpine fleabane .
Riolama is a small genus of lizards that are endemic to the Guiana Highlands in Venezuela .
Dimorphinites is an extinct genus from a well - known class of fossil cephalopods , the ammonites which lived during the Bajocian , .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Capricola fuscidula .
Podocarpus spinulosus , the Dwarf Plum Pine or Spiny - leaf Podocarp , is a species of podocarp native to the warm - temperate coastal regions of New South Wales and southern Queensland .
Niebla isidiaescens is a species of fruticose lichen in the family Ramalinaceae .
Grusonia grahamii is a species of cactus in the family Cactaceae .
The type species is Zoogenetes harpa ( Say , 1824 ) , known as the boreal top .
The Acartophthalmidae are a family of very small ( 1.0 - 2.5 mm ) , dark flies with pubescent arista , placed in the order Diptera .
Leptotyphlops koppesi , commonly known as Amaral 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the family Leptotyphlopidae .
Pardillana exempta is a species of Grasshopper in the genus Pardillana of the family Acrididae .
Haematopota pluvialis , the Common Horse Fly or ' Notch - horned Cleg Fly ' , is a species belonging to the family Tabanidae subfamily Tabaninae .
Megalocoerea recticornis is a species of plant bugs in the Miridae family , that is found throughout the U.K. , the rest of Europe and North America .
The single described species Thyenillus fernandensis is endemic to Bioko .
It was first named by Ge Sun , David L. Dilcher , Hongshan Wang and Zhiduan Chen in 2011 and the type species is Leefructus mirus .
Dendrobium brevicaudum , common name Mount Finnigan pencil orchid , is a species of orchid endemic to the Queensland , Australia .
Colaspidea globosa is a species of beetle in the Chrysomelidae family that can be found in France , Spain , on the island of Sicily , and North Africa .
Senecio aphanactis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names chaparral ragwort , rayless ragwort , and California groundsel .
Hensmania is a genus of herbs in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , first described as a genus in 1903 .
Thottapalayam virus ( TMPV ) is single - stranded , enveloped , negative - sense RNA virus species of the genus hantavirus in the Bunyaviridae family .
Oligoryzomys arenalis , also known as the sandy colilargo or sandy pygmy rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oligoryzomys of family Cricetidae .
The parrot subfamily Agapornithinae consists of three genera , the lovebirds ( Agapornis ) , the hanging parrots ( Loriculus ) and the guaiabero ( Bolbopsittacus lunulatus ) .
Zakerana nilagirica ( Nilgiris wart frog or Nilgiri frog ) is a species of frog that is endemic to the Western Ghats , India .
Eupholus humeridens is a species of beetle belonging to the family Curculionidae .
Dermocystidium is a genus of cyst forming parasitic protists of fish , which are the causative agents of dermocystidiosis .
Laminaria hyperborea is a species of large brown alga , a kelp in the family Laminariaceae , also known by the common names of tangle and cuvie .
Pseudopythina tsurumaru is a species of mollusc in the Kelliidae family .
Archistes is a small genus of sculpins native to the northern Pacific Ocean .
Urastoma cyprinae is a turbellarian that infects the gills of numerous species .
Mirabilis laevis , desert wishbone - bush , is a recently redefined species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family .
Enneanectes carminalis , known commonly as the Carmine triplefin or the Delicate triplefin in Mexico and the United Kingdom , is a species of triplefin blenny .
Conus locumtenens , common name the vice admiral cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Myxine glutinosa , known as the Atlantic hagfish in North America , and often simply as the hagfish in Europe , is a species of jawless fish of the genus Myxine .
Encheloclarias velatus is a species of airbreathing catfish endemic to Indonesia .
Felis chaus prateri is a subspecies of the jungle cat that inhabits western India and Sindh .
Anacamptis is a genus from the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) ; it is often abbreviated as Ant in horticulture .
Hainosaurus is an extinct genus of marine lizard belonging to the mosasaur family .
Orectolobus hutchinsi , the western wobbegong , is a species of carpet shark in the family Orectolobidae .
Polyrhachis scissa is a species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae , found in Sri Lanka , and southern India .
Penicillium angulare is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated in north America .
Leptotyphlops australis , or the Freiberg 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Hexalectris grandiflora , the largeflower crested coralroot or giant coral - root , is a species of orchid native to Mexico from Chihuahua south to Oaxaca , as well as to western and north - central Texas .
Niphoparmenoides tanganjicae is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Niphoparmenoides .
The Sandpaper saucer - berry , or Snot berry , ( Cordia monoica ) , is a species of flowering tree in the borage family , Boraginaceae , that is native to India , Sri Lanka and in African countries from Sudan , Ethiopia , Somalia , Kenya , Zimbabwe down to South Africa .
Eupterocerina conjuncta is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Eupterocerina of the family Tephritidae .
Chortophaga is a genus of `` band - winged grasshopper '' of the family Acrididae .
Kinosternon is a genus of small aquatic turtles from the Americas known commonly as mud turtles .
Hymenoxys quinquesquamata is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names rincon rubberweed or rincon bitterweed .
Siliquariidae is a family of sea snails with unusual , very loosely coiled shells .
Tylopilus nebulosus is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae found in eastern North America .
Kalmiopsis is a small genus of flowering plants in the heath family .
Anoplolepis ( also known as the `` common pugnacious ant '' ) is a genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae .
Sturisoma barbatum is a species of armored catfish native to Argentina and Brazil where it is found in the Paraguay River basin with reports that it can also be found in the Paraná and Uruguay River basins .
Poyntonophrynus grandisonae ( common name : Grandison 's toad or Mossamedes toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Mesopsocus fuscifrons is a species of Psocoptera from Mesopsocidae family that can be found in Macedonia and Kaliningrad , Russia .
Itajahya galericulata is a species of fungus in the family Phallaceae .
Leptosuchus is an extinct genus of leptosuchomorph phytosaurid with a complex taxonomical history .
Zhihengliuella alba is a Gram - positive , non - motile , white - pigmented , short rod actinobacterium , designated YIM 90734 T , the type species of its genus .
Salix atrocinerea , commonly called grey willow or large gray willow , is a species of willow .
Chiloglanis asymetricaudalis is a species of upside - down catfish native to Burundi , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Rwanda and Tanzania where it can be found in the Rusizi and Luiche Rivers .
Kalanchoe orgyalis also known as copper spoons is a species of the succulent genus Kalanchoe , in the family Crassulaceae .
Anaxarcha acuta is a species of praying mantis found in India .
Paragalerhinus is an extinct genus of Gorgonopsia .
Pseudobrickellia is a genus of Brazilian plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Sepia stellifera is a species of cuttlefish native to the Indian Ocean .
Camponotus herculeanus ( or Hercules Ant ) is a species of ant in the genus Camponotus .
Euphorbia serrata is a species of spurge known by the common names serrated spurge and sawtooth spurge .

Coccinia intermedia is a species of Coccinia which was first described in 2011 by Norbert Holstein .
Desmodium is a genus in the flowering plant family Fabaceae , sometimes called tick - trefoil , tick clover , hitch hikers or beggar lice .
Pentaceros is a genus of armorheads native to the Pacific , Indian , and eastern Atlantic Oceans .
Amphineurion is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1948 .
Mastigella is an amoeboid genus belonging to Amoebozoa .
Serpulina hyodysenteriae , formerly known as Brachyspira hyodysenteriae and Treponema hyodysenteriae , is a species of bacteria .
Cyamodus ( pron . : SIE - ah - MO - dus ) is a genus of placodonts discovered from fossil remains in Germany in the early - to - mid-19th century and was named by Christian Erich Hermann von Meyer in 1863 .
Agonum suturale is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily that is endemic to the United States .

The Indonesian mountain weasel ( Mustela lutreolina ) is a species of weasel that lives on the islands of Java and Sumatra in Indonesia at elevations over 1,000 metres ( 3,280 ft ) .

Acartauchenius himalayensis is a species of sheet weaver found in Pakistan .
Yaoshanicus is a genus of cyprinid fish found in eastern Asia with one species endemic to China and one endemic to Vietnam .
Chrosomus is a genus of small cyprinid fish found in freshwater habitats in the eastern half of the United States and Canada .
Glomeremus orchidophilus is a newly discovered species of raspy cricket found in the island of Réunion in the Mascarene Islands .
Streptomyces cavourensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Italy .

The genus comprises only one species , Kigelia africana , which occurs throughout tropical Africa from Eritrea and Chad south to northern South Africa , and west to Senegal and Namibia .

Sepia sokotriensis is a species of cuttlefish native to the western Indian Ocean , specifically off Sokotra Island , and probably east Africa .

Emblemariopsis bahamensis , the Blackhead blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic ocean .

Cyclotyphlops is a monotypic genus created for the blind snake species , C. deharvengi , found in southeastern Sulawesi , Indonesia .

Juscelinomys is a genus of burrowing mice .

Choaspes subcaudata is a species of butterfly belonging to the Hesperiidae family .
Hochstetter 's frog ( Leiopelma hochstetteri ) is a primitive frog native to New Zealand , one of only four extant species belonging to the taxonomic family Leiopelmatidae .
Cyclobatis is an extinct genus of stingray - like skate from the Upper Cretaceous of what is now Lebanon .
Hypopleuron caninum , the whiptail cusk , is a species of cusk - eel found in the Indian and western Pacific Oceans where it occurs at depths of from 300 to 575 metres ( 984 to 1,886 ft ) .
The Ameline swiftlet ( Aerodramus vanikorensis amelis ) , also known as the grey swiftlet , is usually considered a subspecies of the uniform swiftlet , although some taxonomists consider it a distinct species .
Tholodus is an extinct genus of basal ichthyopterygian known from the Middle Triassic ( mid - late Anisian to late Ladinian stage ) of Germany , northeastern Italy and possibly China .
Clathrus columnatus , commonly known as the column stinkhorn , is a saprobic species of basidiomycete fungus in the family Phallaceae .
Adeuomphalus ammoniformis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk unassigned in the superfamily Seguenzioidea .
Polistepipona is an Afrotropical genus of potter wasps .
Sparganium erectum , the simplestem bur - reed or branched bur - reed , is a perennial plant species in the genus Sparganium .
Gleviceras is an ammonite genus ( order Ammonitida ) that lived during the Early Jurassic Period , found in Canada , Hungary , Mexico and the United Kingdom .
Trachelipus nodulosus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Austria , Czech Republic , Germany , Hungary , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , and in all states of former Yugoslavia ( except for Republic of Macedonia and Slovenia ) .
Cimolesta ( from Greek , literally , `` White Clay Thieves '' ) is an extinct order of non - placental eutherian mammals .
Oxelytrum cayennense is a species of burying beetles or carrion beetles belonging to the family Silphidae .

Gracilibacillus is a genus of bacteria within the phylum Firmicutes .
Campanula scouleri is a species of bellflower known by the common names pale bellflower and Scouler 's harebell .
Gaylussacia mosieri , the hirsute huckleberry or woolly huckleberry , is a plant species native to the coastal plains of the southeastern United States ( Louisiana , Mississippi , Alabama , Georgia , Florida ) .

Dorcus nepalensis is a stag beetle species first described by Frederick William Hope in 1831 .

Carabus maurus maurus is a subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Armenia , Georgia , and Turkey .

Squalius cephaloides is a species of cyprinid fish known only from the Armutlu Peninsula in Turkey .
Asylosaurus ( meaning `` unharmed or sanctuary lizard '' ) is a genus of basal sauropodomorph dinosaur from the Late Triassic of England .
Furculattus is a genus of the spider family Salticidae ( jumping spiders ) , with the single species F. maxillosus .
Ptyctolaemus is a genus of agamid lizards from southern Asia .
Amoreuxia gonzalezii is a rare species of flowering plant in the Bixaceae known by the common names Santa Rita mountain yellowshow , Santa Rita throwup weed , saiya and temaqui .
Amblycirrhitus is a genus of hawkfishes found on tropical reefs worldwide .
Fouquieria formosa is a species of Fouquieria in the ocotillo family , native to central and southern Mexico ( Chiapas , Oaxaca , Guerrero , Puebla , Morelos , Michoacán , México State , Distrito Federal , Jalisco ) .
Tersomius is an extinct genus of dissorophoidean euskelian temnospondyl within the family Doleserpetontidae .
The Heleomyzidae are a small family of true flies in the insect order Diptera .
Diplotaxis siettiana , known in Spanish as jaramago de Alborán , is a species of flowering plant in the family Brassicaceae .
Pomacea dolioides is a South American species of freshwater snail with gills and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .
Pseudomasaris is a genus of pollen wasps of the family Vespidae , found in North America .
Sladenia shaefersi is a species of fish in the Lophiidae family .
Acalypha cupricola is a species of spurge native to the copper - rich soils of Katanga Province in the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Rhaphiolepis ( /ˌræfiˈɒlᵻpɪs/ or /ˌræfioʊˈlɛpᵻs/ ; ) is a genus of about fifteen species of evergreen shrubs and small trees in the family Rosaceae , native to warm temperate and subtropical eastern and southeastern Asia , from southern Japan , southern Korea and southern China south to Thailand and Vietnam .
Dendrocoelidae is a family of freshwater tricladida flatworms that has an holarctic distribution .
Apopyllus silvestrii is a spider species in the genus Apopyllus found in Peru , Bolivia , Brazil , Argentina and Chile .
Sibara filifolia , known the common names Santa Cruz Island winged rockcress or Santa Cruz Island rockcres , is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family .
Ambilobeia is an extinct genus of prawn which existed in Ambilobé , Madagascar during the Triassic period .
Gymnodorididae is a taxonomic family of sea slugs , dorid nudibranchs , gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Polyceroidea .
Amphilophus is a genus of cichlid fishes from Central America , ranging from southern Mexico to Panama .
Oedignathus inermis is a species of king crab found off the Pacific coasts of the United States and Canada , from California to Alaska , and disjunctly around the coasts of Japan .

Lepidium flavum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name yellow pepperweed .

The species Tombaatar sabuli is known from remains found in the Upper Cretaceous Djadokhta Formation of Ukhaa Tolgod , Mongolia .
