It contains only one species , Hecatompeda pyrocephala , which is found on the Solomon Islands .
Caobangia squamata is a species of fern known only from Vietnam and from Guangxi Province in southern China .
Hulsea brevifolia is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name shortleaf alpinegold , or shortleaf hulsea .
Telmatochromis bifrenatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it can be found at depths of from 5 to 10 metres ( 16 to 33 ft ) , occasionally down to 20 metres ( 66 ft ) .
Triteleiopsis , common name Bajalily or blue sand lily , is a genus of one known species of flowering plant found in Sonora , Baja California and southwestern Arizona .
Pliocyon is genus of large amphicyonid caniformian carnivoran mammals which inhabited North America from the Early Miocene subepoch to the Middle Miocene subepoch 20.6 - -13.6 Ma , existing for approximately 7 million years .
Syneta adamsi is a species of beetles from the family of leaf beetles , subfamily Synetinae .
Petrochelidon is a genus of birds known as cliff - nesting swallows .
Discodeles bufoniformis ( common name : warty webbed frog or Treasury Island webbed frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Lachesis muta is a venomous pit viper species found in South America ( including the island of Trinidad in the Republic of Trinidad and Tobago ) .
Haplochromis melanopterus is a species of cichlid endemic to the Tanzanian portion of Lake Victoria where it occurs in Smith Sound .
Duabanga moluccana is a species of tree native to Indonesia and surrounding areas .
Dallina is a genus of small to average size lampshells ( maximum 35 millimetres or 1.4 inches long ) .
Castilleja rubicundula is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name cream sacs .
Protanthea simplex is a species of sea anemone found in deep water off the coasts of north west Europe .
Cattleya dowiana ( literal translation : Dow 's Cattleya ) is a species of orchid .
Carabus maurus is a species of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Near East , and countries like Armenia , Georgia , Iran , Iraq , Israel , Lebanon , Syria , Turkey , Turkmenistan , and on Cyprus .
Oxycera leonina , the twin - spotted major , is a European species of soldier fly .
Hedera rhombea , or Japanese ivy or songak , is a species of ivy ( genus Hedera ) which is native to the coast of East Asia and some islands of east Asia .
Hoplomyzon is a genus of banjo catfishes that are native to tropical South America .
Semiarundinaria fastuosa , common names Narihira bamboo , Narihira cane , and Narihiradake , is a species of flowering plant in the grass family Poaceae , native to Japan .
Pilophorini is a tribe of plant bug .
Ants are eusocial insects of the family Formicidae /fɔːrˈmɪsᵻdiː/ and , along with the related wasps and bees , belong to the order Hymenoptera .
Ptereleotris hanae , the Blue hana goby , is a species of dartfish native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Emarginula nordica , common name the northern emarginula , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Diedra cockerellana , Cockerell 's moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Kosmoceratidae is an extinct ammonite family from the Callovian ( Middle Jurassic ) to Early Cretaceous .
Agapanthia villosoviridescens , also known as the golden - bloomed grey longhorn beetle , is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that can be found in the Caucasus , Europe , Kazakhstan , the Near East , Russia and Turkey .
Agrimoniinae is a subtribe of the rose family , Rosaceae .
Platymantis boulengeri ( Boulenger 's wrinkled ground frog or Boulenger 's platymantis ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Haptanthus is a monotypic genus containing the sole species Haptanthus hazlettii , a shrub or small tree known only from the locality of Matarras in the Arizona Municipality in Honduras .
Tomoxia latenotata is a species of beetle in the Tomoxia genus that is in the Mordellidae family .
Erigeron linearis is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name desert yellow fleabane or narrow leaved fleabane .
Pachyophiidae is an extinct family of snakes which lived during the Cenomanian stage of the Late Cretaceous .
Breviraja spinosa is a species of ray in the Rajidae family .
Lupinus antoninus is a rare species of lupine known by the common name Anthony Peak lupine .
Iris foetidissima ( Stinking iris , gladdon , Gladwin iris , roast - beef plant , stinking gladwin ) , is a species of iris found in open woodland , hedgebanks and sea - cliffs .
Exotheca is a genus of African and Southeast Asian plants in the grass family .
Lupinus albifrons , silver lupine , white - leaf bush lupine , or evergreen lupine , is a species of lupine ( lupin ) .
Serratia entomophila is a species of bacteria that like its cogenerate species uses itaconate .
Musa maclayi is a species of seeded banana native to Papua New Guinea and possibly the Solomon Islands .
Mylossoma aureum is a species of serrasalmid native to the Amazon and Orinoco Basins .
Perpolita is a subgenus ( of Nesovitrea ) or genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Oxychilidae .
Senecio californicus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name California ragwort .
Nebria viridipennis is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Georgia and Russia .
Psilocarphus oregonus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Oregon woollyheads and Oregon woolly marbles .
Tagetes lemmonii , Lemmon 's marigold , is a North American species wild marigolds within the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) .
Levenhookia , also known as the styleworts , is a genus of ten recognized species in the family Stylidiaceae and is endemic to Australia .
Lepidium pinnatifidum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known in English by the common name featherleaf pepperweed .
Draba obovata is a species of plant in the Brassicaceae family .
Pannychella callicera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pannychella .
The Barrandeocerina comprise a suborder of Early Paleozoic nautiloid cephalopods , primitively coiled but later forms may be cyroconic , gyroconic , torticonic , and even breviconic , all having empty siphuncles with thin connecting rings .

Holospira hamiltoni , common name Hamilton holospira , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Urocoptidae .

Omphalea ankaranensis is a plant species endemic to a small region in northern Madagascar .
Cystoseira baccata is a species of brown seaweed in the family Fucaceae .
Dinoponera australis is a species of ant notable for its lack of distinct queen caste .
Scolypopa australis , commonly known as the passionvine hopper is a species of planthopper ( Fulgoroidea ) in the insect family Ricaniidae found in Australia .
Tetraperone is a genus of flowering plants in the cosmos tribe within the daisy family .
Berosus aculeatus is a species of hydrophilid beetle native to the United States and Cuba .
Gymnospermium is a group of tuberous flowering plants in the barberry family described as a genus in 1839 .
Sphaerodactylus glaucus is a species of gecko known by the common name collared dwarf gecko ( geco - enano collarejo in Spanish ) .
Colasposoma mutabile is a species of beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae , described by Joseph Sugar Baly in 1867 .
Acanthoclymeniidae is a family of early , primitive , clymeniid ammonoid cephalopods that lived during the Late Devonian .
Tonicella lineata , commonly known as the lined chiton , is a species of chiton from the North Pacific .
Ancistrochilus rothschildianus is a small species of semi - terrestrial , orchid endemic to the African tropics .
Tritonia khaleesi is a species of sea slug , a dendronotid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Tritoniidae .
The Eurasian lynx is the largest lynx species , ranging in length from 80 to 130 cm ( 31 to 51 in ) and standing about 60 - -75 cm ( 24 - -30 in ) at the shoulder .
Petrolisthes armatus , the green porcelain crab , is a species of small porcelain crab in the family Porcellanidae .

Antennaria rosea is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name rosy pussytoes .

Zapogon evermanni , Evermann 's cardinalfish , is a species of cardinalfish native to tropical reefs in the Indian and Pacific oceans and the western Atlantic Ocean .
Lecythis ampla is a species of woody plant in the Lecythidaceae family , which also includes the Brazil nut ( Bertholletia excelsa ) .
Chaenopsis stephensi is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs around Venezuela and Yucatan , Mexico , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
Agaronia acuminata , common name the pointed ancilla , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
The Oceanospirillales are an order of Proteobacteria , with seven families .

The Centridini are a tribe of large apid bees , many of which possess adaptations for carrying floral oils rather than ( or in addition to ) pollen or nectar .
Salmacis bicolor is a species of sea urchin in the family Temnopleuroida found in the western Indian Ocean and the Red Sea .

Vitis mustangensis , commonly known as the mustang grape , is a species of grape that is native to the southern United States .

Simaethistoidea is an obscure superfamily of pyralid - like moths with two genera , whose biology and relationships among the Ditrysia is currently unknown , namely the Australian Metaprotus ( 2 species ) and the China and North Indian Simaethistis ( 2 species ) ( Dugdale et al . , 1999 ) .
Typhochlaena is a genus of rare tarantulas .
Corylus avellana , the common hazel , is a species of hazel native to Europe and western Asia , from the British Isles south to Iberia , Greece , Turkey and Cyprus , north to central Scandinavia , and east to the central Ural Mountains , the Caucasus , and northwestern Iran .
Camponotus laevigatus or the giant carpenter ant is a species of carpenter ant native to eastern Canada , the United States , and Mexico .

Hulettia is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish found in the Morrison Formation in the western United States , measuring approximately three to four inches in length .
Pelicaria vermis , known as the small ostrich foot shell is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Struthiolariidae .

Helianthus dissectifolius is a rare Mexican species of sunflower .
Drosera subhirtella , the sunny rainbow , is a scrambling or climbing perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera .
Gelasine is a genus of flowering plants in the family Iridaceae , first described in 1840 .
Tragopogon miscellus , the Moscow salsify , is a species native to the States of Washington and Idaho .
Dorocordulia libera , the racket - tailed emerald , is a species of the dragonfly in the family Corduliidae found in North America .
Meromacrus is a genus of 43 neotropical and nearctic flower flies or hoverflies
Cynapes wrighti is a species of spider from the family Salticidae .
Leavenworthia crassa is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family , Brassicaceae , known commonly as the fleshy - fruit gladecress .
Omobranchus is a large genus of combtooth blennies found in the Pacific , Atlantic , and Indian oceans .
Platynematichthys notatus is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the monotypic genus Platynematichthys of the family Pimelodidae .
Titoceres jaspideus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Titoceres .
Vasum muricatum , common name the Caribbean vase , is a species of medium to large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinellidae .
Alpharetrovirus is a genus of the retroviridae family .
Bostrychus is a genus of sleeper gobies mostly native to eastern Asia to Australia with one species being found along the Atlantic coast of Africa .
Vanda limbata is a species of orchid native to Java , the Lesser Sunda Islands and the Philippines .
Zephyranthes rosea , commonly known as the Cuban zephyrlily , rosy rain lily , rose fairy lily , rose zephyr lily or the pink rain lily , is a species of rain lily native to Peru and Colombia .
Geosaurinae is a subfamily of metriorhynchid crocodyliforms from the Middle Jurassic to the Early Cretaceous ( Bajocian - Valanginian ) of Europe , North America and South America .
Barbus euboicus , known as the petropsaro or the Evia barbel , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family found only in Greece .
Rhododendron dauricum is a rhododendron species native to Eastern Siberia , Mongolia , North China , and Hokkaido , Japan , with purple flowers .
Achnatherum aridum is a species of grass known by the common name Mormon needlegrass .
Janetogalathea californiensis is a species of squat lobster in a monotypic genus in the family Galatheidae .
The order Trigonotarbida is an extinct group of arachnids whose fossil record extends from the late Silurian to the early Permian ( c. 419 to 290 million years ago ) .
Orioles are colourful Old World passerine birds in the genus Oriolus , the namesake of the corvoidean family Oriolidae .
Lactobacillus paraplantarum is a rod shaped species of lactic acid bacteria first isolated from beer and human faeces .
Cheiridopsis is a genus that consists of 100 flowering succulent perennial plants , native to semi - arid regions in the far west of Namibia and South Africa .
Funtumia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1900 .
Turbonilla abrupta , common name the abrupt turbonilla , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
The Assam laughingthrush ( Trochalopteron chrysopterum ) is a species of bird in the Leiothrichidae family .
Allium kaschianum is a plant species from Central Asia ( Xinjiang , Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan ) .
Karanisia is an extinct genus of strepsirrhine primate and is represented by two species , K. clarki and K. arenula .
Platerodrilus paradoxus is a species of trilobite beetle .
Gibbonsia metzi , the Striped kelpfish , is a species of clinid native to the Pacific coast of North America from British Columbia , Canada , to Baja California , Mexico .
Sio nordenskjoldii , Nordenskjold 's bigscale , is a species of ridgehead found in the southern oceans at depths of from 200 to 3,000 metres ( 660 to 9,840 ft ) .
Amphisbaena fuliginosa , also known as the black - and - white worm lizard , speckled worm lizard or spotted worm lizard , is a species of amphisbaenian in the genus Amphisbaena .
Aphidius nigripes is a species of parasitoid wasp in the subfamily Aphidiinae of the family Braconidae .
Lusitanisuchus is an extinct genus of mesoeucrocodylian crocodylomorph .
Xyliphius barbatus is a species of banjo catfish that is endemic to Argentina where it is found in the Paraguay - Paraná River system basin .
Steiractinia is a genus of South American plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Beris vallata , the orange legionnaire or common orange legionnaire , is a European species of soldier fly .
Ochrosia haleakalae , island yellowwoood or hōlei , is a species of plant in the Plumeria family , Apocynaceae that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Cyclocardia borealis , or the northern cardita , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Carditidae .
Artemisia nova is a North American species of sagebrush , known by the common name black sagebrush .
Leptotyphlops nursii , or Nurse 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Fusigobius signipinnis , commonly called flasher sandgoby or signal goby among various vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiidae .
Oryx is a genus consisting of four large antelope species .
Sagittaria papillosa , the nipplebract arrowhead , is a plant species native to the south - central United States ( Texas , Oklahoma , Louisiana , Arkansas and Mississippi ) .
Lupinoblennius nicholsi , the Highfin blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Atlantic ocean .
Teyumbaita ( meaning `` lizard ( Teyu ´ ) and parrot ( Mbaita ´ ) '' in the Brazilian aborigine Tupi - Guaraní language ) is an extinct genus of hyperodapedontine rhynchosaur from the Upper Triassic ( early Norian age ) epoch of Paleorrota , Rio Grande do Sul , southern Brazil .
Archaeotriton is an extinct genus of prehistoric salamanders .
Meridolum gulosum is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Camaenidae .
Pediastrum duplex is a type species of fresh water green algae in the genus pediastrum .
Tilesia is a genus of Cuban and South American plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Pyrodictium abyssi is a species of heterotrophic marine archaeal hyperthermophile that can grow at 110 ° C ( 230 ° F ) .
Nebria uralensis is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found Russia and Palearctic region .
Ergalatax crassulnata , common name : the coarse cronia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Litaneutria obscura , commonly known as the obscure ground mantis , is a species of praying mantis in North America .
Banksia erythrocephala var . erythrocephala is a variety of Banksia erythrocephala .
Cycas armstrongii is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , endemic to Australia 's Northern Territory .
Conover 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys conoveri ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Micropristis is an extinct genus of guitarfish from the Middle Cretaceous of what is now Lebanon .
Sarcococca confusa ( sweet box ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Buxaceae , probably native to western China .
Callionymus melanotopterus is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific waters of Indonesia where it inhabits estuaries .
Hatcheria macraei is a species of pencil catfish and the only species in its genus .
Mycothele is a fungal genus in the family Gloeophyllaceae .
The Canthyloscelidae are a small family of midges closely related to the Scatopsidae .
Bryobrittonia is a genus of moss in the family Encalyptaceae ; it contains the single species Bryobrittonia longipes .
Hymenaea mexicana is an extinct legume species in the family Fabaceae described from a series of isolated fossil petals , leaflets , and amber .
Hypogomphia is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described in 1873 .
Pachira quinata , commonly known as Pochote , is a species of flowering tree in the mallow family , Malvaceae .
Platorchestia platensis is a species of sand flea , an amphipod crustacean that lives on beaches .
Lontra is a genus of otters from the American continent .
Falsilunatia powelli is a species of deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Naticidae , the moon snails .
Haworthia mucronata is a species of the genus Haworthia in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , endemic to the Little Karoo region , in the Western Cape Province of South Africa .
Chrysothamnus eremobius called Pintwater rabbitbrush , is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Neottia auriculata ( syn . Listera auriculata ) , the auricled twayblade , is a species of terrestrial orchid found in northeastern North America ( Labrador , New Brunswick and Maine west to Manitoba and Minnesota .
Pocota personata is a species of European hover fly .
Discosomatidae is a family of marine cnidarians closely related to the true sea anemones ( Actiniaria ) .
Coleonyx reticulatus is a species of small gecko native to the United States ( Texas ) and Mexico ( Coahuila ) .
Houstonia rosea , the rose bluet , is a North American plant species in the coffee family .
Belosaepiidae is a family of cephalopods known from the Eocene , and bearing close similarity to the sepiid cuttlefish , whilst retaining the remnants of a belemnite - like guard .
Fagus mexicana , the Mexican Beech or Haya , is a species of beech endemic to northeastern and central Mexico , where it occurs from southwest Tamaulipas south to Hidalgo and Puebla .
Arachniodes squamulosa is a species of fern in the Dryopteridaceae family .
The Cimicidae are a family of small parasitic insects that feed exclusively on the blood of warm - blooded animals .
Encheloclarias prolatus is a species of airbreathing catfish endemic to Malaysia where it is only found in western Sarawak on the island of Borneo .
Manilkara mayarensis is a plant species in the family of Sapodillas , which grows wild only in Cuba 's Oriente Province .
Lycaste powellii is a species of terrestrial orchid endemic to Panama .
Westringia glabra , commonly known as Violet Westringia , is a shrub species that is endemic to Australia .
Rhinostomus barbirostris , common name Bottlebrush Weevil or Bearded Weevil , is a species of true weevil family .
Praepapilio is an extinct genus of swallowtail butterfly from the middle Eocene deposits of Colorado , United States , comparable to the Lutetian epoch in age .
Ptycholepiformes were an order of extinct prehistoric bony fish .
Maackia raphidia is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
Gomphostemma is a genus of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described in 1830 .
Electotreta is an extinct genus of firefly closely resembling Ototretinae from the Eocene Epoch .
Rhagonycha nigriceps is a species of soldier beetles belonging to the family Cantharidae , subfamily Cantharinae .
Turbo cornutus , common name the horned turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
Bathyteuthis abyssicola , also known as the deepsea squid , is a species of squid in the family Bathyteuthidae .
Alectryon oleifolius , commonly known as the Boonaree or inland rosewood , is a species of small tree of the soapberry family Sapindaceae , native to Australia .
Charadriiformes is a diverse order of small to medium - large birds .
Chilina fulgurata is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Chilinidae .
Malephora is a genus of succulent plants in the ice plant family .
Corydalis ( Greek korydalís `` crested lark '' ) is a genus of about 470 species of annual and perennial herbaceous plants in the Papaveraceae family , native to the temperate Northern Hemisphere and the high mountains of tropical eastern Africa .
Ecdeiocolea is a genus of grass - like plants from Western Australia .
Cymbopogon commutatus , widely believed to be synonymous with Cymbopogon parkeri , is a perennial grass species , commonly known as Incense grass , Aromatic rush , Camel 's hay , or Lemon grass .
Rhabdodendron is a genus comprising two or three species of tropical South American trees .
Rhodocollybia is a genus of Basidiomycete mushroom .
Machimosaurus is an extinct genus of teleosaurid crocodyliform from the Late Jurassic ( Kimmeridgian and Tithonian ) and Early Cretaceous .
Squalius cappadocicus , the Cappadocian chub , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Cistanthe pulchella ( formerly Calyptridium pulchellum ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name Mariposa pussypaws .
Horkelia parryi is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Parry 's horkelia .
Coccophagus acanthosceles is a species of chalcid wasp belonging to the family Aphelinidae .
Scuticaria strictifolia is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( São Paulo ) .
Bourgueticrinida is an order of crinoids that typically live deep in the ocean .
Rorippa sylvestris ( the creeping yellowcress , keek , or yellow fieldcress ; syn . Radicula sylvestris ( L. ) Druce ) is an invasive species of plant in the United States .
Arum hygrophilum is a species of Arum that has a disjunct distribution , found in Israel , Jordan , Lebanon , Syria , Cyprus and Morocco .
Bolitoglossa orestes ( common name : Culata mushroomtongue salamander ; Spanish : salamandra meridena ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Norops rubribarbus also known as the Sagua de Tánamo anole is a species of lizard in the family Polychrotidae .
Mirosternus discolor is a beetle species in the family Anobiidae .
Crepidula depressa is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails or slipper limpets , cup - and - saucer snails , and hat snails .
The Hoffmanniinae is an adrianitid ammonoid cephalopod subfamily established for the middle Permian genus Hoffmannia .
Encephalartos princeps is a species of cycad that is native to Eastern Cape Province of South Africa .
Pristidactylus is a genus of lizards from Chile and Argentina .
Plantago hookeriana is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names Hookers plantain , tallow weed , and California plantain .
Mekosuchinae was a subfamily of crocodiles from Australia and the South Pacific that have now become extinct .
The Cuban ivory - billed woodpecker or carpintero real ( Campephilus principalis bairdii ) is , or was , a Cuban subspecies of the ivory - billed woodpecker ( Campephilus principalis ) .
Setaria parviflora is a species of grass known by the common names marsh bristlegrass , knotroot bristle - grass , bristly foxtail and yellow bristlegrass .
Cereatta elegans is a harvestman species in the genus Cereatta found in Cameroon .
The Jujuy tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys juris ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Nemastylis , pleatleaf , is a genus of flowering plants in the iris family , first described as a genus in 1835 .
Omphalomargarites sagamiensis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails ( not assigned to a subfamily ) .
Wyethia helenioides is a species of flowering plants in the sunflower family commonly referred to as gray mule 's ears or whitehead mule - ears .
Lophostoma is a genus of Central and South American bats in the family Phyllostomidae .
Mora moro , the common mora , is a deep - sea fish , the only species in the genus Mora .
Sedum spathulifolium is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family known by the common names broadleaf stonecrop and Colorado stonecrop .
Denazinemys was a genus of baenodd turtle that lived in the Late Cretaceous of New Mexico .
Theodoxus pallasi is a species of a freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae , the nerites .
Viola praemorsa is a species of violet known by the common names canary violet , Astoria violet , and yellow montane violet .
Gymnopis syntrema is a species of caecilian in the family Dermophiidae .
Phyllosiphon is a genus of parasitic green algae , specifically of the Trebouxiophyceae .
Pestarella tyrrhena ( formerly Callianassa tyrrhena ) is a species of thalassinidean crustacean ( ghost shrimp or mud shrimp ) which grows to a length of 70 mm ( 2.8 in ) .
Brunsvigia josephinae , commonly called Josephine 's lily or candelabra lily , is a deciduous , subtropical species of Brunsvigia originating from South Africa .
Rhopalosoma is a genus of wasps in family Rhopalosomatidae .
Pterynotus elongatus , common name : the club murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Hymenopappus scabiosaeus , the Carolina woollywhite , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Cephaloleia cyanea is a species of rolled - leaf beetle in the family Chrysomelidae , first found in Costa Rica , Colombia and Venezuela .
Leptacris maxima is a species of grasshopper in the Acrididae family .
Casphalia elegans is a moth species in the genus Casphalia found in Ghana .
Calochortus monophyllus is a North American species of flowering plants in the lily family known by the common name yellow star - tulip .
Cleome ornithopodioides or bird spiderflower is the type species of the genus Cleome which is part of the family Cleomaceae or Brassicaceae .
Plectolites is a coiled nautiloid cephalopod from Nevada ( USA ) somewhat reminiscent of the genus Plectoceras of the Barrandeocerina .
Crataegus lepida is the smallest of the hawthorn species in series Lacrimatae , the `` weeping hawthorns '' , of the southeastern U.S ..
Clanculus ringens , common name the ringent clanculus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Xerula australis is a species of gilled mushroom in the family Physalacriaceae that is found in Australia .
Delphinium robustum is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common names Wahatoya Creek larkspur and robust larkspur .
Pseudomyrmex pallidus is a species of ant found in the Nearctic ecozone with an extensive range throughout the southern United States to Central America .
Abies flinckii , commonly known as the Jalisco fir , is a species of conifer in the genus Abies .
Sarcofahrtiopsis is a genus of small flesh flies .
Zosterophyllum was a genus of Silurian - Devonian vascular land plant with branching axes on which kidney - shaped sporangia were arranged in lateral positions .
Velocisaurus ( `` swift lizard '' ) is a genus of ceratosaurian theropod dinosaur from the Cretaceous period of Argentina .
Lottia subrugosa is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lottiidae .
Limnonectes doriae ( common name : Burmese wart frog , Doria 's frog , or red stream frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family found in the Southeast Asia .
Euphilotes rita , the rita blue or desert buckwheat blue , is a species of butterfly of the Lycaenidae family .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Stanglomyces taxophilus , found in South America .
Temognatha is a genus of metallic wood - boring beetles .
Thunbergia gregorii , commonly known as orange clockvine or orange trumpet vine , is a herbaceous perennial climbing plant species in the family Acanthaceae , native to East Africa and sometimes cultivated as an ornamental vine .
Erythronium mesochoreum ( prairie fawn lily or midland fawnlily ) is a plant species in the lily family , native to the US states of Illinois , Iowa , Indiana , Nebraska , Kansas , Missouri , Oklahoma , Texas and Arkansas .
Prolabeo batesi is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Sierra Leone .
Zakerana teraiensis ( Terai cricket frog or Terai wart(y ) frog ) is a species of frog that is found in southern Nepal , adjacent Sikkim and northeastern India , and southeastern and central Bangladesh .

Haywardiamyia brevicornis is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Haywardiamyia of the family Tachinidae .
Chrysidini is a very large tribe of cuckoo wasps ( the family Chrysididae ) ; this tribe contains more than half of all chrysidid species .
Pinus occidentalis , or Hispaniolan pine , is a pine endemic to the island of Hispaniola , where it is the predominant species in the Hispaniolan pine forests of Haiti and the Dominican Republic .

Titanoeca is a genus of spiders that occurs mainly in Eurasia , with three species found only in North America ( T. americana , T. brunnea , T. nigrella ) .

Huperzia phlegmaria ( commonly known as either coarse tassel fern , or common tassel fern ) is an epiphytic species of tassel fern native to rainforests in Madagascar , some islands in the Indian Ocean , Asia , Australasia and many Pacific Islands .

Phyllodoce caerulea , known as blue heath in British English and purple mountain heather or blue mountainheath in American English , is an evergreen species of dwarf shrub that grows up to around 15 cm ( 6 in ) tall , and bears clusters of 2 - -6 purple flowers .
Holonematidae is an extinct family of relatively large arthrodire placoderms from the Early to Late Devonian .

Procryptocerus is a Neotropical genus of gliding ants , with the ability to `` parachute '' by steering their fall if they drop off of the tree they 're on .
Orthodera rubrocoxata is a species of praying mantis found in Australia .
Solidago spithamaea is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Blue Ridge goldenrod .
Clibanarius digueti is a species of hermit crab that lives off the western coast of Mexico , and is abundant in the Gulf of California .
The Bembicinae comprise a large subfamily of crabronid wasps that includes over 80 genera and over 1800 species .
Scleraxonia is a suborder of corals , a member of the phylum Cnidaria
Delphinium hybridum is a plant species in the genus Delphinium .
Loris is the common name for the strepsirrhine primates of the subfamily Lorinae ( sometimes spelled Lorisinae ) in the family Lorisidae .

Physalis crassifolia is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common names yellow nightshade groundcherry and thick - leaf ground - cherry .
Rangeroceras is an extinct nautiloid cephalopod genus that lived in what is now western North America during the latter part of the Early Ordovician .
Percina burtoni , the blotchside logperch or blotchside darter , is a species of fish in the Percidae family .
Habenaria repens , commonly called the water - spider bog orchid or the floating orchid , is an orchid species widespread across Latin America from Mexico and the West Indies south to Argentina , as well as in the Southeastern United States from Texas and Oklahoma east to Florida and the Carolinas plus an isolated population in Virginia .
Camponotus sericeus is a species of carpenter ant ( genus Camponotus ) widely distributed in the Afrotropical and oriental regions .
Streptomyces stelliscabiei or is a streptomycete bacterium species that is associated with common scab in potatoes .
Coroicoia ligata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Coroicoia .
Abralia siedleckyi is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod known from its type locality in the waters off South Africa .
Hesperaloe funifera ( New Mexico false yucca ) is a plant species native to Texas ( Val Verde County ) and northern Mexico ( Coahuila , Sonora , San Luis Potosí , Nuevo León ) , but sometimes cultivated as an ornamental elsewhere .
Pterostylis pyramidalis , commonly known as the Tall snail orchid or Leafy snail orchid is a species of orchid which is endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Odontanthera is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1883 .
Dekeyseria niveata is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the upper Orinoco River basin .
Protosiren ( taxonomic family Protosirenidae ) is an extinct early genus of the order Sirenia .
The Gomphidae are a family in the Odonata commonly referred to as clubtail dragonflies ; the family contains about 90 genera and 900 species .
Echeandia ( common name craglily ) is a genus of New World plants in the century plant subfamily within the asparagus family .
The Blue Ridge two - lined salamander ( Eurycea wilderae ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to the United States .
The Campylobacterales are an order of Proteobacteria which make up the epsilon subdivision , together with the small family Nautiliaceae .
Schistocerca nitens is a species of grasshopper known by several common names , including vagrant grasshopper and gray bird grasshopper .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Bryodina rhypariza .
Recilia dorsalis is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that can be found in India , Japan , Korea , Malaysia , the Philippines , Sri Lanka , Borneo island , Taiwan , and Henan , province of China .
Xanthoeme signaticornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Xanthoeme .
Hyperolius argus is a common species living near water in low elevation dense , humid savanna and grassland .
Umoonasaurus is an extinct genus of plesiosaur belonging to the family Leptocleididae .
Phlomis fruticosa ( Jerusalem sage ) is a species of flowering plant of the Lamiaceae family , native to Albania , Cyprus , Greece , Italy , Turkey , and regions of the former Yugoslavia .
Ornithopus perpusillus or little white bird's - foot , is a plant species of the genus Ornithopus .
Cyllecoris ernsti is a species of bug in Miridae family that is endemic to Crete .
Osteodontornis is an extinct seabird genus .
Urechis unicinctus ( simplified Chinese : 海肠 ; traditional Chinese : 海腸 ; pinyin : hǎicháng ; Japanese : 螠虫 or ユムシ yumushi ; Hangul : 개불 ; RR : gaebul ) is a species of marine spoon worm .
Paphiopedilum wardii is a species of orchid found from southwestern Yunnan to Myanmar .
Holocentrus is a genus of squirrelfishes found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Heliomeris multiflora is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family called the Showy goldeneye .
Phenacovolva rosea , also known as the Rosy spindle cowry , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ovulidae , the ovulids , cowry allies or false cowries .
Boechera oxylobula , common name Glenwood Springs Rockcress , is a plant species referred to as Arabis demissa in many older publications .
Telmatochromis temporalis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where they areas with rocky substrates usually at depths of from 5 to 10 metres ( 16 to 33 ft ) though occasionally down to 20 metres ( 66 ft ) .
Anisus spirorbis is a species of small freshwater air - breathing snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Banksia acanthopoda is a species of shrub in the Proteaceae family .
Origanum rotundifolium ( round - leaved oregano ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to Turkey , Armenia and Georgia .
Abelmoschus angulosus is a plant species in the family Malvaceae , found in the Indian Subcontinent , Cambodia , Laos , Vietnam and Indonesia .
Uracentron flaviceps , the tropical thornytail iguana or Amazon thornytail iguana is an elusive species of medium sized arboreal lizard found in the tropical lowlands of the Amazon Rainforest .
Calliandra humilis ( common name dwarf stickpea ) is a species of flowering plants of the genus Calliandra in the Fabaceae family .
Renealmia alpinia is a flowering plant species native to the Americas , where it grows from Southern Mexico through much of South America , though not in the Southern Cone .
Alanqa is known only from five fragments of the front upper and lower jaws , and possibly a neck vertebra , representing the single type species Alanqa saharica .
Forficula scudderi is a species of earwig in the family Forficulidae .
Rhynchotherium is an extinct genus of proboscidea endemic to North America and Central America during the Miocene through Pliocene from 13.650 - -3.6 Ma , living for approximately 10 million years .
Daceton armigerum is a Neotropical species of arboreal ants , distributed throughout northern South America .
The Timor green pigeon ( Treron psittaceus ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Samaropsis is a form genus named by Goeppert in 1864 .
Turritriton tenuiliratus , common name : the thin - lined triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Mimon is a bat genus from South America .
Chrozophoreae is a tribe of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae .
Eleutherodactylus counouspeus is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the Massif de la Hotte , Haiti .
Stenella canavaliae or Stenella canavaliae - roseae , formerly known as Cercospora canavaliae is a species of anamorphic fungi .
Veronaea is a genus of ascomycete fungi , which manifest as brownish colonies .
Stenodyneriellus is an Australasian and Indomalayan genus of potter wasps .
Oeceoclades perrieri is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to Mozambique and northwestern Madagascar .
Miodentosaurus is a genus of thalattosaurian ( a type of extinct marine reptile ) from the Late Triassic of China .
Wall spider is the common name for members of the genus Oecobius .
Mycobonia is a genus of tooth fungi in the family Polyporaceae .
Pseudotropheus perspicax is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is known from Deep Bay .
Coloradisaurus ( meaning `` Colorados ( from Los Colorados Formation ) lizard '' ) is a genus of massospondylid sauropodomorph dinosaur .
Platanthera peramoena , the purple fringeless orchid , is a species of flowering plant in the orchid family .
Psammechinus is a genus of sea urchins in the family Parechinidae containing two species :
Mordellistena occidentalis is a species of beetle in the Mordellistena genus that is in the Mordellidae family , which is a part of the Tenebrionoidea superfamily .
Nematomorpha ( sometimes called Gordiacea , Nematomorpha commonly known as horsehair worms or Gordian worms ) are a phylum of parasitoid animals superficially similar to nematode worms in morphology , hence the name .
Nebria quezeli is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to northern part of Morocco .
Tricladida ( triclads ) is an order of turbellarians , a group of free - living flatworms .
Haematopota crassicornis , the Black - horned Cleg is a species in the horse - fly family , Tabanidae .
Didemnum proliferum is a rare species of sea squirt in the family Didemnidae .
Slimonia is a genus of Silurian eurypterid roughly similar to the genus Pterygotus .
Calochortus amoenus is a species of flowering plant in the lily family which is commonly known as purple fairy - lantern .
Clitocybe glacialis is a species of mushroom in the family Tricholomataceae .
Porcellio albinus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that can be found on Canary Islands and in North Africa .
Todaropsis eblanae , also known as the lesser flying squid , is a species of short finned squid in the monotypic genus Todaropsis of the family Ommastrephidae .
The ground sloths of the extinct genus Megalocnus ( `` Great Sloth '' ) were among the largest of the Caribbean ground sloths , with individuals estimated to have weighed up to 90 kg ( 200 lb ) when alive .
Pseudozioidea is a superfamily of crabs , formerly treated in the Eriphioidea , Carpilioidea , Xanthoidea , Pilumnoidea and Goneplacoidea .
Polemonium micranthum is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names annual polemonium or annual Jacob's - ladder .
The Ceratobatrachidae are a family of frogs found in the Malay Peninsula , Borneo , the Philippines , Palau , Fiji , New Guinea , and the Admiralty , Bismarck , and Solomon Islands .
Melampus coffea , commonly known as the coffee bean snail , is a species of small air - breathing salt marsh snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ellobiidae .
Carpathichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish from the Oligocene .
Placostylus eddystonensis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the subfamily Bothriembryontidae .
Penstemon albomarginatus is an uncommon species of penstemon known by the common name white - margined beardtongue .
Sitticus terebratus is a species of spiders from Salticidae family , that can be found in all European countries except for Belgium , Denmark , Spain , and Portugal , the Netherlands , and the Yugoslavian states .
Penicillium austroafricanum is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium
Incara multisquamatus is a species of sleeper goby known from brackish waters along the coasts of India and Australia .
Foetidia is a genus of flowering plants first described as a genus in 1788 .
Anchusa azurea is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae , known by the common names garden anchusa and Italian bugloss ( or just `` bugloss '' ) .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Myriangiopsis sulphurea .
Aulacephalodon is a genus of dicynodont from the Permian of South Africa and Zambia .
Hylarana macrodactyla is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
A pseudoscorpion , also known as a false scorpion or book scorpion , is an arachnid belonging to the order Pseudoscorpionida , also known as Pseudoscorpiones or Chelonethida .
Myristica dactyloides ( මලබොඩ)is a species of plant in the Myristicaceae family .
Lathyrus delnorticus is an uncommon species of wild pea known by the common name Del Norte pea .
Crassatellidae is a family of small saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs of the order Veneroida .
Heteropodagrion is a genus of damselflies in the family Muscidae .
Sternocera aequisignata is a species of beetles belonging to the Buprestidae family called ' Jeerjimbe ' in Kannada language .
The Monhysterida are an order in the phylum Nematoda .
Psilocybe cubensis is a species of psychedelic mushroom whose principal active compounds are psilocybin and psilocin .
Calochortus argillosus is a species of flowering plant in the lily family which is known by the common name clay mariposa lily .
Atlantirivulus is a disputed genus of rivuline fishes endemic to Brazil .
Clematis orientalis is a deciduous vine or scrambling shrub of the Clematis species , that originates from Asia and Central Europe .
Cnidoglanis macrocephalus is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Plotosidae , and is the only species of the genus Cnidoglanis .
Nebaliopsididae is a family of leptostracan crustaceans .
Malacothrix coulteri is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name snake 's head , or snake 's head desertdandelion .
Antennablennius adenensis , the Aden blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian Ocean , from the Red Sea to the Persian Gulf and Pakistan .
Eucalyptus bancroftii , commonly known as Bancroft 's red gum or orange gum , is a species of tree native to eastern Australia .
Muiria hortenseae ( `` Mouse - head '' ) is a rare dwarf species of succulent plant of the family Aizoaceae , indigenous to a very small area in the Little Karoo , Western Cape , South Africa .
Genyorchis micropetala is a species of plant in the family Orchidaceae .
Tetragonia implexicoma , commonly known as bower spinach , is a species of plant in the Aizoaceae , or ice - plant family .
Homosassa incudella is a species of snout moth in the genus Homosassa .
Frullania nisquallensis , commonly known as Hanging millipede liverwort , is a reddish - brown species of liverwort in the Jubulaceae family .
Dalmanites is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida .
Bathygobius burtoni is a species of goby native to the Atlantic shores of western Africa where it is a denizen of tide pools .
Romnalda ophiopogonoides is a vulnerable species of flowering lily plants only known ( endemic ) in a restricted area of the Wet Tropics of Queensland .
Omobranchus verticalis is a species of combtooth blenny found in brackish waters in Australia .
It consists of only one species , Epimydia dialampra , which can be found in mountainous steppe areas in South Siberia , East Yakutia and Northern Mongolia .
Tagiades calligana is a species of spread - winged skipper butterflies in the genus Tagiades .
Clypeomorus batillariaeformis , common name : the Necklace / Channeled Cerith , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cerithiidae .
Penicillium jensenii is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces citrinin , griseofulvin and fumagillin .
Tapinoma sessile is a species of ant that goes by the common names odorous house ant , stink ant , and coconut ant .
Passiflora arborea is a species of passion flower found in Columbia , Ecuador and Panama .
Zanthoxylum planispinum ( Bamboo - Leaf Prickly Ash , Winged Prickly Ash ) is a species of plant in the Rutaceae family .
Osteocephalus planiceps is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Ecuador , Peru , and possibly Brazil .
Upindauara bella is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Upindauara .
Fritillaria yuzhongensis is a plant species native to China ( Gansu , Henan , Ningxia , Shaanxi , Shanxi ) .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Phylloporthe vernoniae .
Euthycera chaerophylli is a species of fly in the family Sciomyzidae , the marsh flies or snail - killing flies .
Sinotympana incomparabilis is a new species of cicada from southern China that was discovered among a group of unidentified specimens in the Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique in Brussels .
Tolmiea is a genus of flowering plants containing two species native to western North America .
Cantharellopsis is a tan- to whitish - colored bryophilous monotypic genus in the Agaricales .
Rubus baileyanus , Bailey 's dewberry , is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Monotropa is a genus of 5 species of herbaceous perennial plants , formerly classified in the family Monotropaceae , but now included within the Ericaceae .
The Sula fruit dove ( Ptilinopus mangoliensis ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Edalorhina perezi ( Perez 's snouted frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Penicillium proteolyticum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces wortmannin .
Aromobates serranus ( common name : Pefaur 's rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Baryancistrus demantoides is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela .
Musa siamensis is an Asian tropical species of plant in the banana family native to Indo - China ( Thailand ) .
Gobiosoma is a genus of gobies native to fresh , brackish and marine waters of the Americas .
Myrmica is a genus of ants within the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Centrolene notostictum ( common name : cordillera giant glass frog ) is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Danio kyathit is a small , schooling species of fish in the family Cyprinidae , native to Burma .
Patriocetus is an extinct genus of toothed whale .
The Fischer 's lovebird ( Agapornis fischeri ) is a small parrot species of the Agapornis genus .
Zorilispiella rufipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Zorilispiella .
Vigna owahuensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Oahu cowpea .
Chromolucuma is a genus of plant in the Sapotaceae family described as a genus in 1925 .
Gastrophrynoides borneensis is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family , known commonly as the Borneo narrowmouth toad .
Zabrus laticollis is a species ground beetle in the Pelor subfamily that is can be found on Dodecanese islands and the Near East .
The single known species , Carpediemonas membranifera , is a small flagellate that was originally isolated from anaerobic intertidal sediment .

Runcinia acuminata is a species of crab spiders .
The longnose hawkfish , Oxycirrhites typus , is a species of hawkfish found on tropical reefs of the Indian Ocean and the Pacific Ocean , where it can be found at depths around 10 to 100 m ( 33 to 328 ft ) .
Crurifarcimen is a monotypic genus of millipedes containing the single species Crurifarcimen vagans .

Ophisops is a genus of wall lizards of the family Lacertidae .

Pachnodus velutinus was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Cerastidae .
Anguilla borneensis , also known as the Borneo eel is a species of the genus Anguilla found in Borneo .
Orcula dolium is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Orculidae .
Solanum physalifolium , known as hoe nightshade , Argentine nightshade , green nightshade and hairy nightshade , is a species in the family Solanaceae ( the nightshade family ) .
Coluber constrictor etheridgei , commonly known as the tan racer , is a nonvenomous colubrid snake , a subspecies of the eastern racer ( Coluber constrictor ) .
Clinus superciliosus , the Super klipfish ' or Highfin klipfish , is a species of clinid that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean from northern Namibia to the Kei River in South Africa where it can be found in the subtidal and intertidal zones .
Phycitodes gallicella is a species of snout moth which is endemic to France .
The deep - sea spiny eels are a family , Notacanthidae , of fishes found worldwide below 125 m ( 410 ft ) , and as deep as 3,500 m ( 11,500 ft ) .
Dwarf sirens are eel - like salamanders of the genus Pseudobranchus .
Cymbium olla , commonly known as the Algarve volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Adoketophyton is a genus of extinct vascular plants of the Early Devonian ( Pragian stage , around 410 million years ago ) .
Agnostotes orientalis is a species of agnostid trilobite belonging to the genus Agnostotes .
Ribes quercetorum is a species of currant known by the common names rock gooseberry , oak gooseberry and oakwoods gooseberry .
Lunella cinerea , common name the smooth moon turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Chloracantha is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , containing the single species Chloracantha spinosa .
The Nihoa millerbird ( Acrocephalus familiaris kingi ) is a subspecies of the millerbird .
Pleidae , the pygmy backswimmers , is a family of aquatic insects in the order Hemiptera ( infraorder Nepomorpha , or `` true water bugs '' ) .
Triraphis is a genus of African , Arabian , Australian , and Brazilian plants in the graass family .
Titiscania is a genus of slug - like sea snails , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Neritopsoidea .
Paragus tibialis , is a species of hoverfly found in many parts of Europe and North Africa .
Brimopsis kivuensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Brimopsis .
Rhynchosaurus ( beaked lizard ) is a genus of rhynchosaur that lived during the Middle Triassic Period .
Turbo kenwilliamsi , common name the beautiful turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Salix phylicifolia , the Tea - Leaved Willow , is a species of willow native to Northern Europe including Iceland , the Faroe Islands , Scandinavia , Finland , Russia , and Western Siberia .
Liatris cymosa , also known as Aggie - land gayfeather or branched blazing star , is a plant species in the aster family Asteraceae and genus Liatris .
Podoscypha petalodes is a widely distributed species of fungus in the family Meruliaceae .
Woodsia is a genus of ferns in the family Woodsiaceae , order Polypodiales , and class Polypodiopsida .
Cautor lutea is a species of small deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Triphoridae .
The Nillu rat ( Rattus montanus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Hylocereus is a genus of cacti , often referred to as night - blooming cactus ( though the term is also used for many other cacti ) .
Lupinus onustus is a species of lupine known by the common name Plumas lupine .
John T. Hunter described Micromyrtus grandis in 1996 , after coming across a colony of Micromyrtus on a porphyritic ridge that did not correspond to any known species .
Bryaninops erythrops , known commonly as the translucent coral goby or Erythrops goby , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiidae .
Muschleria is a genus of African flowering plants in the ironweed tribe within the daisy family .

Praealticus semicrenatus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific ocean , around Indonesia .

Diademodontidae is an extinct family of Triassic cynodonts .

Grigs are insects belonging to the orthopteran family Prophalangopsidae ( formerly known in some classifications as Haglidae ) .
Doellingeria umbellata , known by the common names tall flat - topped white aster , parasol whitetop , or tall white - aster , is a North American plant species in the aster family .

Synodontis arnoulti is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Volta River basin of Burkina Faso and Ghana .
Xylaria is a genus of ascomycetous fungi commonly found growing on dead wood .
The Australian swamp rat -- also known as the Eastern swamp rat ( Rattus lutreolus ) -- is a species of rat found near the coast of south and eastern Australia .
Pinus armandii ( family Pinaceae ) , the Armand pine or Chinese white pine , is a species of pine native to China , occurring from southern Shanxi west to southern Gansu and south to Yunnan , with outlying populations in Anhui .
Reutealis is a monotypic plant genus in the family Euphorbiaceae .
Sepia plana is a species of cuttlefish native to the coast of Australia , specifically the North West Shelf ( 12 ° 04′S 122 ° 59′E to 17 ° 55.5′S 118 ° 16.0′E ) .
Torreyochloa erecta is a species of grass known by the common name spiked false mannagrass .

Parkia parrii is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Fiji .
Uloceras is an early nautiloid genus named by Zhuravleva , 1974 , that lived during the middle Devonian
The granulated catfish ( Pterodoras granulosus ) is a species of thorny catfish found in the Paraná and Amazon basin as well as the coastal drainages of Suriname and Guyana .
Micranthes bryophora is a species of saxifrage known by the common name bud saxifrage .
Bahiopsis is a genus of North American flowering plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Ornithodesmus ( meaning `` bird link '' ) is a genus of small , dromaeosaurid dinosaur from the Isle of Wight in England , dating to about 125 million years ago .
Ceropegia sandersonii is a species of flowering plant in the genus Ceropegia ( Apocynaceae ) , native to Mozambique , South Africa , and Swaziland .
Plagiognathops microlepis , the smallscale yellowfin , is a species of cyprinid fish found in China and Russia .
Houstonia micrantha , the southern bluet , is a plant species in the coffee family .
The rodent subfamily Sigmodontinae is one of the most diverse groups of mammals .
Haemaphysalis leporispalustris , the rabbit tick ( occasionally known as the grouse tick ) , is a species of tick that is widely distributed in the Americas , stretching from Alaska to Argentina .
Ptilodus is a genus of mammals from the extinct order of Multituberculata , and lived during the Paleocene in North America .
Palaeotapirus is an extinct genus of tapir from the Late Miocene of Eurasia .

Malus glaucescens , commonly known as Dunbar crabapple , is a species in the genus Malus in the family Rosaceae .

Manitherionyssus heterotarsus is a species of mite placed in its own family , Manitherionyssidae , in the order Mesostigmata .
