Wobbegong is the common name given to the 12 species of carpet sharks in the family Orectolobidae .
Trisetum spicatum is a species of grass known by the common name spike trisetum and spike false oat .
Xianshou is a genus of small allotherian mammal known from the Oxfordian stage of the Jurassic period , approximately 160 million years ago .
Sea cucumbers are echinoderms from the class Holothuroidea .
Nocomis is a genus of cyprinid fish native to North America .
Andropogon virginicus is a species of grass known by several common names , including broomsedge bluestem , yellowsedge bluestem and ( in Australia , because it was introduced to that country after being used as packaging for bottles of American whiskey ) whiskey grass .
Barycholos ( common name Chimbo frogs ) is a genus of small craugastorid frogs found in southeastern Brazil and tropical lowland Ecuador .
Antennaerenea niveosignata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Antennaerenea .
Megalobrama is a genus of cyprinid fish , consisting of six species native to fresh water in China and eastern Russia .
Paragomphus sabicus , the Sabi hooktail , is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Carabus exiguus absconditus is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Sichuan , China .
Synodus tectus , the Tectus lizardfish , is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Indo - West Pacific .
Herina lacustris is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in France , Portugal , Spain , Morocco , and Algeria .
Maylandia mbenjii is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from Mbenji Island .
Histoctopus is an octopus genus containing two species :
Caribachlamys sentis , or the Sentis scallop , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Pectinidae .
†Mautodontha consobrina was a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Hyphoradulum conspicuum , found in Europe .
Gaillardia spathulata , western blanketflower , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Ronald 's opossum ( Monodelphis ronaldi ) is a South American opossum species of the family Didelphidae .
Dermatophyllum secundiflorum is a species of flowering shrub or small tree in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is native to the southwestern United States ( Texas , New Mexico ) and Mexico ( Chihuahua and Coahuila south to Hidalgo , Puebla and Querétaro ) .
Emblemariopsis signifer is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs in the western Atlantic ocean .
Mytilaster is a genus of marine mussels .
Solanum douglasii is a species of nightshade known by the common name greenspot nightshade .
Euchelus mysticus , common name the mysticus margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chilodontidae .
The Perdido Key beach mouse ( Peromyscus polionotus trissyllepsis ) is an endangered subspecies of the oldfield mouse .
Cassida sareptana is a species of brownish beetle in the leaf beetle family , that can be found in Kazakhstan , Mongolia , Russia and Ukraine .
Lupinus polyphyllus ( large - leaved lupine , big - leaved lupine , many - leaved lupine or , primarily in cultivation , garden lupin ) is a species of lupine ( lupin ) native to western North America from southern Alaska and British Columbia east to Quebec , and western Wyoming , and south to Utah and California .
Therea petiveriana , variously called the `` desert cockroach '' , `` seven - spotted cockroach '' or `` Indian domino cockroach '' , is a species of crepuscular cockroach found in southern India .
Germanodactylus ( `` German finger '' ) is a genus of dsungaripteroid pterodactyloid pterosaur from Late Jurassic - age rocks of Germany , including the Solnhofen limestone .
Paphiopedilum hennisianum is a species of orchid endemic to central Philippines ( Panay , Negros islands of the Visayas ) .
Allium shevockii is a rare species of wild onion known by the common name Spanish Needle onion .
Zodarion granulatum is a spider species found in Cyprus , Greece , Turkey , Lebanon and Israel .
Angraecum subulatum is a species of comet orchid that can be found in Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Côte d'Ivoire , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon , Ghana , Guinea , Liberia , Nigeria and Sierra Leone .
Cotoneaster obovatus is a species of flowering plant in the Rosaceae family that can be found in Kangra and northeastern Punjab provinces of India .
Aguascalientia is an extinct genus of miniature camels , endemic to North America ( as far south as the Panama Canal ) during the Early Miocene 23.030 - -20.6 mya existing for approximately 2.43 million years .
Odorrana lungshengensis ( common names : Lung - shen - hsien frog , Lungshen odorous frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is endemic to China .
Tylototriton is a genus of newts known as crocodile newts or knobby newts .
Pistacia integerrima is a species of pistachio tree native to Asia , commonly called zebrawood .
Tuberculobasis karitiana is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae first identified in Rondônia , Brazil .
Clathrina darwini is a species of calcareous sponge of the genus Clathrina from the Sunda Shelf .
Zosteraceae ( the seagrass family ) is a family of marine perennial flowering plants found in temperate and subtropical coastal waters , with the highest diversity located around Korea and Japan .
Trichocentrum luridum is a species of orchid found from Mexico to northern South America .
Aiphanes lindeniana is a species of palm that is endemic to Colombia .
Abrothrix jelskii , also known as Jelski 's Altiplano Mouse , Jelski 's Grass Mouse , or the Ornate Akodont , is a species of rodent in the genus Abrothrix of family Cricetidae .
Kriegeriales is an order of Fungi that are mostly yeasts and can be found from a variety of places , ranging from arctic waters to tropical ferns .
Penicillium melinii is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces griseofulvin and beta - Nitropropionic acid .
Viviparus acerosus is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae , the river snails .
Ethalia bellardii is a species of sea snail with a top - shaped shell , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Kadua parvula ( formerly Hedyotis parvula ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name rockface star - violet .
Maxwellia santarosana , common name the `` Santa Rosa murex '' is a species of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails .
Physella acuta is a species of small , left - handed or sinistral , air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae .
Scopula subdecorata is the montane sister - species of Scopula vacuata .
Cantherhines dumerilii is a species of fish in the family Monacanthidae , the filefishes .
Cancellaria obesa , common name : the obese nutmeg , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
Eburia bimaculata is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Antigua and Barbuda .
Dyscrasis hendeli is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Dyscrasis of the family Ulidiidae .
Hebeloma aminophilum , commonly known as the ghoul fungus , is a species of mushroom in the Hymenogastraceae family .
Iris kolpakowskiana ( or ' Kolpakowski 's Iris ' ) is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus Hermodactyloides and section Monolepsis .
Leptinaria unilamellata is a species of tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Bidens trichosperma , the marsh beggar - ticks or marsh tickseed , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Brachyglanis is a genus of Three - barbeled catfishes native to South America .
Erigeron pygmaeus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name pygmy fleabane , or pygmy daisy .
Mictyris guinotae is a species of soldier crab of genus Mictyris , endemic to the Ryukyu Islands of Japan .
Nicholsicypris is a genus of cyprinid fish containing two species , one in Vietnam and the other in China .
Lovoa swynnertonii ( also called brown mahogany or Kilimanjaro mahogany ) is a species of plant in the Meliaceae family .
The white Amur bream ( Parabramis pekinensis ) is a species of cyprinid freshwater fish , of the monotypic genus Parabramis .
Rhodymenia cinnabarina is a species of red algae first described in 1841 .
Parascolymia rowleyensis ( Veron , 1985 ) is a species of large polyp stony corals .
Anchiopsis is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , which existed in what is now New York , U.S.A. It was described by Delo in 1935 , and the type species is Anchiopsis anchiops , which was originally described as Calymene anchiops by Green in 1832 .
Nannolytoceras is an extinct genus of lytoceratid ammonite , family Lytoceratidae , with a stratigraphic range extending from the Bajocian age to Bathonian age ( Medium Jurassic ) .
Cecilioides acicula , common name the `` blind snail '' or `` blind awlsnail '' , is a species of very small , air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ferussaciidae .
Bromeliohyla , sometimes known as the bromeliad treefrogs , is a genus of frogs in the Hylidae family .
Wesmaelius mathewesi is an extinct species of lacewing in the neuropteran family Hemerobiidae known from an Eocene fossil found in North America
Pederpes ( ' Peter 's Foot ' ) is an extinct genus of early Carboniferous tetrapod , dating from 348 - 347.6 Ma in the Tournaisian age ( lower Mississippian ) .
The genus Sactoceras was named by Hyatt ( 1884 ) .
Wunderlichia is a genus of Brazilian trees in the gerbera tribe within the daisy family .
Ardisia escallonioides , the Island marlberry , is a plant species native to the West Indies and neighboring areas .
Sairostoma is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Streptaxidae .
Ameerega ingeri , formerly Epipedobates ingeri , is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family endemic to Colombia .
Erigeron wilkenii is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Wilken 's fleabane and Dieter 's erigeron .
Ozyptila praticola is a species of crab spider found throughout Europe and the Middle East .
Lycus foliaceus is a species of beetles belonging to the Lycidae family .
Sesbania tomentosa , commonly known as Oahu riverhemp and ʻŌhai , is an endangered species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to the main Hawaiian Islands as well as Nihoa and Necker Island .
Astragalus cremnophylax is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common names sentry milkvetch and cliff milkvetch .
Callionymus sphinx is a species of dragonet known from the waters off of the Northern Territory , Australia .
Astatotilapia desfontainii is a species of cichlid found in Algeria and Tunisia .
Ramphotyphlops bituberculatus is a species of snake , also known as `` Peters 's Blind Snake '' , which is in the Typhlopidae family .
Spaniopappus is a genus of Cuban plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Sphedanolestes cingulatus is a species of assassin bug belonging to the family Reduviidae , in the subfamily Harpactorinae .
Euphorbia bourgeana , also sometimes called the Tree Euphorbia , is a species of spurge native to La Gomera in the Canary Islands .
Hippocamelus is a genus of Cervidae , the deer family .
Salix hastata is a species of flowering plant in the willow family , known by the common name halberd willow .
Arachis repens ( Portuguese common name : Grama - amendoim ) is a species in the Fabaceae family native to Brazil .
Luciobarbus pectoralis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Luciobarbus from the Orontes River basin ( including Asi Nehri ) in the Near East .
The Manus friarbird or white - naped friarbird ( Philemon albitorques ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Procambarus cometes , the Mississippi flatwoods crayfish is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Parametaria dupontii , tre Dupont 's Dove Shell or False Cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Marstonia ogmorhaphe , common names the royal marstonia or royal springsnail , is a minute species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Hydrobiidae , the mud snails .
Cuthona speciosa , common name the `` candy nudibranch '' , is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Tergipedidae .
Calathus carvalhoi is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that is endemic to the Azores .
Rhododendron galactinum ( 乳黄叶杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to western Sichuan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 2900 - -3500 meters .
Odorrana chapaensis ( Vietnam sucker frog or Chapa torrent frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is found in southern Yunnan in China and in northern Vietnam .
Epopaea acuta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Epopaea .
Tugali elegans is a species of large sea snail or limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the Family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
It was long held that Darwin 's fox was a subspecies of the South American gray fox ( L. griseus ) ; however , the discovery of a small population of Darwin 's fox on the mainland in Nahuelbuta National Park in 1990 and subsequent genetic analysis has clarified the fox 's status as a unique species .
Morelia amethistina is a non - venomous species of snake , known as the amethystine , scrub python or Sanca permata locally , found in Indonesia , Papua New Guinea and Australia .
Phoenix canariensis is a species of flowering plant in the palm family Arecaceae , native to the Canary Islands .
Payena selangorica is a species of plant in the family Sapotaceae .
Ruhuhuaria is an extinct genus of owenettid procolophonoid reptile known from the Middle Triassic Manda Beds of southwestern Tanzania .
The Alamos mud turtle ( Kinosternon alamosae ) is a species of mud turtle in the family Kinosternidae .
Spathopria is an extinct genus of wasp currently comprising a single species Spathopria sayrevillensis .
Eucalyptus oraria , also known as Ooragmandee , is a mallee species of Eucalyptus that is native to Western Australia , occurring in coastal and near - coastal areas .
Aplysina insularis , the yellow - green candle sponge or yellow tube sponge , is a species of demosponge that is found on reefs in the Caribbean Sea and the Gulf of Mexico .
Chromodoris annae is a species of sea slug , a very colourful nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chromodorididae .
Townsend 's mole is classified as Least Concern by the IUCN , however in Canada it is considered an endangered species .
Phalangium is a genus of harvestmen , that occurs mostly in the Old World .
Hyocephalidae are a small family of Heteroptera which are endemic to Australia .
Megalochelys atlas is an extinct species of cryptodiran turtle from the Miocene through to the Pleistocene periods .
Allium peninsulare is a North American species of wild onion .
Bremia is a genus of water moulds in the family Peronosporaceae .
Leporellus is a genus of headstanders found in South America .
Acromantis luzonica , common name Luzon mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in the Philippine .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Anisostagma rotundatum .
Schizothorax labiatus or Kunar snowtrout is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Schizothorax .
Bridetherium is an extinct genus of morganucodontan from Early Jurassic deposits of southern Wales , United Kingdom .
Streptomyces reticuliscabiei is a streptomycete bacterium species that is associated with netted scab in potatoes .
Nebria nigerrima is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Asian countries such as Armenia , Iran , and Turkey .
Allobates is a genus of frogs in the Aromobatidae family .
Conus sponsalis , common name the sponsal cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Cephalanthus glabratus is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family , Rubiaceae , that is native to South America .
Etropus is a genus of large - tooth flounders native to the coastal waters of the Americas .
Caumontisphinctes is an ammonoid genus from the ammonitid superfamily Perkinsonataceae that lived during the Bajocian stage of the Middle Jurassic .
Baccharis wrightii is a North American species of shrubs in the aster family known by the common name Wright 's baccharis or false willow .
Caulanthus barnebyi , the Black Rock wild cabbage , is a plant species endemic to a small region in the US State of Nevada .
Cyclophoridae is a taxonomic family of small to large tropical land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the informal group Architaenioglossa belonging to the clade Caenogastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Mniodes is a genus of South American flowering plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Huperzia compacta is a species of plant in the family Lycopodiaceae .
Podargus is a small genus of in the Podargidae ( frogmouth ) family .
Oritrophium tergoalbum is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
Calliostoma jujubinum , common name the jujube top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Tryonia is a genus of freshwater snails in the family Hydrobiidae . This genus is sometimes placed in the family Cochliopidae .
Pelagiellidae is an extinct family of Paleozoic fossil marine molluscs .
Hypna is a monotypic genus of Neotropical leafwing butterflies .
Trifolium pannonicum is a species of clover known by the common name Hungarian Clover .
Sanvitalia abertii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Abert 's creeping zinnia and Abert 's sanvitalia .
Corybas aconitiflorus is a species of terrestrial orchid native to eastern Australia , from south - east Queensland to Tasmania .
Blaxotes wollastoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Blaxotes .
Ranunculus calandrinioides ( high alpine buttercup ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Ranunculaceae , native to the Atlas Mountains of North Africa .
Adelptes clavipalpis is a species of beetle in the Adelptes genus .
Rapisma is a genus of moth lacewings , Ithonidae .
Sanvitalia procumbens with the common name of Mexican creeping zinnia is the type species of the genus Sanvitalia and a member of the family Asteraceae and tribe Heliantheae .
Linaria maroccana is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names Moroccan toadflax and annual toadflax .
Arnica mollis is a North American species of arnica in the sunflower family , known by the common name soft arnica , or hairy arnica .
Atriplex serenana is a species of saltbush known by the common names bractscale and stinking orach .
Menetus dilatatus is a species of small air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Leptolalax gracilis is a frog species in the family Megophryidae .
Scutiger pingwuensis is a species of toad in the family Megophryidae known commonly as the Pingwu lazy toad and the Pingwu alpine toad .
Murexsul octogonus , or the octagonal murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Neokochia americana ( syn . Bassia americana , Kochia americana ) is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family , subfamily Camphorosmoideae , known by the common name green molly .
Chiloglanis modjensis is a species of upside - down catfish ( Mochokidae ) endemic to Ethiopia .
Daedaleopsis confragosa , commonly known as the thin walled maze polypore or the blushing bracket , is a species of polypore fungus in the family Polyporaceae .
Nebria biseriata is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in China and Amur Oblast of Russia .
Platyrhacidae is a family of polydesmidan millipedes distributed in Southeast Asia and tropical Central and South America .
Cyathea atropurpurea is a species of tree fern native to the islands of Luzon , Mindanao , Leyte and Mindanao in the Philippines , where it grows in forest at above 1000 m. The erect trunk is slender and may be up to 3 m tall .
Multivalvulida is an order of myxozoan .
Pyrenaria buisanensis is a species of tea endemic to Taiwan .
Platygillellus is a genus of sand stargazers native to the Atlantic and Pacific coasts of the Americas .
Ziziphus mucronata , known as the Buffalo thorn , `` blinkblaar - wag-'n - bietjie '' in Afrikaans and `` mphasamhala '' in Tsonga , is a species in the Rhamnaceae family .
Palaemon affinis is a species of shrimp of the family Palaemonidae .
Gonospira duponti is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Streptaxidae .
Tridentea is a genus of plant in family Asclepiadaceae , first described as a genus in 1812 .
Acridocarpus socotranus is a species of plant in the family Malpighiaceae .
Felis chaus nilotica is a subspecies of the jungle cat .
Spergularia rubra , the red sandspurry or red sand - spurrey , is a plant species in the pink family .
Emiliana is an extinct genus of planthopper in the Tropiduchidae tribe Emilianini and containing the single species Emiliana alexandri .
Tagarosuchus is an extinct genus of Early Cretaceous protosuchian - grade crocodyliform .
Angarocaris is an extinct genus of basal chelicerate .
Aphis spiraecola is a species of aphid described in 1914 by Edith Marion Patch .
Harpadon erythraeus is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Western Indian Ocean .
Cynips quercusfolii is a gall wasp species in the genus Cynips .
Solanum crispum is a species of flowering plant in the Solanaceae family , native to Chile and Peru .
Iresine heterophylla ( Standley 's bloodleaf ) is a plant species native to the southwestern United States and also to Mexico .
Eriogonum eremicola is a rare species of wild buckwheat known by the common names Telescope Peak buckwheat and Wild Rose Canyon buckwheat .
Eiders ( /ˈaɪ.dər/ ) are large seaducks in the genus Somateria .
Maytenus aquifolia , the Espinheira - santa , is an endemic tree ( sometimes shrub ) species from the Atlantic Forest Biome in Brazil , occurring in the regions Sudeste ( in Minas Gerais , Rio de Janeiro and São Paulo states ) and Sul ( Paraná , Santa Catarina and Rio Grande do Sul states ) .
Paraclinus infrons , the Bald blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to reefs of the Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from Florida and the Bahamas over to Belize .
Alburnus volviticus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus , that is endemic to Greece .
Allium listera is a species of wild onion endemic to China .
Rhododendron flammeum , the piedmont azalea or Oconee azalea , is a plant species native to the US States of Georgia and South Carolina .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Discoxylaria myrmecophila .
The Bali tiger ( Panthera tigris balica ) , harimau Bali in Indonesian , or samong in Balinese , is an extinct tiger subspecies that was native to the Indonesian island of Bali .
Goniurosaurus is a genus of geckos , containing 17 species .
Brachycerus ornatus , common name Red - spotted Lily Weevil or Moose Face Lily Weevil , is a species of Curculionidae family , Brachycerinae subfamily .
Chrysomya albiceps is a species belonging to the blow fly family , Calliphoridae .
Moganopterus is an extinct genus of boreopterid pterosaur from the Early Cretaceous of western Liaoning Province , China .
Vulpia is a widespread genus of plants in the grass family , native to many countries around the world and naturalized in many of the nations to which it is not native .
Xylomelum occidentale , commonly known as the western woody pear , is a tree species in the family Proteaceae .
Encelia californica is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name California brittlebush .
Mimulus inconspicuus is an uncommon species of monkeyflower known by the common name smallflower monkeyflower .
Cotopaxia is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae family , comprising two species :
The Keroplatidae are a family of small flies known as fungus gnats .
Juncus luciensis is a species of rush known by the common name Santa Lucia dwarf rush .
The Northeastern coyote ( Canis latrans thamnos ) is a subspecies of coyote native to north - central Saskatchewan east to southern Ontario , historically south to northern Indiana and west to Missouri .
Carica is a genus of flowering plants in the family Caricaceae including C. papaya , the papaya ( syn . C. peltata , C. posoposa ) , a widely cultivated fruit tree native to the American tropics .
The Travuniidae are a small family of harvestman with little more than ten described species , within the suborder Laniatores .
Purussaurus is an extinct genus of giant caiman that lived in South America during the Miocene epoch , 8 million years ago .
Chilara taylori , the spotted cusk - eel , is a species of cusk - eel found along the eastern coast of the Pacific Ocean where it is found at depths of around 280 metres ( 920 ft ) from Washington , USA to Ecuador .
Falsoparmena malaccensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsoparmena .
Oxycera rara , the four - barred major , is a European species of soldier fly .
Prorastomidae is a taxonomic family of extinct animals from Jamaica , related to the extant manatees and dugong .
Blancoa is a genus with a single species of perennial herb in the family Haemodoraceae , endemic to the south west of Western Australia .
The genus Pseudechis contains the group of elapids commonly referred to as the black snakes .
Pseudoharpya opulenta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudoharpya .
The Recurvirostridae are a family of birds in the wader suborder Charadrii .
Andricus quercuscalicis is a gall wasp species inducing knopper galls .
Tropidophorus grayi , the spiny waterside skink , is a species of highly secretive lizard .
Cicindela columbica is a species of beetle in the tiger beetle subfamily , Cicindelinae , known commonly as the Columbia River tiger beetle .
Oleandra hainanensis is a species of fern in the Oleandraceae family .
Curiofrea curiosa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Curiofrea .
Frankia alni is a species of actinomycete filamentous bacterium that lives in symbiosis with actinorhizal plants in the genus Alnus .
Teracotona is a genus of moths in the Arctiidae family from the Afrotropics .
Phacelia mohavensis is a species of phacelia known by the common name Mojave phacelia .
Neogonodactylus is a genus of mantis shrimp .
Compsognathus ( /kɒmpˈsɒɡnəθəs/ ; Greek kompsos/κομψός ; `` elegant '' , `` refined '' or `` dainty '' , and gnathos/γνάθος ; `` jaw '' ) is a genus of small , bipedal , carnivorous theropod dinosaurs .
Formica truncorum is a species of wood ant from the genus Formica .
Paraphanis rougemonti is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraphanis .
Polygala curtissii , the Curtiss ' milkwort or Appalachian milkwort , is a species of flowering plant in the milkwort family .
Thyasiridae is a family of bivalve molluscs , including the cleft clams .
Eburna is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Olividae .
Davaineidae is the name of a family of tapeworms that includes helminth parasites of vertebrates .
Dothideomycetes is the largest and most diverse class of ascomycete fungi .
Dasyerrus pilosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Dasyerrus .
Sarcosuchus ( /ˌsɑːrkoʊˈsuːkəs/ ; meaning `` flesh crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of crocodyliform and distant relative of the crocodile that lived 112 million years ago .
Paraclinus integripinnis , the Reef finspot , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of North America from southern California to Baja California .
Sedecula is a genus of fungi in the order Agaricales .
Sphaeralcea angustifolia is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names copper globemallow and narrow - leaved globemallow .
Melica stuckertii , is a grass species in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Argentina and southern South America .
Ancyridris is a small genus of myrmicine ants , with only two described species from New Guinea .
Sepiadarium auritum is a species of cuttlefish native to the eastern Indian Ocean off northwestern Australia .
Deborrea robinsoni is a species of bagworm native to Madagascar .
The genus Anatea contains only one species , Anatea formicaria , an ant - mimicking spider .
Hoheria is a genus of six species of flowering plants in the family Malvaceae .
The Podocopa are a subclass of ostracods .
Pachymenes is a small but widely distributed neotropical genus of potter wasps .
Boechera perstellata ( syn . Arabis perstellata ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Braun 's rockcress and Nevada rockcress .
Pseudomonoxenus crossotoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudomonoxenus .
Tityus serrulatus , the Brazilian yellow scorpion , is a species of scorpion belonging to the family Buthidae .
The Prochaetodermatidae are a family of small worm - shaped ( < 1 cm ) chaetoderm molluscs .
Bradyrhizobium diazoefficiens is a species of bacteria from the genus of Bradyrhizobium .
Axia napoleona is a species of moth of the Cimeliidae family .
Caseolus calvus is a species of small air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Anthurium bushii is a species of plant in the arum family , Araceae .
Cardisoma carnifex is a species of terrestrial crab found in coastal regions from the east coast of Africa and the Red Sea across the Indo - Pacific to the Line Islands and the Tuamotu Archipelago .
Pteris longifolia , the longleaf brake is a species of fern in the Pteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .
Pantilema angustum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pantilema .
Cephalenicodes bimaculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cephalenicodes .
Deroplatys philippinica , common name Philippines dead leaf mantis , is a species of dead leaf mantis from the Philippines .
Vasconcellea goudotiana ( also known as papayuelo ) is a species of flowering plant in the Caricaceae family .
Hybos culiciformis , common name Dance Fly , is a species of flies belonging to the family hybotid .
Bombus terrestris , the buff - tailed bumblebee or large earth bumblebee , is one of the most numerous bumblebee species in Europe .
Ilex guayusa ( /ˈaɪlɛks ˈɡwaɪjuːsə/ or /ˈaɪlɛks ˈwaɪjuːsə/ ) is a species of tree of the holly genus , native to the Amazon Rainforest .
The species Bundibugyo ebolavirus is the taxonomic home of one virus , Bundibugyo virus ( BDBV ) , that forms filamentous virions and is closely related to the infamous Ebola virus ( EBOV ) .
Ageratina havanensis , the Havana snakeroot or white mistflower , is a species of flowering shrub in the sunflower family , native to Texas , Cuba , and northeastern and east - central Mexico ( Veracruz , Tamaulipas , Coahuila , Nuevo León , Hidalgo , San Luis Potosí , Puebla , Guanajuato , Querétaro ) .
Sphagnum capillifolium , the red bogmoss or small red peat moss , is a species of peat moss native to Canada , the northern United States , Greenland and Europe .
Kunzea glabrescens is a species of Western Australian shrub known by the common name spearwood .
Cetichthys is a genus of flabby whalefishes .
Sthenopis purpurascens , the four - spotted ghost moth , is a species of moth of the family Hepialidae .
Cyrtopodion baturensis is a species of gecko found in Pakistan and India .
Syntrophaceticus schinkii is a species of anaerobic , syntrophic acetate - oxidizing bacterium , the type species of its genus .
Barbus magdalenae ( the Bunjako barb ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
†Partula variabilis was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Pachyrhynchus infernalis is a weevil species in the family Brentidae .
Lupinus formosus , the summer lupine or western lupine , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Tamandua is a genus of anteaters with two species : the southern tamandua ( T. tetradactyla ) and the northern tamandua ( T. mexicana ) .
Chaseella pseudohydra is a species of epiphytic orchids , of the monospecific genus Chaseella .
Solenostomus , also known as ghost pipefishes , false pipefishes or tubemouth fishes , is a genus of fishes in the order Syngnathiformes .
Hecistopteris is a fern genus in the Vittarioideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .
Catoptria margaritella , also known as Pearl - band Grass Veneer , is a species of moth of the family Crambidae .
Gymnodoris subflavais a species of colorful sea slug , a nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Gymnodorididae .
Eutrombicula batatas is a species of chigger ( trombiculid mite ) .
Cyrestinae is the name of a small subfamily of nymphalid brush - footed butterflies .
Cyrioides imperialis , commonly known as the banksia jewel beetle , is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae native to southeastern Australia .
Aeschynomene virginica is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Virginia jointvetch and sensitive jointvetch .
Syntripsa is a genus of freshwater crabs found in Sulawesi .
Cirsium clavatum ( Fish Lake thistle ) is a North American species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Kosteletzkya ( pronounced Kost - el - lets - kee - uh ) ) is a genus of the plant family Malvaceae that includes the seashore mallow ( K. virginica ) .
Marattia is a small genus of primitive , large , fleshy eusporangiate ferns .
Crepidodera nitidula is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Albania , Andorra , Croatia , Greece , Ireland , Liechtenstein , San Marino , Spain , Vatican City , and various European islands .
Harpulina arausiaca , common name the gold - banded volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Aiteng mysticus is a species of sea slug in the family Aitengidae , found around Hisamatsu , Miyako - jima , Okinawa , Japan .
The Sierra Juarez brook frog , Duellmanohyla ignicolor , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Mexico .
Lebia analis is a species of beetle in the family of Carabidae , Harpalinae subfamily .
Davidsea attenuata is only known species of the genus Davidsea .
Papilio garamas is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Mexico , Guatemala , Honduras , Panama and Costa Rica .
Choeradodis is a genus of praying mantises with common names such as shield mantis , hood mantis ( or hooded mantis ) , and leaf mantis ( or leafy mantis ) because of their extended , leaf - like thoraxes .
Maratus sceletus ( colloquially named skeletorus ) is a species of the peacock spider genus , or more generically , a member of the Australian jumping spider family .
Anatoma aupouria is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Anatomidae .
Andrena agilissima is a species of mining bee .
The Tremex magus is a species sawfly , native to most of Europe and parts of Russia .
Makinoa crispata is the only species of liverwort in the genus Makinoa and family Makinoaceae .
Carelia lymani was a species of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Amastridae and superfamily Cochlicopoidea .
Lilium parryi , common name lemon lily , is a rare species of lily .
Physalis ( /ˈfaɪsəlɪs/ , sometimes /faɪˈseɪlɪs/ , from physalis = bladder ) is a genus of flowering plants in the nightshade family ( Solanaceae ) , which grow in warm temperate and subtropical regions of the world .
Crayweed ( Phyllospora comosa ) is a species of brown algae in the Seirococcaceae family .
Colobometra perspinosa is a species of Echinodermata known by the common name Black feather star .
Halocoryza maindroni is a species of brown coloured ground beetle in the subfamily Scaritinae which can be found on Comoros , Madagascar , Mauritius , Mayotte , and Réunion , as well as in Djibouti , Saudi Arabia , and Somalia .
Isanda murrea is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Sarcodon martioflavus is a species of tooth fungus in the family Bankeraceae , found in Europe and North America .
Lactarius pubescens , commonly known as the downy milk cap , is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family .
Adriana Ferrarese del Bene ( born c. 1755 in Ferrara - died after 1804 in Venice ) was an Italian operatic soprano .
Marie Brema ( 28 February 1856 -- 22 March 1925 ) was an English dramatic mezzo - soprano singer in concert , operatic and oratorio work in the last decade of the 19th and the first decade of the 20th centuries .
